(11, 'BTU-216F5DD7', 2, 'Mr.', 'Yakubu', 'Issifu Asoor', 'yakubuasoe10@yahoo.com', '0209021822', 'Bolgatanga Technical University,Post Office Box 767, Bolgatanga', 'Bolgatanga', 'Sherigo', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Islam', 'married', 'Suweiba Yussif', 'House Number c. 287, Bolga Tindonmolgo', 'Amin Ayamga Yakubu -08/11.2014\r\nHakim Akayelsi Yakubu  20/05/2019\r\nRahim Bayelsa Yakubu  29/05/2022', NULL, 'GHA-722619869-4', '1985-07-23', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Electronic Science and Technology of China (UESTC)', 7, 'H. Xiong, Y. Bao, X. Nie, and Y. I. Asoor, “Server-aided attribute-based signature supporting expressive access structures for industrial internet of things,” IEEE Transactions on Industrial Informatics, vol. 16, no. 2, pp. 1013–1023, Feb. 2020, doi: 10.1109/TII.2019.2921516.', NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Research and Soccer', '2 weeks.', NULL, 'Dr Oswin Anaba Agandaa', 'Lecturer', 'Head of Department, Liberal Studies, Bolgatanga Technical University.', 'Post Office Box 767, Bolgatanga', '0244574332', 'oswin.anaba@bolgatu.edu.gh', 'Prof. Edward Yellakuor Baagyere,', 'Lecturer', 'Dean of the School of Computing and Information Sciences (SCIS) at -UTAS.', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences, Navrongo (UTAS).', '+233-249990362', NULL, 'Prof. Xuyuan Nie', 'Lecturer', 'Supervisor International Students', 'University of Electronic Science and Technology of China (UESTC)   Chengdu, Sichuan, China', '0086-28-61831361', NULL, 'BTU_216F5DD7_cv_6a0ec53be8cd59.43466580.pdf', 'BTU CV Current.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.140.146', '2026-05-21 08:41:31', '2026-06-12 23:22:50', 'BTU_216F5DD7_photo_6a0ec53be8cdb7.42141529.jpeg', 'pic bt.jpeg'),
(10, 'BTU-4C10CE56', 5, 'Mr.', 'Adakudugu', 'Abdul Rahman', 'aadakudugu@gmail.com', '+233240770005', 'C/o Awe SHTS \r\nBox 105.\r\nNavrongo.', 'Navrongo', 'Navrongo', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Islam', 'married', 'Asaaba Josephine', 'CA 011', 'Adakudugu Latif Junior 11-04-2022\r\n\r\nAdakudugu Ridwan   07 -11-2025', NULL, 'GHA-715816365-6', '1993-11-30', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences, Navrongo.', 3, 'A manuscript is being prepared for publication on my Mphil thesis.', 'I have taught Applied physics and mathematics for over 4 years and has also supervised and conducted engineering physics practicals at both the university level and the senior high school level.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading and Enquiring.', 'Immediately.', 'I have enrolled in my terminal degree (PhD) at the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology. I am currently undertaking my 1 year course work and will begin with my thesis shortly.', 'Professor Aaron Adazabra', 'Head of physics department,  UTAS,  Navrongo.', 'Head of physics department', 'UTAS, box 24, Navrongo.', '0543284917', 'adazabraaron@yahoo.com', 'Dr. Jonas Bugase', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Lab Coordinator', 'UTAS, box 24, Navrongo.', '0249588269', 'jbugase@uds.edu.gh', 'Dr. Mathew Amekpewu', 'Senior lecturer', 'Senior lecturer', 'UDS, Tamale Box 1350.', '0243334812', 'mamek219@gmail.com', 'BTU_4C10CE56_cv_6a0eaa788eb4d2.49648708.pdf', 'Curriculum Vitae_Rahman (1).pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.227.28', '2026-05-21 06:47:20', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_4C10CE56_photo_6a0eaa788eb537.09560992.jpg', '1000000053.jpg'),
(4, 'BTU-8DEA9268', 1, 'Dr.', 'LINUS', 'Kpelle', 'linuskpelle25@gmail.com', '0504837903', 'Vittin Street', 'Nandom', 'Nandom', 'Upper West', 'GHANAIAN', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-723745005-1', '1993-08-03', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Cape Coast', 5, '1.	Osei, G.N., Bockarie, A., Akpalu, A., Adueming, P.O.W., Antwi, M.H., Appiah, F., Kpelle, L., Donkor, D.M. and Simpong, D.L., 2025. Diagnostic potential of near?infrared spectroscopy in mild cognitive impairment and neurodegenerative disorders: Implications for resource?limited settings. Alzheimer\'s &amp; Dementia, 21(10), p.e70769. https://doi.org/10.1002/alz.70769\r\n\r\n2.	Kpelle, L., Bockarie, A., Antwi, M.H., Osei, G.N., Donkor, D.M., Brodie?Mends, D., Adu, A.M. and Simpong, D.L., 2026. Population disparities in Alzheimer\'s disease: A systematic review of fluid and neuroimaging biomarkers. Alzheimer\'s &amp; Dementia: Diagnosis, Assessment &amp; Disease Monitoring, 18(1), p.e70263.\r\nhttps://doi.org/10.1002/dad2.70263\r\n\r\n3.	Adu, A.M., Simpong, D.L., Donkor, D.M., Manu, K.S., Antwi, M.H., Kpelle, L., Osei, G.N. and Bockarie, A., 2026. Parasitic Infections and Associated Cognitive Outcome Among School?Aged Children in Africa: A Systematic Review. Brain and Behavior, 16(4), p.e71326. https://doi.org/10.1002/brb3.71326\r\n\r\n4.	Article: Peripheral Oxidative Stress Related Biomarkers in Alzheimer’s Disease: A Systematic Review of Their Implications for Diagnosis and Disease Monitoring\r\nArticle ID: DAD270354\r\nArticle DOI: 10.1002/dad2.70354\r\nInternal Article ID: 100550053', 'This position will help advance my academic career and enrich my knowledge in histopathology and cytology research and practice. Additionally my current academic qualification will help me transfer knowledge gained so far to build student capacity and research skills', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '1. Medical laboratory mentorship and practical demonstrations\r\n2. Academic presentation and Public speaking\r\n3. Learning AI applications in healthcare and education', 'Immediately as possible', 'I wish to state that my expected date of completion of the MPhil is August 2026, and that I am currently analysing my samples and data for my thesis and would be grateful if considered for the position or considered as a senior technical instructor until all my relevant documentations are ready in August.', 'Mr Daniel Nyaaba', 'Lecturer', 'Head of Department of Allied Health, College of Health, Nalerigu', 'College of Health, Nalerigu, North East region. P. O. Box 10', '0209190493', 'ndanielayine@yahoo.com', 'Dr. David Larbi Simpong', 'Lecturer', NULL, 'College of Health and Allied Sciences, University of Cape Coast, Ghana', '+1(628)289-6814', 'dsimpong@ucc.edu.gh', 'Dr. Francis Atoroba Apodola', NULL, NULL, 'College of Health, Department of Allied Health Sciences, Nalerigu', '0248588131', 'apodolafrancis@gmail.com', 'BTU_8DEA9268_cv_6a0dcaa66a47e7.64238969.pdf', 'KPELLE LINUS CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '197.251.240.76', '2026-05-20 14:52:22', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_8DEA9268_photo_6a0dcaa66a4820.15145370.jpeg', 'Off. Passport photo.jpeg'),
(5, 'BTU-1D1E90AB', 1, 'Dr.', 'Boakye', 'Kingsley', 'kingsley.boakye9@gmail.com', '+233541814685', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences\r\nDepartment of Clinical Microbiology and Immunology\r\nP. O.Box 24\r\nNavrongo', 'Accra', 'Wechiau', 'Upper West', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', 'P0030692253', 'GHA-723504455-1', '1994-06-07', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences', 5, '1.	Boakye, K., Kulariba, J., Nenyewode. F. E., Inusah A., Dramani. K. A., Boodba, D. D., Adu Frimpong, M., Agongo, G., Abugri, J., Dassah, S. D. (2025). Prevalence of mecA Gene in Staphylococcus aureus: A Molecular and Antibiogram Analysis from a Referral Hospital in Northern Ghana. Pan African Medical Journal (Under Review).\r\n\r\n2.	Bani, S. B., Quaye, L., Dapare, P. P. M., Adams, Y., Banyeh, M., Gandau, B. B. N., Nkansah, C., Mensah, K., Appiah, S. K., Boakye, K., Rogers, S. J., &amp; Bani, F. (2022). Assessing Haemoglobin Concentration and Red Cell Morphology in Stored Blood Units. International Journal of Research and Reports in Hematology, 5(2), 248-257.\r\n\r\n3.	Boakye, K., Dassah, S. Y., &amp; Abugri, J. (2025). Prevalence of mecA Gene in Staphylococcus aureus: A Molecular and Antibiogram Analysis from a Referral Hospital in Northern Ghana. Poster presentation at West African Centre for Cell Biology of Infectious Pathogens (WACCBIP) Research Conference, University of Ghana, Accra, Ghana, 23-25th July, 2025', 'My teaching, research, and professional experiences align strongly with the requirements of the Lecturer position in the Medical Laboratory Technology Department. My background in Medical Laboratory Science education, combined with hands-on laboratory and research experience, positions me to contribute effectively to competency-based training, applied biomedical research, and student development in clinical laboratory practice.\r\nIn teaching, I have experience delivering both theoretical and practical courses across Medical Laboratory Science, Public Health, Midwifery, and Pharmaceutical Technology programmes. I currently teach Chemical Pathology I and II (including practicals), Biochemistry II, General Pathology, Clinical Microbiology and Infection Prevention and Control, as well as Public Health Laboratory courses. These teaching areas directly align with core components of Medical Laboratory Technology training. My learner-centred approach incorporates lectures, laboratory demonstrations, case-based learning and discussions, enabling students to connect theoretical concepts with clinical and diagnostic applications. My experience as a Graduate Teaching and Research Assistant further strengthened my ability to develop instructional materials and support teaching in Immunology, Serology, Microbiology, and Pharmaceutical Microbiology, all of which are central to laboratory science education.\r\nMy research experience is also highly relevant to this post, as it focuses on molecular microbiology, virology, antimicrobial resistance, immunology, and infectious disease epidemiology. My Master’s research on ?-lactam resistance in Staphylococcus aureus combined phenotypic and molecular diagnostic approaches, reflecting the investigative and analytical skills required in medical laboratory practice. I have also contributed to research on schistosomiasis, malaria, and institutional research integrity, gaining experience in sample processing, microscopy, field epidemiology, and laboratory-based diagnostics. My proposed PhD research on integrated immunological and nutritional determinants of measles vaccine breakthrough infections further demonstrates my commitment to advancing diagnostic immunology and public health laboratory science, which are critical to modern medical laboratory technology.\r\nProfessionally, I have developed strong competencies in laboratory diagnostics, supervision, and research collaboration through various academic and international research projects. I have supported trainees in laboratory practical, supervised sample processing, and contributed to quality laboratory procedures in microbiology, parasitology, and molecular studies. These experiences have strengthened my ability to work in structured laboratory environments, uphold quality standards, and mentor students effectively. Collectively, my teaching, research, and professional experiences align well with the goals of the Medical Laboratory Technology Department and I am well-prepared to contribute to curriculum delivery, practical training, and research advancement in Medical Laboratory Science.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'I enjoy watching football and movies', '1 month', NULL, 'Prof. Dr. (Med) Juventus Benogle Ziem', 'Lecturer and Medical Officer', 'Dean, School of Medical Sciences, UTAS', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences,\r\nP. O. Box 24\r\nNavrongo – Upper East Region', '+233244753335', 'jbziem@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Prof. James Abugri', 'Lecturer', 'Dean, School of Chemical and Biochemical Sciences, UTAS', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences,\r\nP. O. Box 24\r\nNavrongo – Upper East Region.', '+233204088294/+22324', 'jabugri@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Dr. Sylvester Dassah', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer, School of Chemical and Biochemical Sciences', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences,\r\nP. O. Box 24\r\nNavrongo – Upper East Region.', '+233243005950', 'sddassah@utas.edu.gh', 'BTU_1D1E90AB_cv_6a0dddcfe42d99.46106357.pdf', 'CV_Kingsley_Boakye .pdf', 'pending', NULL, '102.207.4.5', '2026-05-20 16:14:07', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_1D1E90AB_photo_6a0dddcfe42de0.67938959.jpg', 'kingsley-9592-1.jpg'),
(6, 'BTU-961604F7', 1, 'Mr.', 'Johnson', 'Sam', 'samjohnsonjunior1998@gmail.com', '+233549052590', 'C/O Johnson Sam\r\nEssikado Hospital,\r\nP. O Box 187,\r\nSekondi.', 'Sekondi', 'Assin Amoakrom', 'Western', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-723510883-5', '1998-06-06', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Cape Coast', 5, '1.	Sam, J., &amp; Dickson, K. S. (2026). Trend and pattern of antenatal care utilisation and neonatal mortality in Ghana: analyses 2003–2022 demographic and health survey. BMJ Open, 16(5), e103892.\r\n\r\n2.	 Sam, J., &amp; Kasu, C. (2025). Determinants of caesarean section use in Ghana: A trend analysis of 2003–2022 DHS data. PLOS Global Public Health, 5(11), e0005473. \r\n\r\n3.	Aggrey-Bluwey, L., Johnson, S., &amp; Obu, R. N. (2022). Condom use among students in a Ghanaian public university: A quantitative survey. International STD Research &amp; Reviews, 11(1), 25–33. https://doi.org/10.9734/isrr/2022/v11i130141', 'I have about five years of experience working at the hospital and have rotated across different departments and units.\r\nMy teaching philosophy is grounded in the belief that higher education should empower students with critical thinking skills, practical competencies, and the confidence to apply knowledge to solve real-world public health challenges. I strive to create an inclusive, engaging, and student-centered learning environment that encourages active participation, intellectual curiosity, and lifelong learning.\r\nAs a public health researcher and doctoral student in Epidemiology and Biostatistics, I recognize the importance of integrating theory with practice. I therefore approach teaching by linking classroom concepts to contemporary public health issues, real-life case studies, and practical data analysis applications (computer labs) using survey data. I believe students learn best when they are encouraged to engage actively with content rather than passively receiving information.\r\nIn my teaching, I prioritize clarity, interaction, and application. I employ a variety of teaching strategies including lectures, discussions, case-based learning, group activities, demonstrations, and practical computer-based sessions using statistical software such as SPSS, Stata, and R. These approaches help students build analytical skills and improve their ability to interpret and apply evidence in professional settings.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'I like playing football and tv games', 'Two weeks to one month', NULL, 'Dr. Kwamena Sekyi Dickson', 'Lecturer', 'Senior lecturer', 'Department of Population and Health\r\nUniversity of Cape Coast', '+ 233242517664', 'kwamena.dickson@ucc.edu.gh', 'Dr. Listowel Ferka', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Department of Population and Health\r\nUniversity of Cape Coast', '+233544066730', 'listowel.ferka@ucc.edu.gh', 'Mr. Joseph Eghan', 'Accountant', 'Senior Accountant (Essikado Hospital)', 'Essikado Hospital,\r\nP O Box 187, \r\nSekondi.', '+233243902757', 'joseph.eghan@ghs.gov.gh', 'BTU_961604F7_cv_6a0df0610046a1.57429322.pdf', 'CV_JOHNSON_SAM.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '156.38.114.33', '2026-05-20 17:33:21', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_961604F7_photo_6a0df0610046e0.22303962.jpeg', 'sjsj passport.jpeg'),
(7, 'BTU-0F709A33', 10, 'Dr.', 'YAHAYA', 'ABDUL-GANIWU', 'yahayaabdulganiwu66@gmail.com', '+233599195244', 'ZUARUNGU SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL BOX 133 BOLGATAGA EAST  UPPER EAST REGION', 'EJURA-HIAWOANWU', 'EJURA-SEKYEREDUMASI', 'Ashanti', 'GHANAIAN', 'ISLAM', 'married', 'MOHAMMED RUBAMA', 'EJURA-HIAWOANWU HA/68', 'YAHAYA UMMY SAFIA- 08/10/2024', 'P0058468676', 'GHA-715539394-6', '1993-09-27', 'male', 'PhD', 'C.K. TEDAM UNIVERSITY OF TECHNOLOGY AND APPLIED SCIENCES', 7, '1.	Abdul-Ganiwu Yahaya, Agbedemnab, P.A., Bankas, E.K. (2024). A Modified RSA Cryptosystem for Cloud Security Using Residue Number System. International Journal of Computer and Organization Trends, Vol. 14(1).\r\n2.	Agbedemnab, P. A., Abdul-Ganiwu Yahaya, Bankas, E. K., &amp; Nantomah, K. K. (2026). Image Security on Cloud Using Enhanced RSA Cryptosystem and Residue Number System.\r\nInternational Journal of innovation Science, Engineering &amp; Technology, Vol. 13(2).', 'My academic background, teaching experience, and research activities strongly align with the position of Lecturer in Computing and Information Technology. I possess interdisciplinary training in Computer Science, Computational Mathematics, and Mathematics Education which has equipped me with both theoretical knowledge and practical teaching teaching skills relevant to higher education in computing and information technology.\r\nCurrently, I hold a PhD in Computer Science, where my research focuses on cloud security, cryptography, and residue number system. My Doctorate thesis, Efficient Cryptographic Scheme for Cloud Security Using Asymmetric Techniques and Residue Number System demonstrates my ability to conduct advanced research in contemporary areas of computing and cybersecurity.\r\nI also possess practical skills in Python programming, MATLAB, Latex and academic research methods which are highly relevant for teaching undergraduate computing courses and supervising student project. In terms of teaching experience, I have over seven years of experience in education at both secondary and tertiary levels. As a Teaching Assistant at the University for Development Studies, I assisted in teaching courses such as Logical  and Critical Thinking, Research Methods and Sociology of Education. This role enhanced my competence in tutorial delivery, student assessment, grading, academic administration, and student supports services. These experiences have prepared me to effectively deliver lectures, facilitate practical sessions, and contribute to curriculum implementation in a university environment.\r\nFurthermore, my current role as a Mathematics Tutor at Zuarungu Senior High School has strengthen my communication, mentoring and instructional skills. I have extensive experience in lesson planning, assessment design, examination setting, and student guidance. My background in mathematics education complements computing and information technology because of the strong analytical and problem-solving foundation required in computing disciplines.\r\nBeyond teaching and research, I have demonstrated leadership and administrative capabilities through role such as Assistant House Master, Form Master Deputy Secretary of Election Committee, Treasurer of the Graduate Student Association at CKT-UTAS. These responsibilities have developed my teamwork, organizational, and interpersonal skills, which are essential for academic collaboration and institutional service. \r\nAdditionally I have participated in several workshops and seminars related to research methodology, academic writing, proposal development, mathematics education, and professional development. These engagements have enhanced my pedagogical approaches and research capacity, enabling me to contribute effectively to teaching, research and community service within the university system.\r\nMy academic qualifications, research expertise, and teaching experience make me a well suited for the position of lecturer in Computing and Information Technology. I am confident in my ability to contribute meaningfully to teaching, research, student mentorship, and the advancement of the department', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'COACHING, SPORTING, EDITTING AND RESEARCH', 'IMMEDIATELY', NULL, 'PROF. MOHAMMED MUNIRU IDDRISU', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'PRINCIPAL', 'UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES BOX TL1350 NYANKPALA CAMPUS', '233243642642', 'mmuniru@uds.edu.gh', 'PROF. CHRISTOPHER SAA BORNAA', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'DEAN', 'C.K TEDAM UNIVERSITY OF TECHNOLOGY AND APPLIED SCIENCES BOX 24  NAVRONGO-GHANA', '+23324 470 1216', 'cbornaa@cktutas.edu.gh', 'PROF. PETER A. AGBEDEMNAB', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'PRINCIPAL', 'TUMU COLLEGE OF EDUCATION BOX 19 TUMU UPPER WEST REGION-GHANA', 'pagbedemnab@cktutas.', '233208529720', 'BTU_0F709A33_cv_6a0df1b2529264.86594548.pdf', 'Abdul-Ganiwu Yahaya Academic CV Lecturer.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.237.119', '2026-05-20 17:38:58', '2026-05-20 17:38:58', 'BTU_0F709A33_photo_6a0df1b25292d8.89724360.jpeg', 'passport .jpeg'),
(8, 'BTU-0F0CE7C8', 1, 'Dr.', 'DAGUNGONG', 'CLEMENT BINWATIN', 'DAGUNGONGC@GMAIL.COM', '+233546367535', 'SCHOOL OF ALLIED HEALTH SCIENCES, UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES, P. O. BOX TLC 1883, TAMALE.', 'KAMBAGU-BUNKPURUGU', 'KAMBAGU-BUNKPURUGU', 'North East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIANITY', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'NONE', 'P0027246558', 'GHA-714949947-6', '1995-08-12', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'KWAME NKRUMAH UNIVERSITY OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY', 5, 'PUBLICATIONS\r\nDissertations\r\n•	Dagungong, C. B. (2026). Immunophenotyping T-Cell sub-population, their cytokine expression and its association with chronic kidney disease: A case control study at Tamale Teaching Hospital (Manuscript under review)\r\n•	Dagungong C.B. (2021) Relationship between maternal sex hormones (testosterone, estradiol) and 2d:4d of offspring (Undergraduate Thesis)\r\n\r\nJournal Articles\r\n•	Banyeh M., Buadee R., Dagungong C.B, et al, 2025. Comparative Evaluation of Glycaemic and Non-Glycaemic Factors as Determinants of Retinopathy Status in an Adult Population: A Case-Control Study. (2025), (https://doi.org/10.1002/hsr2.71554)\r\n•	Amidu N, Banyeh M., Dagungong C.B, et al, 2024. Investigating hemolysis, elevated liver enzymes and lowplatelet count in preeclampsia: A case?control study in Ghana. (2024).(http://dx.doi.org/10.1002/hsr2.2277)\r\n•	Banyeh, M., Woli, M. K., Mayeem, B. N., Kolekang, A. S., Nukpezah, R. N., Habib, N., . . Dagungong, C. B. (2024). Maternal hepatitis B status and Sex at birth: A cross-sectional study in a Ghanaian population Sex at birth and HBV status. Heliyon.\r\n•	Banyeh M., Mayeem B. N., Woli M. K., Kolekang A. S., Dagungong C., B., Bure D., Wemegah R. K., Azindow M. I., Yakubu S., Seidu M., Baba M. M., Essoun E., Owireduwaa N. Exploring Hematological and Biochemical Disparities in Same-Sex and Opposite-Sex Females: A Cross- Sectional Twin Study in a Ghanaian Population. Twin Research and Human Genetics (https://doi.org/10.1017/thg.2024.7)\r\n•	Banyeh, M., Shittu, S. O., Ziblim, S.-D., Dapare, P. P. M., Nyewie, M., &amp; Dagungong, C. B. (2023). Can maternal postpartum testosterone and estradiol retrospectively predict the offspring\'s sex at birth? A cross-sectional study in Ghana. Physiological Reports, 11, e15757. (https://doi.org/10.14814/phy2.15757)\r\n•	Nkansah, C., Agyemang, L. D., Osei-Boakye, F., Appiah, S. K., Mensah, K., Abbam, G.,... Dagungong, C. B., &amp; Chukwurah, F. E. (2022). Circulating Naturally-Occurring Anticoagulants before Treatment and after Recovery from SARS-CoV-2 Infection inGhana. SciMedicine Journal, 4(4), 142-154 (https://doi.org/10.28991/SciMedJ-2022-04-04-01)\r\n•	Banyeh, M., Zogli, K. E., Osumanu, H. A., Obeng, L., Acheampong, T. K., Dagungong, C.B, Elizabeth, B. Amidu, N. (2022). Does sex interact with the 2D: 4D ratio or adult circulating hormones on the estimated glomerular filtration rate? A cross?sectional study in Ghana.\r\nPhysiological Reports, 10(22), e15516.', 'As both Guest Assistant Lecturer and an ASCPi-certified Biomedical Laboratory Scientist, my career has always been about connecting theory with actual real-world practice which I believe fits with Bolgatanga Technical University’s practical. On the professional side, my years of hands-on diagnostic experience in major clinical laboratories allow me to show students exactly how what they learn in class applies on a laboratory bench. This clinical background naturally feeds into my teaching; over the past four years in higher education, I’ve focused on breaking down complex subjects like immunology and immunodiagnostics in clear and ready skills. My research skills keep me at the cutting edge of our field, allowing me to help drive BTU’s goals for applied research and the development of new postgraduate programs. Ultimately, I bring a balance of active laboratory experience, a genuine passion for classroom teaching, and a commitment to research that will help mentor the next generation of BTU science students.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, listening to news and playing football.', '1 week', 'N/A', 'Dr. Moses Banyeh', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Head of Department for Immunology and immunodiagnostics', 'SAHS, UDS, P. O. BOX TLC 1883, Tamale.', '+233542615649', 'mbanyeh@uds.edu.gh', 'Prof. Samuel B. Kombian', 'Senior Lecturer', 'HoD: Department of Pharmacology and Toxicology', 'P. O. Box TL 1350', '+233209740561', 'skombian@uds.edu.gh', 'Prof. Abdul Nashirudeen Mumuni', 'Senior Lecturer', 'HoD : Department of Medical Imaging', 'SAHS, UDS, P. O. BOX TLC 1883.', '+233(0)206212210', 'mnashiru@uds.edu.gh', 'BTU_0F0CE7C8_cv_6a0e1d91e4e955.12159560.pdf', 'Clement Binwatin Dagungong_Resume (CV) (3).pdf', 'pending', NULL, '179.64.71.151', '2026-05-20 20:46:09', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_0F0CE7C8_photo_6a0e1d91e4e9a3.61626268.jpg', 'Passport DC.jpg'),
