(14, 'BTU-6107FB9E', 2, 'Dr.', 'ATIAH', 'KUDUGU', 'kudugua@gmail.com', '+233244303218', 'GHANA EDUCATION SERVICE, P O BOX 8, BAWKU WEST DISTRICT,ZEBILLA', 'ZEBILLA', 'ZEBILLA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'ISLAM', 'married', 'AHMED RABI', 'UW-0003-3831', 'ATIAH ABDUL-GANIW AYAWINI-7TH JULY, 2009\r\nATIAH MAAHIR APIIGA-18TH FEBRUARY, 2014\r\nATIAH RUHUL-HAQ WINTUMAH-10TH JUNE, 2017', 'P0006554288', 'GHA-715299209-6', '1978-04-21', 'male', 'PhD', 'C. K. TEDAM UNIVERSITY OF TECHNOLOGY AND APPLIED SCIENCES', 7, '1. Atiah, K., Nasiru, S., and Katara, S. (2022). The Proportional Hazard Generalized Power Weibull Distribution: Properties, Applications, and Regression Model. Asian Journal of Probability and Statistics, 20(4), 120-145. \r\n2. Atiah, K., Nasiru, S., and Katara, S. (2026). Chen Proportional Hazard Model with Applications to Lifetime Data. Journal of Statistics and Management Systems, 29(3), 231-254.', 'My academic background in Applied Statistics, Biometry, and Mathematics Education is highly relevant to the lecturer position, as it equips me with strong teaching, research, and analytical skills. My research interests in statistical modeling, data analysis, and quantitative methods align with tertiary education and research needs. In addition, my professional experience in the Ghana Education Service has enhanced my communication, leadership, and instructional abilities.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Solving the mathematical problem at my leisure time and listening to music.', '1 month', NULL, 'PROF. SULEMAN NASIRU', 'TEACHING', 'PROFESSOR', 'UNIVERSITY OF TECHNOLOGY AND APPLIED SCIENCES, DEPARTMENT OF STATISTICS, P O BOX 24, NAVRONGO, UPPER EAST REGION', '0246609024/020482945', 'sulemanstat@gmail.com', 'MR. TIMOTHY NAASAL YUORNUO', NULL, 'DISTRICT DIRECTOR OF EDUCATION', 'GHANA EDUCATION SERVICE, P O BOX 8, BAWKU WEST DISTRICT, ZEBILLA', '0243132690', 'timothyyuornuo@gmail.com', 'PROF. KATARA SALIFU', 'TEACHING', 'ASSOCIATE PROFESSOR', 'UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES, DEPARTMENT OF STATISTICS, SCHOOL OF ENGINEERING, TAMALE', '0246640722/020578272', 'skatara@uds.edu.gh', 'BTU_6107FB9E_cv_6a0eedb5c0d7e7.42379496.pdf', 'Dr_Atiah_Kudugu_CV.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.163.246', '2026-05-21 11:34:13', '2026-06-12 23:23:07', 'BTU_6107FB9E_photo_6a0eedb5c0d838.63994945.jpg', 'IMG-20260506-WA0056.jpg'),
(15, 'BTU-56712A39', 6, 'Mr.', 'YAKUBU', 'MUSAH SAAJJI', 'saajji6060@gmail.com', '+233241756971', 'EREMON SHTS box 77', 'BOLI', 'WA', 'Upper West', 'GHANAIAN', 'ISLAM', 'married', 'OSMAN MAMA HAWAA', 'EREMON SHTS box 77', 'MUSAH SAAJJI KHALISA 08/05/2019\r\nMUSAH SAAJJI AL-MAHIR 12/06/2021\r\nMUSAH SAAJJI KIYAAN 21/08/2023\r\nMUSAH SAAJJI YAKUBU 22/12/2025', 'P0011760494', 'GHA-716148509-7', '1990-04-27', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'AKENTEN APPIAH-MENKA UNIVERSITY OF SKILL TRAINING AND ENTREPRENEURIAL DEVELOPMENT', 7, 'Sustainable utilization of lannea acida wood: evaluation its physico-mechanical and natural durability properties in Ghana (under review)', 'My educational background in wood technology and wood science combined with my experience in teaching technical subjects (woodwork and technical drawinng).', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading and teaching', '2 weeks', NULL, 'Dr. I.I Shaibu', 'teacher', 'Headmaster Eremon SHTS', 'EREMON SHTS box 77', '0244970628', NULL, 'Dr. Kwaku Antwi', 'Lecturer', 'HOD for Civil Engineering', 'USTED BOX 77 KUMASI', '0208150964', 'Kantwi@aamusted.edu.gh', 'Mr. Salia Adams', 'Teacher', 'SISO', 'GES Wa East Box 1 Funsi', '0247476920', 'bundoiadams@gmail.com', 'BTU_56712A39_cv_6a0f054aa587b8.90834058.pdf', 'CV Musah Saajji Yakubu.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.234.22', '2026-05-21 13:14:50', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_56712A39_photo_6a0f054aa58804.29353463.jpg', 'IMG-20260521-WA0010.jpg'),
(16, 'BTU-5C74F36C', 3, 'Mr.', 'PETER', 'AKANFAH ASODEWINE', 'peterakanfah@gmail.com', '+233247811385', 'KONGO SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL\r\nBOX 39\r\nKONGO-BOLGATANGA', 'NATUGNIA', 'NATUGNIA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIANITY', 'married', 'Peter Akanfah Asodewine', 'P.O. BOX TL 1882', 'ABLE AKANFAH 2010-09-28\r\nPEACE AKANFAH 2014-01-17\r\n FAITH AWINBONO AKANFAH  2018-12-15', 'P0014447436', 'GHA-715860859-1', '1984-04-11', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'BOLGATANGA TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY', 5, '1. Asodewine, P. A., Lamptey, S., Addai, I. K., &amp; Tetteh, A. (2026). Assessing current Sorghum agronomic practices and production constraints in the Guinea and Sudan savannahs of Ghana. Agricultural Sciences, 17, 91–109. https://doi.org/10.4236/as.2026.172007\r\n2. Asodewine, P. A., Lamptey, S., &amp; Dzomeku, I. K. (2021). Pearl millet–cowpea intercrop effect on Striga hermonthica and grain yield in the Sudan savannah zone of Ghana. Indian Journal of Weed Science, 53(2), 146–152.\r\n3. Sam, E. K., Kugbe, X. J., Adu-Gyamfi, R., Odoom, A. D., Laryea, O. K., &amp; Asodewine, P. (2019). Comparative assessment of phosphorus fertilization and rhizobia inoculation on soybean production in the Guinea savannah zone of Ghana. Journal of Agriculture and Crops, 5(6), 78–86.', 'My teaching, research, and professional experiences align closely with the demands of an agricultural engineering lecturer role. In my teaching, I have focused on making complex engineering concepts accessible and relevant to students, often linking theory to real-world agricultural challenges like soil management, irrigation systems, and mechanization. This hands-on approach helps students see the practical impact of what they are learning.\r\nMy research centers on areas directly relevant to agricultural engineering particularly soil analysis, crop growth optimization, and sustainable farming technologies. I have designed and conducted field experiments, analyzed soil chemical and physical properties, and investigated how different management practices affect Sorghum yield and soil health. These projects have strengthened my ability to guide students through the research process, from experimental design to data interpretation and publication.\r\nProfessionally, I have worked on agronomic field trials and soil amendment strategies that bridge the gap between academic research and on-farm application. This practical experience allows me to bring real industry insights into the classroom and mentor students on how agricultural engineering solutions can improve productivity and sustainability.\r\nTogether, these experiences have prepared me to teach effectively, supervise meaningful research, and contribute to the department’s mission of advancing agricultural engineering education and practice.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'MY HOBBIES INCLUDE READING RESEARCH ARTICLES, SCIENTIFIC WRITINGS, AND CONDUCTING RESEARCHES', 'I CAN ASSUME DUTY IMMEDIATELY UPON NOTIFICATION OR BASED ON THE DATE GIVEN IN THE ENGAGEMENT LETTER', NULL, 'Professor Shirley Lamptey', 'LECTURER', 'HEAD OF CROP SCIENCE DEPARTMENT', 'University for Development Studies, Nyankpala Campus, P.O. Box TL 1882, Tamale, Ghana', '0244649270', 'slamptey@uds.edu.gh', 'Mr. James Adiisi', 'TEACHER', 'Assistant Headmaster (Administration)', 'KONGO SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL\r\nBOX 39\r\nKONGO-BOLGATANGA', '0242932168', 'jadiisi73@gmail.com', 'Professor Isaac K. Addai', 'LECTURER', 'SENIOR LECTURER/Professor of Plant Breeding', 'University for Development Studies, Nyankpala Campus, P.O. Box TL 1882, Tamale, Ghana', '0243621302', 'ikaddai2014@gmail.com', 'BTU_5C74F36C_cv_6a0f14283074e8.40788773.pdf', 'APPLICATION LETTER.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.10.214', '2026-05-21 14:18:16', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_5C74F36C_photo_6a0f1428307522.55438683.jpg', 'PASSPORT CARD.jpg'),
