(21, 'BTU-770ECBE0', 2, 'Dr.', 'EMMANUEL', 'BRUCE', 'kinbuki100@outlook.com', '+233536477775', 'CHAMPION MAN LANE - TANOSO, KUMASI, GHANA\r\nAH-1309-1832', 'EGYAA VIA ANOMABO', 'ANOMABO', 'Central', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIANITY', 'married', 'LAURETTA KUSIWAA MENSAH', 'CHAMPION MAN LANE - TANOSO, KUMASI, GHANA', 'NANA AMA BRUCE 02/06/2012', NULL, 'GH-729594864-8', '1984-08-08', 'male', 'PhD', 'University of Electronic Science and Technology of China, Chengdu', 7, 'Bruce, E., Shurong, Z., Amoah, J., Egala, S. B., Sarfo, P. A., Baidoo, B. E., ... &amp; \r\nYongxing, Y. (2025). Examining the impact of social media usage on start-ups \r\nperformance: Mediating Role of Brand Image. PLoS One, 20(5), e0320133.  \r\n2. Bruce, E., Shurong, Z., Amoah, J., Egala, S. B., &amp; Sobre Frimpong, F. K. (2024). \r\nReassessing the impact of social media on healthcare delivery: insights from a less \r\ndigitalized economy. Cogent Public Health, 11(1), 2301127. \r\n3. Egala, S. B., Amoah, J., Bashiru Jibril, A., Opoku, R., &amp; Bruce, E. (2024). Digital \r\ntransformation in an emerging economy: exploring organizational drivers. Cogent Social \r\nSciences, 10(1), 2302217. \r\n4. Keelson, S. A., Bruce, E., Egala, S. B., Amoah, J., &amp; Bashiru Jibril, A. (2024). Driving \r\nforces of social media and its impact on tourists’ destination decisions: a uses and \r\ngratification theory. Cogent Social Sciences, 10(1), 2318878. \r\n5. Adu Sarfo, P., Zhang, J., Nyantakyi, G., Lassey, F. A., Bruce, E., &amp; Amankwah, O. \r\n(2024). Influence of Green Human Resource Management on firm’s environmental \r\nperformance: Green Employee Empowerment as a mediating factor. Plos one, 19(4), \r\ne0293957. \r\n6. Jibril, A. B., Egala, S. B., Keelson, S. A., Amoah, J., &amp; Bruce, E. (2024). Revisiting the \r\nFacilitators of Social Media Adoption within the Tourism Sector: An Empirical \r\nInvestigation \r\nin \r\nE2772316X300254.  \r\nan \r\nEmerging Economy. Current Social Sciences, 2(1), \r\n7. Bruce, E., Shurong, Z., Ying, D., Yaqi, M., Amoah, J., &amp; Egala, S. B. (2023). The Effect \r\nof Digital Marketing Adoption on SMEs Sustainable Growth: Empirical Evidence from \r\nGhana. Sustainability, 15(6), 4760. \r\n8. Bruce, E., Keelson, S., Amoah, J., &amp; Bankuoru Egala, S. (2023). Social media integration: \r\nAn opportunity for SMEs sustainability. Cogent Business &amp; Management, 10(1), \r\n2173859. \r\n9. Amoah, J., Bruce, E., Shurong, Z., Bankuoru Egala, S., &amp; Kwarteng, K. (2023). Social \r\nMedia Adoption in SMEs Sustainability: evidence from an emerging economy. Cogent \r\nBusiness &amp; Management, 10(1), 2183573. \r\n10. Bruce, E., &amp; Lauretta, K. M. (2023). Investigating Social Media Impact on Construction \r\nFirms’ Performance in Developing Economies. Sciences, 10(1), 24-40. \r\n11. Bruce, E., Shurong, Z., Egala, S. B., Amoah, J., Ying, D., Rui, H., &amp; Lyu, T. (2022). \r\nSocial Media Usage and SME Firms’ Sustainability: An Introspective Analysis from \r\nGhana. Sustainability, 14(15), 9433. https://doi.org/10.3390/su14159433 \r\n12. Bruce E., Zhao, S., Egala, S. B., Mammet, Y., &amp; Godson, K. (2022). Social Media and Its \r\nConnection to Business Performance—A Literature Review. American Journal of \r\nIndustrial \r\nand \r\nBusiness \r\nhttps://doi.org/10.4236/ajibm.2022.125045 \r\nManagement, \r\n12(05), \r\n877–893. \r\n13. Bruce E., Shurong Z., Akakpo A., &amp; Oppong J. (2022). Impact of social media on start\r\nup survival: Qualitative evidence from Ghana. Journal of Management, Economics, and \r\nIndustrial Organization, 6(2), 48-69. http://doi.org/10.31039/jomeino.2022.6.2.4  \r\n14. Bruce, E., &amp; Priscilla, O. A. (2022). A Review of Corporate Social Responsibility and Its \r\nRelationship with Customer Satisfaction and Corporate Image. Open Journal of Business \r\nand Management, 10(02), 715–728. https://doi.org/10.4236/ojbm.2022.102040', 'As a passionate educator and researcher in the field of Business Administration, I am excited to apply for a lecturer position in the Department of Liberal Studies, School at the School of Applied Science and Arts, Bolgatanga Technical University. My academic background in management and extensive experience in teaching and research have equipped me with a unique blend of technical and pedagogical skills that I believe would be valuable in this role. With a PhD in Business Administration specializing in Strategic Management, and a Masters in Science in Business Administration, I focus on exploring how data and business intelligence can drive decision-making in social business and organizational environments. My scholarly contributions include publications in prestigious journals.  \r\nResearch Interests \r\nMy research interest is centred around the applications of social media in enhancing organizational decision-making and performance. Specifically, I am interested in exploring the impact of social media analytics and business intelligence on strategic decision-making, as well as the role of digital marketing in fostering a data-driven culture within organizations. I have a strong track record of publishing research in top-tier academic journals such as Plos One, Cogent Business and Management, Sustainability and other notable outlets. I am committed to continuing this work as a faculty member of the Bolgatanga Technical University.\r\nTeaching Interests \r\nAs a Lecturer in Strategy and Innovation, I am committed to creating engaging and interactive learning experiences for my students. I believe effective teaching involves conveying technical knowledge and fostering critical thinking, problem-solving, and collaboration skills. My teaching philosophy centres on creating a supportive and inclusive learning environment that encourages students to take ownership of their learning and apply theoretical concepts to real-world problems. \r\nTeaching Experience \r\nThroughout my academic career, I have taught a range of management courses, including innovation and entrepreneurship, Fundamentals of Marketing, theories in management, Research Methods, Qualitative Research Methods, Evidence-Based Practice, Digital Marketing and Strategic Marketing Management. I have consistently received positive feedback from students and colleagues alike, and I am confident in my ability to adapt my teaching style to meet the needs of diverse student populations. \r\nResearch and Teaching Goals \r\nIn the next five years, I aim to continue publishing research in top-tier conferences and journals, focusing on exploring the applications of digital marketing tools in enhancing organizational decision-making and performance. I aim to design engaging new courses that integrate emerging trends in management practices into the curriculum. I hope to establish collaborations with industry partners to provide students with hands-on experience in applying management concepts to real-world problems. It is my goal in the coming years to increase the number of publications in reputable journals such as Journal of Business Research, Journal of Retailing and Consumer Service, and Industrial Marketing Management, among others. \r\nMy unique blend of technical and pedagogical skills and my passion for teaching and research make me an ideal candidate for the faculty position in Bolgatanga Technical University. I am excited about the opportunity to join the M Bolgatanga Technical University community and contribute to the growth and development of Bolgatanga Technical University.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING AND PLAYING SOCCER', '2 weeks', NULL, 'Prof. Zhao Shurong', 'PROFERSSOR/LECTURER', 'Professor/Director   School of Public Administration  Center for West African Studies of UESTC, Chen', 'No.2006, Xiyuan Ave, West Hi-Tech Zone, 611731, Chengdu-Sichuan, China', '+8618381096264', 'shurz2015@ustc.edu.cn ;  shurz2015@163.com', 'DR. JOHN AMOAH', 'LECTURER/COORDINATOR', 'COORDINATOR, CENTER FOR GRADAUTE STUDIES AND RESEARCH, KAAF UNIVERSITY', 'BOX WU, 177, \r\nKASOA-CENTRAL REGION', '0548079960', 'John.amoah@kaafuni.edu.gh', 'DR. SULEMANA EGALA', 'ASSOCIATE PROFESSOR', 'Head, Department of Computer Science  SD Dombo University of Business and Integrated Development Stu', 'Head, Department of Computer Science \r\nSD Dombo University of Business and Integrated Development Studies, Wa', '0244469246', 'sbegala@ubids.edu.gh', 'BTU_770ECBE0_cv_6a0f40148b8737.84874824.pdf', 'DR. EMMANUEL BRUCE- RESUME.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.186.31', '2026-05-21 17:25:40', '2026-05-21 17:25:40', 'BTU_770ECBE0_photo_6a0f40148b8786.30698407.jpg', '3617c500a8119a4b8ef8b5e8cbfb9594.jpg'),
(22, 'BTU-47968C94', 10, 'Mr.', 'AKOLGO', 'ERIC AYINTAREBA', 'eayintareba@gmail.com', '+233545554506', 'DEPARTMENT OF COMPUTER SCIENCE\r\nREGENTROPFEN UNIVERSITY COLLEGE, \r\nPMB, NAMOO', 'ZUARUNGU', 'ZUARUNGU', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'P5001462754', 'GHA-716057578-8', '1992-02-25', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF ENERGY AND NATURAL RESOURCES, UENR', 7, '•	Korda, D. R., Owusu-Boateng, O., Akolgo, E. A., Seidu, N., &amp; Barnes, K. N. (2026). Evaluating the Effectiveness of SIM Card Re-Registration as a Cybersecurity Intervention: Evidence from Ghana. International Journal of Computer Applications, 975, 8887.\r\n•	Ayintareba, A. E., Korda, D. R., &amp; Owusu-Boateng, O. (2026). Performance Metrics in Machine Learning: A Comprehensive Narrative Review. Journal of Advances in Mathematics and Computer Science, 41(5), 183-199.\r\n•	Ayintareba, A. E., Korda, D. R., &amp; Owusu-Boateng, O. (2025). The Application of Transfer Learning in Medical Image Classification: A Review of Literature. Asian Journal of Research in Computer Science, 18(7), 1-11.\r\n•	Korda, D. R., Naawe, N., Akolgo, E. A., &amp; Owusu-Boateng, O. (2025). Combating Illegal Small-Scale Mining (Galamsey) In Ghana with Artificial Intelligence: A Comprehensive Approach. AJSE, 19(3).\r\n•	Agyir, M. A., Akolgo, E. A., Korda, D. R., Adekoya, A. F., &amp; Owusu-Boateng, O. (2025). Diagnosing Diseases in the Leaves of Food Crop Plants Using Residual Network–Powered by Microsoft Azure Custom Vision Service. Journal of Advances in Mathematics and Computer Science, 40(5), 135-157.\r\n•	Akolgo, E., Korda, D. R., &amp; Owusu Boateng, O. (2025). A comprehensive review of six load balancing algorithms in cloud computing. Direct Research Journal of Engineering and Information Technology, 13, 43–50. https://doi.org/10.26765/DRJEIT21061153\r\n•	Akolgo, E. A., Korda, D. R., &amp; Dapaah, E. O. (2024). Artificial Intelligence in Healthcare: A Fusion of Technologies. Journal of Computer and Communications, 12(12), 116-133.\r\n•	Akolgo, E.A, Adekoya, A.F., Korda, D. R., &amp; Dapaah, E.O. (2024). Detection of Malicious Websites using a three model Ensemble Classifiers. Academy Journal of Science and Engineering, 18(1), 1–21.\r\n•	Korda, D. R., Dapaah, E.O., &amp; Akolgo, E.A. (2024). THE ROLE OF AI CHATBOTS IN EDUCATION: A REVIEW. Academy Journal of Science and Engineering, 18(1), 79–87.\r\n•	Korda, D. R., Akolgo, E. A., Dapaah, E. O., &amp; Hodowu, D. K. M. Securing Data in Clouds using the SDC Algorithm: Current Trends and Research Directions. International Journal of Computer Applications, 975, 8887.\r\n•	Seth Gyamerah, Godfred Tour Soori, Dennis Redeemer Korda, John Kwame Tawiah, Eric Ayintareba Akolgo, et al. (2023). Comparative Analysis of Feature Extraction of High Dimensional Data Reduction Using Machine Learning Techniques. American Journal of Electrical and Computer Engineering, 7(2), 27-39. https://doi.org/10.11648/j.ajece.20230702.12\r\n•	Azure, I., Wiredu, J. K., Musah, A., &amp; Akolgo, E. A. (2023). AI-Enhanced Performance Evaluation of Python, MATLAB, and Scilab for Solving Nonlinear Systems of Equations: A Comparative Study Using the Broyden Method. American Journal of Computational Mathematics, 13(4), 644-677', 'CYBERSECURITY MEASURES ARE NECESSARY TO PROTECT CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION FROM BREACHING THE CIA TRIAD.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'WRITING, TESTING, &amp; EXPLORING COMPUTER PROGRAMS, LISTENING TO MUSIC, PLAYING VOLLEYBALL, ETC.', 'AS SOON AS POSSIBLE', NULL, 'DR. MOSES AGEBURE', 'SNR. LECTUERER, UTAS-NAVRONGO', 'HoD COMPUTER SCIENCE DEPARTMENT, UTAS-NAVRONGO', 'Computer Science Department\r\nUniversity of Technology and Applied Sciences\r\nBox 24\r\nNavrongo, Upper East Region', '0244696764', 'magebure@cktutas.edu.gh', 'DR. JAMES KONJAANG KOK', 'LECTURER, BTU-SUMBRUNGO', 'HoD COMPUTING AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY DEPARTMENT, BTU-SUMBRUNGO', 'Bolgatanga Technical University \r\nPost Office Box 767 \r\nSumburungu, Bolgatanga Ghana, West Africa', '0243743851', 'jkok@bolgatu.edu.gh', 'PROF. BENJAMIN ASUBAN WEYORI', 'SNR. LECTURER, UENR-SUNYANI', 'SNR LECTURER, COMPUTER SCIENCE DEPARTMENT', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE DEPARTMENT\r\nUNIVERSITY OF ENERGY AND NATURAL RESOURCES, UENR\r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 214, SUNYANI GHANA', '0244407421 / 0200934', 'Benjamin.weyori@uenr.edu.gh', 'BTU_47968C94_cv_6a0f4d1c3a59e4.54050934.pdf', 'Cv - Eric Akolgo.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.103.41', '2026-05-21 18:21:16', '2026-06-12 23:33:14', 'BTU_47968C94_photo_6a0f4d1c3a5a24.78854166.jpg', '20240804001.jpg'),
(23, 'BTU-61D983D0', 1, 'Mr.', 'Yintii', 'George', 'gyintii@gmail.com', '+233548149861', 'P.O. Box 767', 'Accra', 'Baare', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-715808253-1', '1988-10-06', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences', 7, NULL, 'Chemistry is a foundational concept at the heart of every science-related program. With my background in the field, I can help students understand the vital role chemistry plays in medical laboratory science and demonstrate how to apply these principles practically in their future careers.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Playing video games and football', 'a month', 'I am currently pursuing a PhD in Applied Chemistry (Analytical chemistry) at the University of Technology and Applied Sciences, Navrongo.', 'Auphedeous Yenme Dang-i', 'Lecturer', 'Assistance Dean of Students', 'C. K. Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences\r\nP. O. Box 24\r\nNavrongo, Upper East Region, Ghana', '0243729980', 'adangi@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Jonas Bayuo', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'C. K. Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences\r\nP. O. Box 24\r\nNavrongo, Upper East Region, Ghana', '0543290589', 'jbayuo@cktutas.edu.gh', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_61D983D0_cv_6a0f5a1996d1b0.67531836.pdf', 'TakugbilCV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.100.168', '2026-05-21 19:16:41', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_61D983D0_photo_6a0f5a1996d200.19002381.jpg', 'passportPix.jpg'),
(24, 'BTU-CB1C7B3A', 1, 'Mr.', 'Mubarik', 'Yusif', 'mubas2007@yahoo.com', '+233240835627', 'WACCBIP,\r\nVolta Road\r\nP.O. Box LG 54. Legon', 'Kumasi', 'Akropong, Tabre', 'Ashanti', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Mrs. Getrude Mubarik', 'Kwadaso, Estate, Kumasi, Flat L8', 'Esther Mubarik - 26th April, 2013\r\nDerrick Mubarik - 26th May, 2014\r\nElsie Mubarik - 26th March, 2018', NULL, 'GHA-718458888-1', '1982-05-05', 'male', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'University of Cape Coast', 7, '1.	Mubarik, Y., Boyetey, S. T., Aikins, A. R., &amp; Mutocheluh, M. (2025). Effect of Ochratoxin A (OTA) on the Immune System: A Systematic Review. Toxins, 17(5), 256.\r\n\r\n2.	Specht, S., Klarmann-Schulz, U., Debrah, A.Y., Debrah, L.B., Mand, S., Osei-Mensah, J., Dubben, B., Ayisi-Boateng, N.K., Mubarik, Y., Marfo-Debrekyei, Y. and Fimmers, R., 2026, March. Comparison of six weeks doxycycline versus six weeks rifampicin or three weeks of the combination of doxycycline plus rifampicin in the treatment of onchocerciasis: a randomized, placebo-controlled, double-blind, phase 2 trial. In Open Forum Infectious Diseases (p. ofag065). Oxford University Press.\r\n\r\n3.	Charles, B., Singh, B., Feglo, P., Mubarik, Y., Ntiamoah, P., Owusu, E. A., ... &amp; Singh, S. (2025). Immunological and haematological profiles of pulmonary tuberculosis patients in the Ahafo Region. Egyptian Academic Journal of Biological Sciences. C, Physiology and Molecular Biology, 17(1), 141-152.\r\n\r\n\r\n4.	Kwarteng, Alexander, Ebenezer Asiedu, Augustina Sylverken, Amma Larbi, Yusif Mubarik, and Charles Apprey, ‘In Silico Drug Repurposing for Filarial Infection Predicts Nilotinib and Paritaprevir as Potential Inhibitors of the Wolbachia 5 ?   Aminolevulinic Acid Synthase’, Scientific Reports, 2021, 1–14 https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-021-87976-4\r\n\r\n5.	Charles, B., Singh, B., Abonuusum, A., Feglo, P., Mubarik, Y., &amp; Singh, S. (2025). Haematological and Inflammatory-Associated Cytokine Profiles of Gastrointestinal Parasite-Infected Individuals in The Ahafo Region of Ghana. Egyptian Academic Journal of Biological Sciences, G. Microbiology, 17(1), 203-216.\r\n\r\n6.	Debrah, Linda Batsa, Aliyu Mohammed, Jubin Osei-Mensah, Yusif Mubarik, Olivia Agbenyega, Nana Kwame Ayisi-Boateng, and others, ‘Morbidity Management and Surveillance of Lymphatic Filariasis Disease and Acute Dermatolymphangioadenitis Attacks Using a Mobile Phone-Based Tool by Community Health Volunteers in Ghana’, PLoS Neglected Tropical Diseases, 14.11 (2020) https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pntd.0008839\r\n\r\n7.	Debrah, L.B., Phillips, R.O., Pfarr, K., Klarmann-Schulz, U., Opoku, V.S., Nausch, N., Owusu, W., Mubarik, Y., Sander, A.L., Lämmer, C. and Ritter, M., 2019. The efficacy of doxycycline treatment on Mansonella perstans infection: an open-label, randomized trial in Ghana. The American journal of tropical medicine and hygiene, 101(1), p.84.\r\n\r\n8.	Batsa Debrah, L., Klarmann-Schulz, U., Osei-Mensah, J., Dubben, B., Fischer, K., Mubarik, Y., Ayisi-Boateng, N.K., Ricchiuto, A., Fimmers, R., Konadu, P. and Nadal, J., 2020. Comparison of repeated doses of ivermectin versus ivermectin plus albendazole for the treatment of onchocerciasis: a randomized, open-label, clinical trial. Clinical Infectious Diseases, 71(4), pp.933-943.\r\n\r\n9.	Nausch, N., Antwi-Berko, D., Mubarik, Y., Abass, K.M., Owusu, W., Owusu-Dabo, E., Debrah, L.B., Debrah, A.Y., Jacobsen, M. and Phillips, R.O., 2017. Analysis of Mycobacterium ulcerans-specific T-cell cytokines for diagnosis of Buruli ulcer disease and as potential indicator for disease progression. PLOS Neglected Tropical Diseases, 11(2), p.e0005415.\r\n\r\n10.	Klarmann-Schulz, U., Specht, S., Debrah, A.Y., Batsa, L., Ayisi-Boateng, N.K., Osei-Mensah, J., Mubarik, Y., Konadu, P., Ricchiuto, A., Fimmers, R. and Arriens, S., 2017. Comparison of doxycycline, minocycline, doxycycline plus albendazole and albendazole alone in their efficacy against onchocerciasis in a randomized, open-label, pilot trial. PLoS neglected tropical diseases, 11(1), p.e0005156.\r\n\r\n11.	Ritter, M., Osei-Mensah, J., Debrah, L.B., Kwarteng, A., Mubarik, Y., Debrah, A.Y., Pfarr, K., Hoerauf, A. and Layland, L.E., 2019. Wuchereria bancrofti-infected individuals harbor distinct IL-10-producing regulatory B and T cell subsets which are affected by anti-filarial treatment. PLoS neglected tropical diseases, 13(5), p.e0007436.', 'My academic training and research experience have provided me with a strong foundation in microbiology, immunology, cell biology, molecular biology, and scientific research methodologies, which are highly relevant to teaching in the Medical Laboratory Department. Through my experience as a Graduate Assistant at KCCR/KNUST, I have developed effective communication and mentoring skills that enable me to explain complex scientific concepts clearly to students.\r\n\r\nMy teaching philosophy emphasizes active learning, critical thinking, and practical laboratory training to enhance students’ understanding and professional competence. With approximately 11 years of experience in clinical microbiology research, I have acquired extensive hands-on laboratory expertise and exposure to diverse biomedical research techniques. This experience has also contributed to several scientific publications in reputable journals, demonstrating my commitment to research excellence and scientific advancement.\r\n\r\nI believe my combined experience in teaching, laboratory practice, and research equips me to effectively train and mentor students in the theoretical and practical aspects of medical laboratory science while contributing meaningfully to academic and research development within the department.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading and playing football', 'Immediately', NULL, 'Prof. P Mohamed Mutocheluh', 'Lecturer', 'Professor', 'Department of Clinical Microbiology,  \r\nSchool of Medical Sciences,  \r\nKNUST, Kumasi, Ghana', '0200504700', 'mutocheluh@gmail.com', 'Prof. Alexander Kwarteng', 'Lecturer', 'Professor', 'PMB, KCCR/KNUST, KUMASI', '0555677389', 'senkwarteng@yahoo.co.uk', 'Dr. Anastasia Rosebud Aikins', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Department of Biochemistry, Cell and Molecular Biology,  \r\nSchool of Biological Sciences,  \r\nUniversity of Ghana, Legon, Ghana', '0249126964', 'araikins@ug.edu.gh', 'BTU_CB1C7B3A_cv_6a0f695ae21de4.52359892.pdf', 'MUBARIK CV FOR BTU.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.253.218', '2026-05-21 20:21:46', '2026-06-12 23:06:52', 'BTU_CB1C7B3A_photo_6a0f695ae21e30.43494399.jpg', 'PASSPORT PICTURE.jpg'),
