(29, 'BTU-CEF5F05F', 10, 'Mr.', 'Abagna', 'David', 'davidabagna12@gmail.com', '+233540994549', 'Kongo Senior High School, \r\nPost Office Box 39,\r\nNabdam', 'Sumbrungu', 'Sumbrungu', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'David Abagna', 'Kongo Senior High School,', 'Abagna Daniela 15th June, 2017\r\nAbagna David    8th October,2020', 'P001626007-4', 'GHA-715649607-1', '1990-04-08', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'C.K Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences', 11, NULL, 'I am a dedicated and highly motivated ICT professional with strong commitment to teaching, learning, and continuous professional development. I bring 12 years of teaching experience across basic, senior high school, and tertiary levels, currently serving as a part-time Assistant Lecturer in Computing and Information Technology at Bolgatanga Technical University. I have strong skills in ICT integration, curriculum delivery, and educational technology support.\r\n\r\nI have also served in leadership roles such as Form Master, ICT Coordinator, and Trainer for Core Curriculum programs at both school and district levels, which have strengthened my ability to mentor colleagues and support institutional development.\r\n\r\nMy research in deep learning-based child identification demonstrates my interest in applying emerging technologies such as artificial intelligence and machine learning to real-world problems. I am committed to contributing to academic excellence, research, and innovation in higher education.', 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'My hobbies include  mentoring students, and playing sports.', 'Immediately', 'I am a dedicated ICT professional with 12 years of teaching experience and a strong commitment to academic excellence and ICT integration in education', 'Ms. Gifty Ayamga', 'Teaching', 'Headmistress', 'Kongo Senior High School, \r\nPost Office Box 39,\r\nNabdam', '0244629795', 'giftyayamgaa@gmail.com', 'Prof. Peter Awon-nartemi Agbedemnaab', 'Professor', 'Principal', 'Tumu College of Education\r\nP.O. Box 29\r\nTumu\r\nUpper West Region\r\nGhana', '0208529740', 'petermnaab18@gmail.com', 'Mr. James Adissi Anabire', 'Teaching', 'Assistant Headmaster', 'Kongo Senior High School, \r\nPost Office Box 39,\r\nNabdam', '0242932168', NULL, 'BTU_CEF5F05F_cv_6a0f96e0160368.97431468.pdf', 'DAVID ABAGNA, CURRICULUM VITAE 1.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.126.0', '2026-05-21 23:36:00', '2026-06-12 23:23:14', 'BTU_CEF5F05F_photo_6a0f96e01603b5.01348671.jpg', 'Adobe Scan Jan 03, 2021_1 (1).jpg'),
(30, 'BTU-52BCB4AD', 5, 'Mr.', 'Abban', 'John', 'abbanjohn34@gmail.com', '+233248212699', 'C/O Bethel Methodist Church Taifa\r\nP.O.BOX AT 1019 \r\nAchimota- Accra', 'Accra', 'Mankessim', 'Central', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Martha Osafo', 'C/O Bethel Methodist Church Taifa P.O.BOX AT 1019  Achimota- Accra', 'Dion     Abban                        18th August 2006\r\nJudith   Abban                         21th January 2008\r\nJohn     Abban Júnior              17th May 2011\r\nJudith   Abban                          07th July 2014', 'GHA-000582174-7', 'GHA-000582174-7', '1980-05-13', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development (USTED)', 3, '1.	Power Quality Management using FACTS Devices for Grid-connected PV Solar and Wind    Turbine Systems. Doi: 10.51 52/tepes.2 024.24029    February 2025\r\n2.	 Electricity Potential and Economic Viability for Solar Thermal Plant in Ghana, December 2021\r\n3.	 Techno-Economic and Environmental Analysis of the Energy Scenario in Ghana. https://doi.org/10.4236/sgre.2021.126006     June 2021', '•	Electrical &amp; Electronics Engineering \r\n•	MATLAB-Simulink and HOMER modules simulations, \r\n•	Electrical Power Systems,\r\n•	Power Electronics Modelling and Analysis\r\n•	Machine Drives. \r\n•	Power Plant Engineering. \r\n•	Measurement &amp; Instrumentation\r\n•	Renewable Energy Sustainability solar PV and wind turbine integrations \r\n•	Control System and Telecommunication\r\n•	Research', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '•	Beyond academics, I am actively involved in sports, which enhance my discipline, teamwork, and resilience traits that complement my teaching and leadership roles. \r\n•	I enjoy listening to country music, which provides relaxation and inspiration, nurturing creativity and focus.\r\n•	 I am also deeply passionate about teaching and mentoring, continuously seeking opportunities to guide and motivate young engineers to reach their full potential.', 'I would be able to assume duty within 2 weeks after receiving notification of selection, to allow fo', 'John Abban is an enthusiastic academic committed to teaching all areas of electrical and electronics engineering, as well as to research and innovation in Electrical and Renewable Energy Engineering. He holds a BSc in Electrical/Electronic Engineering, an MTech in Electrical Engineering, and an MPhil in Electrical Power Systems. He is currently pursuing a PhD in Sustainable Energy Engineering and Management. His research focuses on improving the stability and efficiency of grid-connected solar PV and wind systems using FACTS devices. With expertise in MATLAB/Simulink, HOMER Pro, and LEAP, he is well-equipped to teach and mentor students in power systems, renewable energy technologies, and energy management. His teaching philosophy emphasises participatory learning, practical simulations, and project-based training to bridge the gap between theory and real-world engineering challenges. He is passionate about contributing to engineering education, research development, and sustainable energy solutions in Ghana and Africa.', 'Dr Albert Awopone', 'Senior Lecturer - University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development', 'HoD- Electrical and Electronic Department', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development \r\nP.O. Box 1277, Kumasi', '0200784372', 'awopone@gmail.com', 'Dr Felix Amankwah Diawuo', 'Senior Lecturer, University of Energy and Natural Resources (UENR)', 'HoD- Electrical and Electronic Department', 'University of Energy and Natural Resources (UENR)\r\nP.O.BOX 214 Sunyani', '0205100539', 'Felix.diawuo@uenr.edu.gh', 'MR. Francois Sekyere', 'Senior Lecturer - University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development \r\nP.O. Box 1277, Kumasi', '0208185356', 'fskyere@gmail.com', 'BTU_52BCB4AD_cv_6a0fac5f54fd30.41885296.pdf', 'abban CVgtu-compressed.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.160.2.26', '2026-05-22 01:07:43', '2026-06-12 23:42:54', 'BTU_52BCB4AD_photo_6a0fac5f54fda1.40440238.jpg', 'IMG_0496.JPG'),
(31, 'BTU-57BB9347', 1, 'Mr.', 'BUKARI', 'RAYMOND ADOCTA', 'adocta80@gmail.com', '0243615192', 'BOLGATANGA TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY\r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 767, BOLGATANGA', 'SANDEMA', 'SANDEMA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CATHOLIC', 'married', 'AKAATALI JOYCE', 'SANDEMA, MANGO HOUSE', 'ELI ADOCTA 24/02/2006\r\nBLESSING ADOCTA 14/12/2014\r\nAWENSEBA KINGSTON ADOCTA 6/7/2016', NULL, 'GHA-001378343-5', '1980-10-10', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES', 11, NULL, 'My professional experience strongly aligns with the requirements of a university lecturer through my extensive background in medical laboratory science, research, and teaching. With over 15 years of practice in clinical diagnostics within the Ghana Health Service, I have developed deep subject expertise and practical competence that enrich teaching with real-world application. My role as a Health Tutor at NTC and Senior Research Assistant at the University for Development Studies has equipped me with hands-on teaching, student mentoring, and academic research skills. Additionally, my ongoing postgraduate studies in Biochemistry, Molecular Medicine, and Higher Education have strengthened my pedagogical knowledge and research capacity, positioning me to effectively deliver quality teaching, contribute to curriculum development, and support academic research in the university setting.', 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading scientific and medical literature\r\nResearch and data analysis\r\nMentoring and guiding students\r\nParticipating in academic discussions and seminars\r\nCommunity health education and outreach\r\nLearning new laboratory techniques and technologies', 'Immediately', NULL, 'Dr. Nsoh Godwin Anabire', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Head of Biochemistry and Molecular Medicine', 'University for Development Studies\r\nSchool of Medicine\r\nPost Office Box TL 16\r\nTamale', '0240307235', 'nanabire@uds.edu.gh', 'Dr. Charles Nkansah', 'Lecturer', 'Head of Haematology Department', '