(33, 'BTU-5A4B2350', 16, 'Mr.', 'Kaayeng', 'Frederick', 'kaayeng2024@gmail.com', '+233246094178', 'P.O. Box 1\r\nTarkwa - Western Region', 'Zanlerigu', 'Zanlerigu', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Atorboro-Musah Ayishetu', 'OASL - Techiman Municipal Assembly', 'Kaayeng Yenimi -05/10/2009\r\n\r\nKaayeng Lausigna – 25/01/2011\r\n\r\nKaayeng Yenpang – 28/06/2014\r\n\r\nKaayeng Worevonya – 07/04/2022', NULL, 'GHA-718770414-9', '1978-09-22', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Media, Arts and Communication, UNiMAC', 2, '1. “Economic implications of AI on media industries: A systematic review” (2025)\r\nCo-authored with Samuel Danso, Solace Yawa Asafo, Ebenezer Ato Kwamena Aidoo, and Ruth Larweh.\r\n\r\n2. “Mobile Media and Citizen Journalism in Social Activism: A Case of #FixTheCountry Movement” (2024).\r\nUniversity of Cape Coast research thesis', 'Teaching, research, and professional practice of this position, will collectively prepare individuals to communicate effectively through visual media while contributing to artistic development, industry growth, and societal transformation.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Teaching, Learning, Governance, Community Development and Accountability', '1 Month', NULL, 'Dr. Jacob Nyarko', 'Educationist', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University of Cape Coast\r\nCommunication Department', '+233 247407264', 'jacob.nyarko@ucc.edu.gh', 'Alhaji Boffour Ahmed Haruna', 'Civil Servant', 'Municipal Coordinating Director', 'P.O. Box 1\r\nTarkwa - Western Region', '+233 242054455', 'boffouradmedharuna@tnma.gov.gh', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_5A4B2350_cv_6a0fff9fe2eb86.77293672.pdf', 'Frederick Kaayeng - CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.18.63', '2026-05-22 07:02:55', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_5A4B2350_photo_6a0fff9fe2ebe5.58547939.jpg', 'fred.jpg'),
(34, 'BTU-E03DA801', 15, 'Dr.', 'Yidaan', 'Peter Yin-nyeya', 'peteryidaan2@gmail.com', '+233541115909', 'Box 301, Ghana Navy, Sekondi Naval Base, Sekondi', 'Gaare, Tongo', 'Gaare, Tongo Upper East', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-003759599-9', '1986-10-11', 'male', 'PhD', 'Valley View University', 11, 'RESEARCH EXPERIENCE/PUBLICATIONS \r\n1. Experiences of students pursuing a doctoral program: Voices from a private university \r\nin Ghana- 2021 Name and Address of Employer Date of Assumption Position held and \r\nwork involved, Subjects taught if relevant  \r\n2. An analysis of human resource policy framework and governance in the Ghana Armed \r\nForces Peter Yin nyeya Yidaan Western Naval Command, Sekondi Naval Base, Sekondi. \r\nEmail: peteryidaan2@gmail.Com Available Online: 30th June, 2022 URL: \r\nhttps://journals.adrri.org/index.php/home  \r\n3. Labour Turnover and its Effects on Performance of Public Firms in Ghana Peter Yin\r\nnyeya Yidaan1 and Peter Agyekum Boateng2 1Western Naval Command, Sekondi Naval \r\nBase, Communication Department. 2Valley View University, School of Business, Accra. \r\n4 \r\n1Correspondence: peteryidaan2@gmail.com Available Online: 31st March, 2023 URL: \r\nhttps://journals.adrri.org/index.php/home \r\n4. A review on the effect of organizational culture on recruitment and selection practices \r\nin public and private firms in Ghana Peter Yin-nyeya Yidaan Valley View University Email: \r\npeteryidaan2@gmail.com \r\nAvailable \r\nOnline: \r\n31st \r\nMarch, \r\n2022 \r\nURL: \r\nhttps://journals.adrri.org/index.php/home \r\n5. The influence of Christian Ethics and Job Satisfaction on Employee Retention in the \r\nSecurity Services in Ghana - 2022  \r\n6. Africa Perspective of Corporate Governance Practices: A Literature Review – 2023 \r\n7. Effect of perceived ease of use on attitude towards the paperless system in Ghana\'s Ports \r\nand \r\nHarbours \r\nAuthority. \r\n2024 \r\nhttps://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=7779041004203976221&amp;hl=en&amp;oi=scholarr \r\n8. PhD Thesis; Mediating Role of Attitude on the Relationship Between Perceived Ease   \r\nof Use, Perceived Usefulness on Usage Behavior Towards the Paperless System in \r\nGhana’s Ports and Harbour Authority - 2024 \r\n9. Master’s Thesis \r\nTitle: Effect of Reward on Employee Performance at Ghana Cement Company Limited, \r\nTakoradi Branch- 2018 \r\n10. Bachelor degree dissertation \r\nTitle: The Nature and extend of Child Labour among Junior High School Students in \r\nEllembele District in the Western Region of Ghana. - 2015 \r\n11. Diploma project work \r\nTitle: Assisting class two pupils of Ayusiyine Primary School to differentiate between \r\nlower- and upper-case letters. - 2010', 'As an analytical and critical thinker, I approach institutional challenges with structured reasoning and evi-dence-based decision-making. Throughout my career, I have demonstrated the capacity to assess complex administrative systems, identify gaps, and implement practical, results-oriented solutions that enhance effi-ciency and accountability. My ability to interpret policy frameworks and translate them into actionable insti-tutional strategies positions me well to support the University’s governance and regulatory compliance func-tions.\r\nI am highly innovative and visionary, with a forward-looking mindset toward institutional development. I be-lieve that the Office of the Registrar plays a pivotal role in driving academic administration, records man-agement, policy implementation, and stakeholder engagement. I am committed to leveraging technology, strengthening systems, and fostering a culture of continuous improvement to align administrative processes with the \r\nUniversity’s strategic goals.\r\nI possess hands-on ability to work independently while maintaining high standards of professionalism and integrity. My experience has equipped me with excellent communication, interpersonal, and supervisory skills, enabling me to effectively coordinate diverse teams, manage administrative personnel, and build pro-ductive relationships with faculty, students, governing bodies, and external stakeholders.\r\nAs a collaborative leader and good team player, I value collective responsibility and inclusive decision-making. I thrive in dynamic environments and remain composed under pressure, consistently meeting dead-lines and delivering measurable results. My capacity to manage multiple priorities simultaneously ensures that institutional objectives are achieved efficiently and effectively.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading Story Books, swimming, and playing of handball', 'Immediately i receive an appointment letter', 'I wish you would consider my application for the position.', 'Commander Callistus Kuuboma Kommogldomo.', 'Military Officer in the Ghana Navy', 'Commanding Officer', 'box 301, sekondi naval base, sekondi', '0207755238', 'ckuuboma@yahoo.com', 'Dr. Stephen Arthur', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Valley View University, School of Graduate Studies, Oyibi Campus, Accra.', '0546594580', 'Sarthur1@vvu.edu.gh', 'Dr. Josephine Pepra-Mensah', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Valley View University, School of Graduate Studies, Oyibi Campus, Accra.', '0244993075', 'jpepramensah@vvu.edu.gh', 'BTU_E03DA801_cv_6a1011df1df8c9.56472255.pdf', 'CURRENT CV- PETER YIN-NYEYA YIDAAN PDF.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.63.106', '2026-05-22 08:20:47', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_E03DA801_photo_6a1011df1df912.78807485.jpg', 'PP2.jpg');
