l homepage: www.cell.com/heliyon https://doi.org/10.1016/j.heliyon.2023.e19419\r\n\r\n\r\n5. Alexis Munyengabe1, Ledwaba Samuel Kamogelo1, Titus Yeliku-ang Ngmenzuma2 and Maria Fezile Banda1. (2024). The Potential of Helichsryum splendidum (Thunb.) Less. for the Restoration of Sites Polluted with Coal Fly Ash. https://doi.org/10.3390/plants13182551 (published on 11th September 2024)\r\n\r\n\r\n6. Ngmenzuma, T., Oteng-Frimpong, R. and Dakora, F.D. (2025). N2 fixation, grain mineral accumulation, and water-use efficiency in 30 field-grown groundnut (Arachis hypogaea L.) genotypes in South Africa, measured using 15 N and 13 C natural abundance. Frontiers in Agronomy, 7, p.1483741. doi: 10.3389/fagro.2025.1483741.Section: Plant-Soil Interactions \r\n\r\n7. Aluwani Mutanwa Nelwamondoa*, Titus Yeliku-ang Ngmenzumad, Malik Maazab,c, Keletso Cecilia Mohaleb. (2025). Carbon assimilation of three groundnut genotypes subjected to the application of macronutrients nanoparticles (Journal of Crop Science and Biotechnology, https://doi.org/10.1007/s12892-025-00295-2)\r\n\r\n8.Hlengiwe P. Buthelezi1, Titus Y. Ngmenzuma2, Ebere L. Udeh1, Keletso C. Mohale1* (2025). Symbiotic N2 fixation and nutrient uptake of mung bean (Vigna radiata L.) co-inoculated with Bradyrhizobium japonicum and Pseudomonas fluorescens under simulated drought conditions: DOI:10.1080/23311932.2025.2578330 Corpus ID: 282381789\r\n\r\n\r\n9. Innocentia Moloto,Hosana Mkoyi, Fikile Makhuhu,Sandra,Titus Ngmenzuma (2025). Comparison of effects on chlorophyll content and growth between four Solanaceae crops inoculated with Pseudomonas syringae pv. syringae and Pectobacterium carotovorum subsp. carotovorum&quot;, which was submitted to Discover Plants on 18 October 2025 UTC (https://doi.org/10.1007/s44372-025-00437-4)\r\n\r\n\r\n10. Mahlodi R. Maripa1, Titus Y. Ngmenzuma1, Felix D. Dakora2. (2025). Selecting 27 Field-Grown Common Bean (Phaseolus vulgaris L.) Genotypes for Symbiotic Performance and Drought Tolerance at Malkerns Research Station, Eswatini (MDPI, https://doi.org/10.3390/blsf2026057004 or https://sciforum.net/event/IECAG2025)\r\n\r\n\r\n11. Rotondwa Pascalia Gunununu1, Titus Yeliku-ang Ngmenzuma1, Felix Dapare Dakora2 and Mustapha Mohammed. (2026). Plant growth, symbiotic N2-fixation, carbon accumulation and water-use efficiency of 63 common bean (Phaseolus vulgaris L.) genotypes grown under field conditions at Malkerns, Eswatini using the 15N natural abundance technique (Frontiers in Agronomy: (10.3389/fagro.2025.1713315)\r\n\r\n\r\n12. Lebogang J. Msiza1, Titus Y. Ngmenzuma1, Mustapha Mohammed2,4, Sanjay K. Jaiswal3 &amp; Felix D. Dakora3. (2025). Cross-infectivity of 11 different legume species by 15 native rhizobia isolated from African soils (MDPI-Microorganisms section): https://doi.org/10.3390/microorganisms13112463)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n13. Lebogang J. Msiza 1*, Titus Y. Ngmenzuma 1, Mustapha Mohammed 2, and Felix D. Dakora 3*. (2026). Water-use efficiency and mineral nutrition of diverse legume species nodulated by different native rhizobial isolates: do rhizobia have a say in the mineral nutrition of their host plants? (MDPI-Crop Physiology section-accepted): https://doi.org/10.3390/plants15101478', 'As a student mentor, teacher, and researcher, I have supervised several master\'s and PhD students as indicated in my CV. I specialized in crop physiology and soil microbiology.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading and soccer/football', '2 months', 'I have no specific additional information', 'Prof Frank Teng-Zeng', 'Lecturer', 'Professor/ Lecturer', 'Simon Diedon Dombo University of Business and Integrated Development Studies (SDD-UBIDS), Department of History and Political Science, Wa, Ghana, WA', '+233241476983', 'Frank.tengzeng@gmail.com', 'Dr. Richard Oteng-Frimpong', 'Research Scientist', 'Senior Research Scientist', 'CSIR-SAR, Savanna Agricultural Research Institute, Nyankpala, Tamale, Ghana.', '+233208080916', 'kotengfrimpong@gmail.com', 'Dr. Mustapha Mohammed', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University for Development Studies, Tamale, Ghana', '+233241341765', 'imustaph@gmail.com', 'BTU_5DF94CA4_cv_6a106418b3f588.73941016.pdf', 'TITUS CV and certs.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '168.172.0.45', '2026-05-22 14:11:36', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_5DF94CA4_photo_6a106418b3f5d1.79543029.jpg', 'Passport copy.jpg'),
(38, 'BTU-C832157C', 1, 'Mr.', 'ANAFO', 'RAMZY BUGRI', 'rambugri201248@gmail.com', '+233242956101', 'WAR MEMORIAL HOSPITAL, BOX 34, NAVRONGO-UPPER EAST REGION', 'WALEWALE', 'KONGO-BOLLGATANGA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'married', 'ESTHER AWAH', 'J.SQ, TANZUI', 'LORDINA KUNDIHYAN ANAFO-21/12/2012\r\nJEFFERY KUNDIHYAN ANAFO-15/11/2015\r\nLILIAN KUNDIHYAN ANAFO-03/11/2020', NULL, 'GHA-712676825-6', '1984-12-25', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Ghana', 11, '1. Duut, F. Y., Kolog, S. G., Ayimavor, F. K., Anuah, E., Honorfe, C., Anafo, R. B., Agongo, G., Abugri, J., Dang-I, A. Y., &amp; Dassah, S. D. (2026). Prevalence and temporal trends of transfusion-transmissible infections among blood donors in a municipal hospital in Navrongo, Ghana: A retrospective study (2018–2024). Health Science Reports.\r\n\r\n2.	Anafo RB, Atiase Y, Kotey FCN, Dayie NTKD, Tetteh-Quarcoo PB, Duodu S, Osei MM, Alzahrani KJ, Donkor ES. Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) nasal carriage among patients with diabetes at the Korle Bu Teaching Hospital. PLoS One. 2021 Sep 17;16(9):e0257004. doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0257004. PMID: 34534230; PMCID: PMC8448364.\r\n3.	Anafo RB, Atiase Y, Dayie NTKD, Kotey FCN, Tetteh-Quarcoo PB, Duodu S, Osei MM, Alzahrani KJ, Donkor ES. \r\nMethicillin-Resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) Infection of Diabetic Foot Ulcers at a Tertiary Care Hospital in Accra, Ghana. Pathogens. 2021 Jul 24;10(8):937. doi: 10.3390/pathogens10080937. PMID: 34451401; PMCID: PMC8398970.', 'Professional Expertise: the over 16 years of clinical experience and my current role as Laboratory Manager means i bring real-world authority. I can bridge the gap between textbook theory and actual laboratory practice in departments of the laboratory sector.\r\nTeaching Experience: Having already served as an Assistant Lecturer at UDS and UCC, I have a proven track record in academia. I understand curriculum delivery and student engagement specifically within the Ghanaian university system.\r\nResearch Excellence: Publishing in high-impact journals like PLOS ONE and Pathogens demonstrates that I am an active contributor to scientific knowledge. My recent work on transfusion-transmissible infections is also highly relevant for guiding student research and collaboration.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'I enjoy reading, research-related discussions, mentoring younger students, and learning new things within and outside my field. I also like listening to educational podcasts and engaging in outdoor activities to relax and stay productive', '3 months', 'I am a year 3 Medical Microbiology PhD candidate of the University of Ghana Medical School.\r\n In addition to my working experience on the bench, i am also the Regional Mentor for Laboratory Quality Management Systems where i Mentor Upper West Regional Hospital on implementing Quality Management Systems in the lab to improve quality of healthcare in the Region.', 'Prof. Eric Sampane-Donko', 'Lecturer', NULL, 'Dept. Medical Microbiology                                                 \r\nUniversity of Ghana Medical School\r\nP. O. Box 4236\r\nKorle-Bu, Accra', '233547844664', 'ericsdon@hotmail.com.', 'Dr. Richard Glover', 'Programme Specialist International Council for Science', 'Programme Specialist', '(ICSU), Regional Office for Africa,\r\nP. O. Box 13252, Hartfield,\r\nPretoria 002', '+27734743673', 'richkwame@yahoo.com', 'Dr. Eric Wedam', 'MEDICAL OFFICER', NULL, 'WAR MEMORIALL HOSPPITAL, NAVRONGO. BOX 34.', '0242977087', 'wedam5eric@gmail.com', 'BTU_C832157C_cv_6a1066b5885013.16998845.pdf', 'Ramzy\'s curriculum vitae..pdf', 'pending', NULL, '41.155.117.231', '2026-05-22 14:22:45', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_C832157C_photo_6a1066b5885051.98140936.jpeg', 'WhatsApp Image 2026-05-21 at 09.34.06.jpeg'),
