(44, 'BTU-6E7DE88C', 2, 'Dr.', 'Zakaria', 'Adnan', 'yandayekekenan@gmail.com', '233208773118', 'P.O.Box TL 2002, Tamale, Ghana.', 'Tamale', 'Tamale', 'Northern', 'Ghanaian', NULL, 'married', 'Mohammed Fuseina', 'P.O.Box TL 2002, Tamale, Ghana', NULL, NULL, 'GHA-715192167-3', '1980-07-25', 'male', 'PhD', 'C.K. Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences', 11, 'Adnan Zakaria, Shaibu Osman, Christian John Etwire, and Oluwole Daniel Makinde. Modeling the dynamics of some common reported offenses by the Ghana Police Service. Partial Differential Equations in Applied Mathematics, 14:101171, 2025.', NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, NULL, '1 week', 'I have recently, successfully defended my PhD thesis in Mathematics at C. K. Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences and am currently awaiting my formal graduation in June 2026.', 'Dr. Shaibu Osman', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University of Health and Allied Sciences \r\nPMB 31, Ho, Volta Region, Ghana.', '0246343568', 'sosman@uhas.edu.gh', 'Prof. Etwire Christian John', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'C.K. Tedam University of Technology and Applied Science\r\nP. O. Box 24, Navrongo', '0246013140', 'cetwire@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Mr. Mohammed Dokurugu', 'Teacher', 'Headmaster', 'Anbariya Senior High School  \r\nP. O. Box TL 75, Tamale.', '0244457652', NULL, 'BTU_6E7DE88C_cv_6a10b9ddef9413.24524509.pdf', 'CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.43.64', '2026-05-22 20:17:33', '2026-05-22 20:17:33', 'BTU_6E7DE88C_photo_6a10b9ddef9479.67600028.jpg', 'AD_US21.jpg'),
(45, 'BTU-85C6C650', 15, 'Mr.', 'GORATEBE', 'NORBERT BIYEEN', 'goratebenorbert@gmail.com', '0208489811', 'BOLGA ANGLICAN JUNIOR HIGH \r\nPOST OF OFFICE BOX 46\r\nBOLGATANGA, UPPER EAST RIGION', 'BUNKPURUGU', 'BUNKPURUGU', 'North East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'married', 'ATUESAH MARY', 'BOLGA ANGLICAN JUNIOR HIGH  POST OF OFFICE BOX 46 BOLGATANGA, UPPER EAST RIGION BOLGA ANGLICAN JUNIOR HIGH  POST OF OFFICE BOX 46 BOLGATANGA, UPPER EAST RIGION', 'GORATEBE CONDOLEEZZA DANANSUAH -   10TH AUGUST, 2008\r\n\r\nGORATEBE ELIAS YOBE- 19TH AUGUST, 20012\r\n\r\nGORATEBE GADDIEL- 20TH APRIL,2019', 'P0010414851', 'GHA-715346980-9', '0000-00-00', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION, WINNEBA', 11, NULL, NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING, LISTENING TO MUSIC, WATCHING AND PLAY SOCCER, VOLLEYBALL AND ATHLETICS', 'IMMEDIATELY', 'I AM ALWAYS READY TO LERAN FROM OTHERS', 'PROF. CHARLES B. CAMPION', 'DIRECTOR', 'DIRECTOR, QUALITY ASSURANCE', 'REGENTROPFEN UNIVERSITY COLLEGE \r\nP.M.B KANSOE, BOLGATANGA. UER', '024820376', 'dapqa@regentropfen.edu.gh', 'GEORGE ASIRA', 'DIRECTOR', 'BOLGA MUNICIPAL  EDUCATIION DIRECTOR', 'BOLGA MUNICIPAL EDUCATION DIRECTORATE \r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 11', '0244090480', NULL, 'CATHERINE NYAABA', 'SUPERVISOR', 'SCHOOL IMPROVEMENT SUPPORT OFFICER', 'BOLGA MUNICIPAL EDUCATION DIRECTORATE \r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 11', '0246180026', NULL, 'BTU_85C6C650_cv_6a1197683ec157.65651880.pdf', 'Goratebe Norbert CV.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '41.155.117.245', '2026-05-23 12:02:48', '2026-06-12 22:48:41', 'BTU_85C6C650_photo_6a1197683ec1a1.45032522.jpeg', 'WhatsApp Image 2026-05-23 at 11.22.04 AM.jpeg'),
(46, 'BTU-FA56ADBA', 3, 'Mr.', 'Akangaamkum', 'Alaazi Terah', 'alaaziterah94@gmail.com', '+233547524961', 'Bolgatanga Technical University (BTU), Post Office Box 767; Sumbrungu, Bolgatanga, Upper East Region.\r\nDepartment of Agricultural Engineering', 'Sandema, Upper East Region', 'Sandema, Upper East Region', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-727604263-3', '1994-08-04', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University for Development Studies', 5, 'List of Publications \r\n\r\n1.  Akangaamkum, T. A., Adongo, T. A., Sibale, D. (2025): Keyhole Gardening: A Water-Smart Pathway to Household Food Security-A Review. International Journal of Agriculture and Food Science 2025; 7(9): 528-538. DOI: https://doi.org/10.33545/2664844X.2025.v7.i9g.790.\r\n2.  Akangaamkum, T. A., Ayambila, S. N., and Adongo, T. A. (2025). Gross Margin Analysis of Chili Pepper and Okro Cultivated Under Rainfed and Supplementary Irrigation in the Northern Region of Ghana. Acta Sci. Pol. Formatio Circumiectus 24 (2) 2025, 17–28. DOI: http://dx.doi.org/10.15576/ASP.FC/207134.\r\n3.  Akangaamkum, T. A., Ayambila, S. N., and Adongo, T. A., Kareem O.M. (2025). Can the Synergy Between Supplementary Irrigation and Fertilizer Improve Chili Pepper Productivity in Semi-Arid Climates? Lessons from the WACWISA Experimental Site in Ghana. International Journal of Agriculture and Food Science. IJAFS 2025; 7(11): 640-647 DOI: https://www.doi.org/10.33545/2664844X.2025.v7.i11i.1016.\r\n4.  Othong, Z. J., Bwambale, E., Sibale, D., Umukiza, E., Ntole, R., Alaazi, T. A. &amp; Chikavumbwa, S. R. (2025). Financial viability of centre pivot sprinkler irrigation systems in a semi-arid climate. Journal of Water and Land Development, 9-14. DOI: 10.24425/jwld.2025.154245. \r\n5.  Akangaamkum, A. T. (2023). Effect of Supplementary Irrigation and Fertilizer Levels on Growth and Yield of Chili Pepper (Capsicum annuum L.) and Okro (Abelmoschus esculentus L.) in Northern Region of Ghana (Masters Dissertation). http://udsspace.uds.edu.gh/handle/123456789/4183#:~:text=to%20this%20item%3A-,http%3A//hdl.handle.net/123456789/4183,-Title%3A%C2%A0.\r\n\r\nList of Conference Proceedings \r\n\r\n1.  William Amponsah, John B. A. Nyasapoh, Alaazi Terah Akangaamkum, Eric Oppong Danso, Amadu Mahama, Patricia Amankwaa-Yeboah, Francis Kemausuor (2026). Can Agrivoltaic Technology Improve Vegetable Yield and Water Use Efficiency in Semi-Arid Climates? Lessons from the Tropical Agrivoltaic Research Fields (TARF) in Ghana. Conference proceedings (Oral presentation): The 56th Ghana Institution of Engineering (GhIE) under the theme “Engineering the Food Security and Sustainable Agriculture Value Chain; March 16th –20th, 2026.\r\n\r\n2. Akangaamkum, T. A., Ayambila, S. N., and Adongo, T. A. (2024). Gross Margin Analysis of Chili Pepper and Okro Cultivated Under Rainfed and Supplementary Irrigation in the Northern Region of Ghana. In conference proceedings (Book of Abstracts): The 7th Annual Conference of Ghana Association of Agricultural Economists (GAAE) under the theme “Regenerative and Precision Agriculture for Inclusive Value Chain Development in Africa” at UDS Guest House, Tamale from October 2nd – 5th, 2024.\r\n\r\n\r\n3.  Akangaamkum, T. A., Ayambila, S. N., and Adongo, T. A. (2024). Effects of Supplementary Irrigation and Fertilizer Levels on Growth and Yield of Chili Pepper (Capsicum annuum L.) in Northern Ghana. In conference proceedings (Book of Abstracts): Third Annual Graduate School Conference (AGC) under the theme “Research and National Development: The Role of Graduate Students,” underscoring the essential link between academic inquiry and national progress, UDS, Nyankpala campus, November 6th –7th, 2024.', 'My teaching, research, and professional experiences are highly relevant to the position of Lecturer in the Department of Agricultural Engineering. My academic background in Agriculture Technology and MPhil in Irrigation and Drainage Engineering has provided me with strong theoretical and practical knowledge in irrigation systems, soil–water–plant relationships, water management, and sustainable agricultural practices, which are key areas within Agricultural Engineering.\r\n\r\nMy experience as a Teaching and Research Assistant at the University for Development Studies has equipped me with practical teaching skills in lecture delivery, tutorials, supervision of practical sessions, and student assessment, all of which are essential responsibilities of a lecturer.\r\n\r\nIn the area of research, my MPhil work on supplementary irrigation and vegetable production strengthened my competencies in experimental design, data analysis, and scientific writing, leading to several publications. These experiences have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to research, student supervision, and academic publications within the department.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, my involvement in research and field-based projects with institutions such as Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST), World Food Programme (WFP), Ghana Productive Safety Net Project 2 (GPSNP II), and Council for Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR) has exposed me to applied agricultural engineering research and community-based development interventions. These experiences have enhanced my ability to integrate theory with practical field applications, which is essential for effective teaching, research, and extension services in Agricultural Engineering.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading and Research activities', 'Immediately', '1. In addition to my teaching and research experience, I was recently contracted as the Lead Assessor for the risk assessment of the rehabilitation of small earth dams across selected communities in the Upper East and North East Regions under the Ghana Productive Safety Net Project II (GPSNP II). In this role, I was responsible for assessing potential environmental, structural, and social risks associated with dam rehabilitation activities. This assignment strengthened my practical expertise in water resources infrastructure, safety evaluation, and field-based engineering assessment, further enhancing my ability to apply agricultural engineering principles to real-world development projects.\r\n\r\n2. I have also applied to begin my PhD programme in 2026, as part of my continuous academic and professional development.\r\n\r\n3. I also completed a professional training course in project management, covering key areas such as project planning, execution, monitoring and evaluation, risk management, and stakeholder coordination.', 'Prof. Raphael Adu-Gyamfi', 'University lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University for Development Studies, Post Office Box TL. 1882, Tamale\r\nDepartment of Crop Science', '+233 (0) 208114382', 'raphpat205@yahoo.com', 'Dr. Thomas Apusiga Adongo', 'University lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University for Development Studies, Post Office Box TL. 1882, Tamale\r\nDepartment of Agricultural Mechanization and  Irrigation Technology', '+233 (0)249690174', 'aapusiga@uds.edu.gh', 'Prof.  Gordana Kranjac-Berisavljevic', 'University lecturer', 'Senior lecturer', 'University for Development Studies, Post Office Box TL. 1882, Tamale\r\nDepartment of Agricultural Engineering', '+233 (0) 244467142', 'nova.gordanak@gmail.com', 'BTU_FA56ADBA_cv_6a11b43ab2a9c5.46121230.pdf', 'Curriculum Vitae.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.254.66', '2026-05-23 14:05:46', '2026-06-12 23:52:26', 'BTU_FA56ADBA_photo_6a11b43ab2aa19.73947696.jpeg', 'Passport picture.jpeg'),
(47, 'BTU-08A2C898', 8, 'Mr.', 'Nsobila', 'Charles', 'nsobilac68@gmail.com', '0548012623', 'Ampunyase D/A Junior High School, \r\nPost Office Box 4, \r\nAkrofuom-Adansi.', 'Vea', 'Vea', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Joanita Ayimpoka Akolbila', NULL, 'Rex Apusiyine Atorogo, 19/11/2018\r\nThelma Ayinnongmah Atorogo, 16/04/2021\r\nNeriah Ayinmaaliya Atorogo, 28/04/2026', 'P0014249170', 'GHA-717134755-8', '1986-09-26', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development', 7, 'No formal publication yet; however, a manuscript based on my M.Phil. thesis has been developed and is being accepted for the Global Interdisciplinary Green Cities Conference 2026 in Western New England University, which will come off on June 16-20, 2026.', 'I have a decade of teaching experience at the secondary level and at the basic level. Also, my academic training has equipped me with a strong foundation in financial accounting, management accounting, audit and assurance, corporate reporting, and financial reporting, as well as financial management. This makes me a strong and committed candidate for the position. \r\nMy research experience is also based on my MPhil thesis. which was conducted on &quot;Corporate Governance and Orgnizational Performance: The Mediation and Moderation Roles of Innovation and Innovative Culture in the Manufacturing Sector of Ghana&quot;.\r\nBased on the above information regarding my teaching experience and my research experience, I am confident that I will be the most suitable candidate for this position.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '•	Reading storybooks.\r\n•	Watching documentaries.\r\n•	Listening to news and watching movies. \r\n•	Listening to current affairs, especially news files on Saturdays.', 'At least 1 to 2 weeks.', '•	Form master/examination team member for Ampunyase D/A JHS, 2023 to date.\r\n•	Financial Secretary for St William\'s Chaplaincy, USTED, 2020/2021.\r\n•	Ag. Headteacher for Nyariga-Doone Girls’ Primary School for a year, 2017/2018.\r\n•	Examination coordinator for Maurice Browne JHS, 2016/2017.\r\n•	President, Association of Catholic Teacher Trainees, Gbewaa College of Education, 2013/2014.\r\n•	Financial Secretary for St Maria Goretti Chaplaincy, Big Boss 2010/2011.', 'Dr. Prince Gyimah', 'Lecturing', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development,\r\nPost Office Box 1277,\r\nKumasi.', '0540643517', 'pgyimah@aamusted.edu.gh', 'Dr. Engr. Patrick Nyaaba Ayambire', 'Lecturing', 'Lecturer', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development,\r\nPost Office Box 1277,\r\nKumasi.', '0552424305', 'pnayambire@aamusted.edu.gh', 'Mr. Eric Amponsah', 'Teaching', 'Headteacher', 'Ampunyase D/A Junior High School,\r\nPost Office Box 4, \r\nAkrofuom.', '0246136287', 'ercowinsouls@gmail.com', 'BTU_08A2C898_cv_6a11d2a788f0f5.08560320.pdf', 'HTU Application Letter.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.122.85', '2026-05-23 16:15:35', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_08A2C898_photo_6a11d2a788f141.36783595.jpg', '966787.jpg'),
(48, 'BTU-9578F1CE', 1, 'Dr.', 'NUOH', 'ROBERT DOMO', 'nuohrobert@yahoo.com', '0244525513', 'GHANA HEALTH SERVICE  PO BOX 298 WA UWR\r\nRGIONAL HEALTH DIRECTOATE/ WA MUNICIPAL HOSPITAL', 'New -Longor', 'Lawra-Zambo', 'Upper West', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Ruby K Jia', 'TI Ahamadyiya school Kumasi', 'Maureen Nuoh : 11/05/2011\r\nElvis Nuh : 03/01/2013\r\nMichelle Nuoh 21/05/2017\r\nMichael Nuoh 21/05/2017', NULL, 'GHA-715874051-0', '1978-07-07', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'university of Ghana', 11, '•	Review of meningitis surveillance data, Upper West Region of Ghana, 2009-2013\r\n•	Large Cholera Outbreak in Brong Ahafo Region of Ghana \r\n•	Uncommon mixed Outbreak of Pneumococcal and Meningococcal meningitis in Jirapa District of the Upper West Region of Ghana, 2016', 'I have directly conduct research in the laboratory space  including writing SOPs testing in all major medical laboratory departments  including haematology, Microbiology, Clinical chemistry and Blood banking. I have also bee teaching intern laboratory scientist and attachment student in last 10 years', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'reading , riding , movies and watching academic content o social media', '1 month', NULL, 'Dr Culbert Nuolabong', 'Tutor/Lecturer/Epidemiologist', 'Principal-Nursing  ad Mdwifery training college Sekondi, Coodinator UDS nursing program', 'Nursing and Midwifery  Training college, Sekondi\r\nP.O. Box 33 Sekondi Western  Region \r\nGhana', '0243841631', 'culbertnuolabong@yahoo.com', 'Dr Nuhaila Koray Issaka', 'Medical laboratory scientist / lecturer', 'Acting Laboratory Manager, Wa Municipal Hospital, Lecturer HLTU, Wa', 'Wa Municipal Hospital\r\n\r\nP.O.Box 6 , Wa  UWR', '024497972370', 'Nuhailako@yahoo.co.uk', 'Professsor Ernest Kenu', 'university Profesor', 'Professor  and Program Director, Ghana Field Epidemiology and Laboratory Training Program', 'Ghana Field Epidemiology and Laboratory Training program\r\nSchool of Public Health  University of Ghana\r\nP.O Box LG 13\r\nLegon Accra', '0244592122', 'ernest_kenu@yahoo.co.uk', 'BTU_9578F1CE_cv_6a120ea2df0a96.54307511.pdf', 'ROBERT NUOH DOMO CV-HTI app.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.243.63', '2026-05-23 20:31:30', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_9578F1CE_photo_6a120ea2df0af3.44943431.jpg', 'ROBERT PHOTO 4.jpg'),
(49, 'BTU-DF6083CA', 14, 'Mr.', 'ADOLINAMA', 'ANAAFO ERIC', 'ericadolinama@gmail.com', '0249868947', 'YOUTH EMPLOYMENT AGENCY\r\nBOX 50\r\nRCC-BOLGATANGA', 'AKAMO', 'KANDIGA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIANITY', 'married', 'STELLA AYAMGA', 'ZENGA PRIMARY SCHOOL, BOX 46, KNWD', 'FORTUNATUS ADOLINAMA - 07/08/2010\r\nTALITHA ADOLINAMA - 22/09/2014\r\nEVAN ADOLINAMA - 02/01/2018\r\nNINA ADOLINAMA 1/07/2021', 'P0009946608', '715785808-3', '1984-03-30', 'male', 'Professional Certificate', 'INSTITUTE OF CHARTERED ACOOUNTANTS-GHANA', 11, NULL, NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING AND FOOTBALL', 'IMMEDIATELY', 'BEFORE ASSUMING THE ROLE AS A DEPUTY REGIONAL DIRECTOR- OPERATIONS, I HAVE WORKED WITH YOUTH EMPOLYMENY AGENCY AS A PROJECT ASSISTANT AND DISTRICT DIRECTOR FOR KASSENA NANKANA WEST DISTRICT.', 'MICHAEL AKELINBONA ATIA', 'AUDITOR', 'AUDIT MANAGER', 'A.A. GRAND CONSULT \r\nBOX BG593\r\nBOLGA- BRANCH\r\nUPPER EAST REGION', '0244040841', 'atiaamike@gmail.com', 'ROBERT ANERIBA AYELIKILUM', 'BANKER', 'BRANCH MANAGER', 'NAARA RURAL BANK\r\nBOX 14\r\nNAVRONGO- BRANCH', '0243366031', 'rayelikilum@yahoo.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_DF6083CA_cv_6a1212bcd17215.03412449.pdf', 'CV-ERIC ADOLINAMA.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.101.55', '2026-05-23 20:49:00', '2026-06-12 22:40:48', 'BTU_DF6083CA_photo_6a1212bcd173c0.11082428.jpeg', 'ERIC P.jpeg'),
(50, 'BTU-54ECD247', 1, 'Mr.', 'ADONGO', 'JOEL AZUURE', 'joeladongo@gmail.com', '0242344557', 'AGGREY MEMORIAL AME ZION SHS\r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 189\r\nCAPE COAST', 'BONGO', 'BONGO', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIANITY', 'married', 'SHIRLEY ALATIAH', 'BOX 189, CAPE COAST', 'JAEL ABERINGA ADONGO- 26/01/2024\r\nJOANNA AWINESEKEMA ADONGO-01/01/2026', 'P0024800449', 'GHA-72004614-2', '1990-04-24', 'male', 'PhD', 'UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION, WINEBA', 0, '•	Undergraduate project work on the topic; Science Teachers Beliefs in Teaching Science\r\n•	Postgraduate MPhil thesis on the topic; Effects of Computer-Assisted Instruction and Concept Mapping on Students Performance in Cellular Respiration\r\n•	Owusu, E.Y, Adongo, J.A, Agyare, E.B and Appiah-Kubi, K. (2023). Assessing the Impact of Integrating Information and Communication Technology on Senior High School Students’ Achievement in Genetics. International Techology and Education Journal 7(18-27). https://itejournal.com/en/assessing-the-impact-of-integrating-information-and-communication-technology-on-senior-high-school-students-achievement-in-genetics.htm\r\nPapers under working for publication \r\n•	Effects of Computer-Assisted Instruction and Concept Mapping on Students Performance in Cellular Respiration\r\n•	Is the Concept Mapping the Alternate to Teaching Perceived Difficult Biology Concept in Under-resourced schools? Assessing Students’ Experiences and Attitudes\r\nBOOK AUTHORSHIP\r\n• Author: Bedrock Series – Elective Biology (SHS-level textbook aligned with the Ghana Education Service curriculum)', 'My experience as a science educator, researcher, and curriculum developer closely aligns with the demands of a Biology Lecturer in the Department of Medical Laboratory Sciences. Having taught Elective Biology and Integrated Science for over eight years at the senior high school level I have developed strong competencies in breaking down complex biological concepts and delivering them in ways that are accessible, engaging, and academically rigorous. These skills translate directly to university-level teaching, where clarity of instruction and deep content knowledge are essential. My experience organizing and supervising laboratory practical sessions has further equipped me with the ability to guide students through hands-on scientific procedures, a fundamental requirement in training Medical Laboratory Science students.\r\nBeyond teaching, my research and scholarly work demonstrate a solid academic foundation appropriate for a lecturer\'s role. My MPhil thesis investigated the effects of Computer-Assisted Instruction and Concept Mapping on students\' performance in Cellular Respiration, a subject central to biological and medical sciences. I have a peer-reviewed publication on ICT integration in genetics instruction, with two additional papers currently being prepared for publication. As an author of the Bedrock Series: Elective Biology textbook, I have proven my ability to develop structured, curriculum-aligned academic content. My ongoing PhD in Biology Education further reflects my commitment to scholarly growth. Combined with my proficiency in statistical tools such as SPSS and Excel, my experience as a WAEC Examiner and Team Leader, and my participation in international educational programmes such as Engineering for Us All (e4usa), I am confident that my background positions me as a well-rounded candidate who will contribute meaningfully to both the teaching and research goals of your department.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'I like science quiz competitions and drills. I also sing as a hobby.', 'Immediately', 'I am ready to take further programs to enhance my role in this position', 'Mr. Abudu Fatao', 'Lecturering', 'Lecturer', 'School of Science, Mathematics and Technology Education, \r\nC. K. Tedam University of Technology and Applied Science,', '+233 243980810', 'fabudu@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Dr. Stacy Klein-Gardner', 'Lecturing', 'Executive Director, Engineering for US All', 'Engineering for US All \r\n7761 Diamondback Drive, College Park, Maryland 20740, United States', '240-623-0053', 'stacy@e4usa.org', 'Dr. John Essandoh', 'Lecturing', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University of Cape Coast, School of Biological Sciences', '+233 277144915', 'jessandoh@ucc.edu.gh', 'BTU_54ECD247_cv_6a123ac7025ee0.82562085.pdf', 'Joel Azuure Adongo CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.130.15', '2026-05-23 23:39:51', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_54ECD247_photo_6a123ac7025f28.97252332.jpg', 'MR. ADONGO.jpg');
