(54, 'BTU-52544D1B', 2, 'Mr.', 'AYINE', 'NSOH DONATUS', 'donatusayinesh@gmail.com', '0541939450', 'C/O ZAMSE SHTS P.O.BOX 203, BOLGATANGA', 'DULUGU', 'DULUGU', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIANITY', 'married', 'SHIRLEY AGALSEY AYINE', 'C/O FOUNTAIN GATE CHAPEL BOX 299, BOLGA', 'DAVINA AZUSIYINE-                          24TH FEBRUARY,   2009\r\nDANIELLE  AYINONGEMA-                28TH SEPTEMBER, 2011\r\nDAMIAN    AYINBONO                      6TH SEPTEMBER,   2016', 'P0010145699', 'GHA-715567615-3', '1978-09-09', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION, WINNEBA', 11, 'Israel, P. C., Baba, M., Abusah, E., &amp; Ayine, D. N. (2022). Discursive Functions of Monosyllabic Responses in Online Friendly Conversations. NIU Journal of Humanities, 7(4), 127-135.\r\n\r\nAyine, D. N. (2025). An analysis of clause complexing in selected coronavirus updates by President Nana Akufo-Addo (Mphil thesis, University of Education, Winneba).', 'I have 15 years of teaching experience at the secondary school level, during which I have developed strong skills in lesson planning, classroom instruction, curriculum delivery, and student assessment. This long experience has enabled me to simplify complex concepts, manage diverse learners effectively, and create engaging learning environments that promote understanding and academic performance. I am also well-versed in syllabus interpretation and examination preparation, having consistently participated in setting, marking, and evaluating student work. In addition, I have been involved in continuous professional development and classroom-based reflection to improve teaching outcomes. I also have a strong research experience at the tertiary level. I am committed to developing my research skills to contribute effectively to teaching, research, and academic service in higher education.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING, WRITING, WATCHING FOOTBALL', 'IMMEDIATELY', NULL, 'DR. AMA ABRAFI', 'LECTURING', 'GRADUATE COORDINATOR', 'University of Education, Winneba\r\nP. O. Box 25\r\nWinneba\r\nCentral Region\r\nGhana', '024473980', 'gcdee@uew.edu.gh', 'EMMANUEL AKAGERI', 'TEACHING', 'ASSISTANT HEADMASTER, ACADEMIC AFFAIRS', 'ZAMSE SENIOR HIGH/ TECHNICAL SCHOOL\r\nP.O.BOX 203\r\nBOLGATANGA\r\nUPPER EAST REGION', '0243235422', 'emmakageri@gmail.com', 'DR. JAMES AZANLERIGU', 'LECTURING', 'SRN LECTURER', 'BOLGATANGA TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY\r\nP.O.BOX  767\r\nSUMBRUGU, BOLGATANGA\r\nGHANA', '0206341395', 'jamesabagna43@gmail.com&gt;', 'BTU_52544D1B_cv_6a133facc7c8f2.46525166.pdf', 'AYINE DONATUS NSOH.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.247.122', '2026-05-24 18:13:00', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_52544D1B_photo_6a133facc7c944.57294110.jpeg', 'WhatsApp Image 2026-05-24 at 17.21.34.jpeg'),
(55, 'BTU-483D8D9C', 14, 'Mr.', 'ABAANE', 'MOSES AYINYELYA', 'mosesabaane@gmail.com', '+233243789847', 'SACRED HEART CATHEDRAL PARISH\r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 5', 'BOLGA, UPPER EAST REGION', 'ZUARUNGU, UPPER EAST REGION', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'married', 'NDEGO KATE AWIN', 'SACRED HEART CATHEDRAL PARISH', NULL, 'P0023926775', 'GHA-715404679-3', '1989-11-18', 'male', 'Professional Certificate', 'ICAGH', 5, NULL, 'I am a Chartered Accountant with expertise in financial reporting, audit, budgeting, and internal controls. I bring strong analytical skills, integrity, and a solutions-driven mindset to every assignment. My ability to think critically, work collaboratively, and communicate clearly sets me apart. I aim to strengthen financial discipline, enhance decision-making, and contribute meaningfully to organisational growth and success.', 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING, TEACHING, WATCHING, AND PLAYING SOCCER', 'IMMEDIATELY', NULL, '1.	SAEED HUSSEIN YAKUBU', 'ACCOUNTANT', 'DEPUTY DIRECTOR OF FINANCE', 'GHANA HEALTH SERVICE\r\nPOST OF BOX 175', '+233 262 211 554', 'ysfuzzy@gmail.com', '2.	ISSAH NOBLE MUBARAK', 'INTERNAL AUDIT', 'HEAD OF INTERNAL AUDIT', 'HEAD OF INTERNAL AUDIT\r\nUPPER EAST REGIONAL HOSPITAL', '+233 208 740 625', 'noblemubarak@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_483D8D9C_cv_6a137b529ec589.08623023.pdf', 'ABAANE, MOSES AYINYELYA -ICAG CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.121.44', '2026-05-24 22:27:30', '2026-05-24 22:27:30', 'BTU_483D8D9C_photo_6a137b529ec5e9.42978062.jpeg', 'MOSES AYINYELYA ABAANE.jpeg'),
(56, 'BTU-05ED3EBB', 8, 'Mr.', 'Atindana', 'Elijah', 'elijahatindana@yahoo.com', '+233206408423', 'Post Office Box 39, Bolgatanga', 'Accra', 'Bongo-Feo', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', NULL, NULL, 'Atindana Winmalya Ariella-21 September 2025', NULL, 'GHA-715367649-8', '1989-10-20', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences', 0, '2024: ‘Statistical Network Analysis of Macroeconomic Variables in Ghana’ published by American Journal of Theoretical and Applied Statistics (https://doi.org/10.11648/j.ajtas.20241306.15).', 'My academic training has provided me with advanced knowledge in econometrics, applied statistics, and economic analysis. During my MPhil program, I worked extensively with empirical data, applied statistical modeling, and explored macroeconomic relationships, experiences that strengthened my ability to integrate research with teaching. In addition, my background in education has equipped me with pedagogical skills, enabling me to deliver lectures effectively, mentor students, and design engaging coursework that fosters critical thinking.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading of novels, sports, watching documentaries, playing guitar and listening to music.', '1 week', NULL, 'Dr. Gideon Mensah Engmann', 'Lecturer', 'lecturer at Department of Statistics and Actuarial Sciences, University of Technology and Applied Sc', NULL, '+233 207861309', 'gidengmann@yahoo.com', 'Dr. Alidu Musa', 'Lecturer', 'Principal at Gbewa College of Education', NULL, '0244537476', 'tkhalid2001@yahoo.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_05ED3EBB_cv_6a137d64db1732.09502662.pdf', 'Elijah cv -.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.140.46', '2026-05-24 22:36:20', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_05ED3EBB_photo_6a137d64db1783.62605361.jpg', 'passport pic1.jpg'),
(57, 'BTU-763E4A4E', 1, 'Mr.', 'AYAMGA', 'ELVIS', 'ayamga4live@gmail.com', '+233248257956', 'BONGO DISTRICT HOSPITAL, P.O. BOX 18, BONGO, UER.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1991-04-25', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences, Navrongo, Ghana', 7, '1.	Essien-Baidoo, S., Obiri-Yeboah, D., Opoku, Y. K., Ayamga, E., Hodi Zie, K., Attoh, D., Obboh, E., Hayfron Benjamin, A., &amp; Afrifa, J. (2019). ART Regimen and Other Sociodemographics Do Not Affect Cytokine Expression in HIV Patients in Ghana. The Canadian journal of infectious diseases &amp; medical microbiology = Journal canadien des maladies infectieuses et de la microbiologie medicale, 2019, 2730370. https://doi.org/10.1155/2019/2730370\r\n\r\n2.	Duut, F. Y., Nfoke, S. P., Ayamga, E., Kwayaja, N., Senoo, D. K. J., Agongo, G., Abugri, J., &amp; Dassah, S. D. (2026). Prevalence and determinants of hepatitis B, hepatitis C, and liver injury among people living with HIV on antiretroviral therapy in the Upper East Region of Ghana. BMC infectious diseases, 26(1), 515. https://doi.org/10.1186/s12879-026-12784-y\r\n\r\n3.	Francis Yennube Duut, Samuel Punignan Nfoke, Elvis Ayamga et al. Virologic outcomes and associated factors among people living with HIV on antiretroviral therapy in the Upper East Region of Ghana: a facility-based cross-sectional study, 10 February 2026, PREPRINT (Version 1) available at Research Square [https://doi.org/10.21203/rs.3.rs-8603324/v1]', 'Relevant to this position of a lecturer in medical laboratory science are my diverse experiences in academics; continual engagement in training, supervision and mentorship; scientific presentations; participation in research activities; publications; clinical practice; and leadership roles. Coupled to these is a deep passion, developed over the years, for teaching and developing future healthcare professionals.\r\nFirstly, my educational background in Medical Laboratory Science and Biochemistry and Molecular Biomedicine has provided me with the required academic and research skills needed to educate learners in higher institutions. During this academic journey, I obtained profound knowledge in core subject areas in medical laboratory science including, clinical chemistry, immunology, pathology, hematology and microbiology. Also, the researches I conducted in the course of my studies helped refine my skills in scientific writing, data analysis, experimental design, and scientific presentations; all of which are essential for this lecturer role. \r\nApart from my academic pursuits, my professional endeavors accorded me opportunities for active engagement in tutoring, mentoring, and supervising in the clinical setting. Serving in various roles including: as a biomedical scientist, quality manager and laboratory manager at the Paga and Bongo District Hospitals, my regular duties included supervising and mentoring laboratory staff, interns, and laboratory personnel in sub-district facilities. Further, I have been involved in facilitating the training of health professionals in malaria diagnostics as well as making presentations in both clinical meetings and international conferences. These activities have equipped me with strong skills in communication and facilitation necessary for the lecturer position.\r\nIn addition, I have been involved in biomedical and epidemiological research activities throughout my education and professional endeavors. Besides my academic research, I have been engaged in fieldworks such as case investigations as well as participant recruitment and sample collection for nationwide surveillances. My articles published in academic journals and my presentation at a scientific symposium prove my active engagement in scholarly activities. These experiences will enable me to contribute significantly to institutional research and supervision of student projects.\r\nAgain, over the years in clinical practice, I have garnered extensive laboratory experience in various laboratory science disciplines including; clinical chemistry, hematology, immunology, microbiology, pathology, blood banking, and molecular diagnostics. These hands-on bench experiences are relevant in linking theory to practice and equips me for teaching both classroom and laboratory courses.\r\nFinally, as a laboratory manager, my leadership experiences in overseeing and coordinating laboratory activities; organizing and supervising personnel and tasks; and implementing quality management systems; has equipped me with organizational and administrative skills that are important for curriculum development and administrative departmental activities.\r\nIn all, my educational background, supervisory and mentoring experience, scientific presentations, research involvement, publications, clinical practice, as well managerial and leadership skills, are a solid foundation for the position of a medical laboratory technology lecturer.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, chess games, football, and listening to music.', 'One month', NULL, 'Dr. Sylvester D. Dassah', 'Lecturer', 'Senior lecturer', 'Department of Biochemistry and forensic sciences\r\nUniversity of Technology and Applied Sciences, Navrongo, Ghana', '+233243005950', 'sddassah@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Dr. (Med) Kofi Asare-Ansah', 'Medial doctor', 'Medical superintendent', 'Bongo District Hospital, P.O. BOX 18, Bongo, UER.', '+233249746397', 'kodinsah@yahoo.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_763E4A4E_cv_6a138224478301.18308662.pdf', 'Elvis-Ayamga-CV.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '41.155.117.180', '2026-05-24 22:56:36', '2026-06-12 23:07:21', 'BTU_763E4A4E_photo_6a138224478344.89425459.jpg', 'Elvis-Ayamga-passport-pic.jpg'),
