(70, 'BTU-C293CF11', 15, 'Mr.', 'Essandoh', 'Emmanuel Ebo', 'essandohebo05@gmail.com', '+233243452338', 'GC-118-2047\r\nPost Office Box 16866 Accra North', 'AWOSHIE LASTSTOP ACCRA', 'Apam', 'Greater Accra', 'GHANAIAN', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Gha-712679497-6', '1989-02-07', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'university of cape coast', 5, NULL, NULL, 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'SOCCER', 'IMMEDITELY', 'NO PLEASE', 'Samuel Nimoh', 'Banker', 'Executive Customer Officer', 'POST OFFICE BOX 401\r\nKANESHIE', '0241730907', 'SAMUELNIMOH334@GMAIL.COM', 'DANIEL GYEEDU ESSANDOH', 'ACCOUNT MANAGER', 'SALES OFFICER', 'BOX 45', '0548274862', 'DANIELGYEEDU234@GMAIL.COM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_C293CF11_cv_6a14580c36ea90.56176547.pdf', 'EMMANUEL CV (1).pdf', 'pending', NULL, '41.155.42.151', '2026-05-25 14:09:16', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_C293CF11_photo_6a14580c36eaf0.59187373.jpg', 'WIN_20250812_10_17_56_Pro.jpg'),
(71, 'BTU-696A2530', 15, 'Mr.', 'Awaab', 'Emmanuel Ackalacha', 'emmanuelawaab@gmail.com', '+233245067241', 'P.Obox 30 Fomena Ashanti', 'Sandema', 'Sandema', 'Upper East', NULL, 'Christian', 'married', 'Rose Nsor', 'Enyresi Government Hospital', 'Jayden Awaab-6th January 2023\r\nJenil Awaab-20th June, 2025', NULL, 'GHA-002124698-2', '1987-03-22', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'University of Professional Studies- Accra', 11, 'Relevance by Role\r\n1. Branch/Sales Manager Sales and branch managers are experts at setting targets, managing budgets, and driving departmental revenue. University Application: In the university setting, this translates directly into managing institutional budgets, driving operational efficiency, and promoting academic programs or corporate partnerships. Relevant Skills: Performance tracking, risk management, client relations, resource allocation, and team motivation.\r\n2. Headmaster \r\nA headmaster (or school principal) operates as the chief administrator of an educational institution. University Application: This is the closest analog to an Assistant Registrar. It proves you understand educational policies, curriculum frameworks, student disciplinary processes, and faculty supervision. Relevant Skills: Academic administration, student records management, regulatory compliance, policy implementation, and handling grievances', 'Relevance by Role\r\n1. Branch/Sales Manager Sales and branch managers are experts at setting targets, managing budgets, and driving departmental revenue. University Application: In the university setting, this translates directly into managing institutional budgets, driving operational efficiency, and promoting academic programs or corporate partnerships. Relevant Skills: Performance tracking, risk management, client relations, resource allocation, and team motivation.\r\n2. Headmaster \r\nA headmaster (or school principal) operates as the chief administrator of an educational institution. University Application: This is the closest analog to an Assistant Registrar. It proves you understand educational policies, curriculum frameworks, student disciplinary processes, and faculty supervision. Relevant Skills: Academic administration, student records management, regulatory compliance, policy implementation, and handling grievances', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Volunteering: Shows empathy, leadership, and a commitment to community work. \r\nTeam Sports: Highlights collaboration, communication, and resilience. Creative Pursuits (Blogging, Photography): Demonstrates attention to detail and digital literacy. Endurance/Solo Sports: Reflects discipline, goal-setting, and personal drive. Strategy Games: Indicates problem-solving, logic, and analytical thinking', 'One Month', NULL, 'Evans Osei Bediako', 'Insurer', 'Branch Manager', 'National Insurance Commission- Cantonments', '0541082862', NULL, 'Prof. Jonathan Fletcher', 'Lecturer', 'Head of Education Department', 'University of Ghana', '0249907192', NULL, 'Prof. Stephen Adei', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'GIMPA', '0244316572', NULL, 'BTU_696A2530_cv_6a1461ec10da02.25176671.pdf', 'CV Glico Emmanuel A Awaab CV (1).pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.31.51', '2026-05-25 14:51:24', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_696A2530_photo_6a1461ec10da51.37087506.jpg', 'PASSPORT NOW.jpg'),
(72, 'BTU-2067187E', 15, 'Mr.', 'Nsobila', 'Charles', 'nsobilac68@gmail.com', '0548012623', 'Ampunyase D/A Junior High School,\r\nPost Office Box 4,\r\nAkrofuom-Adansi.', 'Vea', 'Vea', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christians', 'married', 'Joanita Ayimpoka Akolbila', 'C/O P. O. Box1277, Kumasi.', 'Rex Apusiyine Atorogo,  DOB: 19/11/2018\r\nThelma Ayinnongmah Atorogo,  DOB: 16/04/2021\r\nNeriah Ayinmaaliya Atorogo,  DOB: 28/04/2026', 'P0014249170', 'GHA-717134755-8', '1986-09-26', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'Akenten Appiah-Menka University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development', 7, NULL, 'My administrative competencies have been developed through varied institutional responsibilities over the years. As Acting Headteacher at Maurice Browne JHS and Nyariga-Doone Girls\' Primary School, I managed student admission and registration, maintained academic records, and coordinated staff and parental engagement. My internship at Bolgatanga Senior High School further exposed me to student data entry and examination administration functions central to any university registry. In addition, my service as financial secretary at St William\'s Chaplaincy, AAMUSTED, reflects my capacity for disciplined record management and institutional accountability.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading storybooks, watching documentary films, listening to current affairs, and news analysis.', 'With 1 or 2 weeks.', 'As a dedicated and results-oriented education professional with over a decade of experience in teaching and institutional administration under the Ghana Education Service. I managed student admission and registration, maintained academic records, and coordinated staff and parental engagement as an acting headteacher at Nyariga-Doone Girls\' Primary School. I am persuaded that these competencies, combined with my administrative background, make me a fitting candidate for this role.', 'Dr. Prince Gyimah', 'Lecturing', 'Senior Lecturer', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development,\r\nPost Office Box 1277,\r\nKumasi.', '+233 054 064 3517', 'pgyimah@aamusted.edu.gh', 'Dr. Patrick Nyaaba Ayambire', 'Lecturing', 'Lecturer', 'University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development,\r\nPost Office Box 1277,\r\nKumasi.', '+233 055 242 4305', 'pnayambire@aamusted.edu.gh', 'Mr. Eric Amponsah', 'Teaching', 'Headteacher', 'Ampunyase D/A Junior High School,\r\nPost Office Box 4,\r\nAkrofuom-Adansi.', '0246136287', 'ericowinsouls@gmail.com', 'BTU_2067187E_cv_6a147579846427.60119298.pdf', 'Charles_Nsobila_CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.232.147', '2026-05-25 16:14:49', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_2067187E_photo_6a147579846496.14331933.jpg', '966787.jpg'),
(73, 'BTU-2F38B51E', 9, 'Ms.', 'TABLIBA', 'PAULINA', 'linatabs1@gmail.com', '+233244296894', 'ZAMSE SENIOR HIGH/TECHNICAL SCHOOL\r\nP. O. BOX 203\r\nBOLGATANGA', 'BOLGATANGA', 'GOROGO', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'GODFRED YINZOR TABLIBA - 13/05/1995\r\nGABRIELLA TACKIE - 23/09/2015', 'P0031421970', 'GHA-727440377-5', '1978-08-27', 'female', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'AKENTEN APPIAH-MENKA UNIVERSITY OF SKILLS TRAINING AND ENTREPRENEURIAL DEVELOPMENT', 11, NULL, 'My teaching, research, and professional background are highly relevant to the position of Lecturer in the Department of Fashion Design and Textiles at a Technical University. I hold an MPhil in Fashion Design and Textiles, which has equipped me with advanced theoretical knowledge, practical skills, and research competence in the field of fashion and textile education.\r\nThrough my academic training, I have gained expertise in areas such as garment construction, textile studies, fashion illustration, pattern making, apparel production, fashion entrepreneurship, and contemporary fashion trends. My educational background has also strengthened my ability to conduct research, analyze industry developments, and apply innovative teaching methods that support technical and vocational education.\r\nIn terms of teaching relevance, I possess the ability to prepare lesson plans, deliver lectures effectively, supervise practical studio work, assess students’ performance, and guide students in project and research work. My training has prepared me to combine theory with practical applications, which is essential in technical university education.\r\nProfessionally, my knowledge and skills in fashion design and textiles enable me to contribute to curriculum development, skills training, and industry-oriented education that will help students meet the demands of the fashion and textile industry. I am also committed to mentoring students, promoting creativity and innovation, and contributing to academic research and community development.\r\nTherefore, my academic qualifications, research background, practical experience, and passion for teaching make me well suited for the position of Lecturer in a Technical University.', 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'SEWING, MODELLING, READING', 'WITH IMMEDIATE EFFECT', NULL, 'MR. EMMANUEL AKAGERI', 'TEACHING', 'ASSISTANT HEAD MASTER ACADEMIC', 'ZAMSE SENIOR HIGH/TECH. SCH. \r\nP. O. BOX 203', '0540834396', NULL, 'DR. DANIEL K. DANSO', 'LECTURER', 'LECTURER', 'AKENTEN APPIAH-MENKA UNIVERSITY OF SKILLS TRAINING AND ENTREPRENEURIAL DEVELOPMENT\r\nKUMASI', '0244851798', NULL, 'MR. CHRISTOPHER OPPONG', 'LECTURER', 'LECTURER', 'BOLGATANGA TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY\r\nP. O. BOX 767\r\nBOLGATANGA', '0244660905', NULL, 'BTU_2F38B51E_cv_6a14769c6da604.96313503.pdf', 'combinepdf (10).pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.253.161', '2026-05-25 16:19:40', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_2F38B51E_photo_6a14769c6da653.41347676.jpg', '20260525184526_001.jpg');
