(74, 'BTU-A2A383E1', 2, 'Dr.', 'David', 'Amankona', 'davidamankona@gmail.com', '0548648754', 'GD 063 2570\r\n16 Okro Link ,Ogbojo\r\nAccra', 'Accra', 'Wechiau', 'Upper West', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-727457576-4', '1989-07-26', 'male', 'PhD', 'Zhejiang Gongshang University', 0, '1.	Korankye, Benard; Yi, Kaigang ; Borah, Prasad; Kodua, Lois; Odai, Leslie; Amankona, David (2026) Explainable Co-Creation: A Generative AI Model of Guest Engagement and Experiential Value in Star-Rated Hotels. Journal of Hospitality and Tourism Insight. Emerald insight. DOI: 10.1108/JHTI-10-2025-1260 (SCOPUS Q1 ACCEPTED)\r\n\r\n2.	Korankye, Benard; Yi, Kaigang ; Borah, Prasad; Odai, Leslie; Kodua, Lois; Amankona David (2026). From Perceived ESG Knowledge to Sustainable Tourism Support Intentions: The Roles of ESG Authenticity and Destination Trust. Journal of Hospitality and Tourism Insight. Emerald insight. DOI: 10.1108/JHTI-12-2025-1452 (scopus Q1, ACCEPTED) \r\n \r\n3.	David Amankona, Chikwanda Kampamba, Bright Okyere Ofosu, William Agoke, Lois Tweneboa Kodua, Raphael Mmieh Kwakye (2026). Modelling the Relationship between Environmental Responsibility, Green Innovation and Enterprise Performance among  Ghanaian Firms. The role of Managerial Environmental Concerns. Journal of Innovation Management (Scopus Q3 ACCEPTED) \r\n\r\n4.	Amankona David, Kaigang Yi and Mmieh Kwakye Raphael (2025). Unravelling the nexus of corporate digital responsibility and business success: assessing the impact of digital innovation. Technology Analysis &amp; Strategic Management, 1–15.   \r\nhttps://doi.org/10.1080/09537325.2025.2566154 (Q2, SSCI)   \r\n   \r\n5.	Amankona David, Kaigang Yi, Evelyn Agba tackie, Lois Tweneboa Kodua, Leslie Afotey   Odai (2025). Responsible Digital Innovation and Innovation Performance in Ghana\'s HighTech Industry: The Mediating Roles of Digital Organizational Culture and Strategy, and the Moderating Role of Digital Literacy. SAGE Open, 15(2).    https://doi.org/10.1177/21582440251341256 (Q1, SSCI)   \r\n   \r\n6.	Korankye, Benard, Hao, Yunhong; Borah, Prasad; Iqbal, Shuja; Odai, Leslie; Amankona, David (2025). Harnessing Digital Transformation and ESG Performance for Innovation, Competitiveness, and Financial Success: Insights from European Multinationals.    Business Process Management Journal. DOI: https://doi.org/10.1108/BPMJ-12-2024-1215  (Q1, SSCI)   \r\n   \r\n7.	Amankona David, Kaigang Yi. and Kampamba, Chikwanda. (2024), &quot;Understanding digital social responsibility\'s impact on purchase intention: insights from consumer engagement, brand loyalty and Generation Y consumers&quot;, Management Matters, Vol.  \r\nahead-of-print No. ahead-of-print. https://doi.org/10.1108/MANM-03-2024-0015   \r\n   \r\n8.	Tackie, Evelyn Agba, Hao Chen, Isaac Ahakwa, Amankona David, and Samuel Atingabili. (2023) &quot;Drivers of food security in West Africa: Insight from heterogeneous panel data analysis on income-level classification.&quot; Environmental Science and Pollution Research: 1- 21. https://doi.org/10.1007/s11356-023-28548-z (Q1, SSCI)   \r\n   \r\n9.	Kodua, Lois Tweneboa, Yuchun Xiao, Nana Osae Adjei, Dennis Asante, Bright Okyere Ofosu, and Amankona David (2022) &quot;Barriers to green human resources management   (GHRM) implementation in developing countries. Evidence from Ghana.&quot; Journal of   Cleaner Production 340  130671. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jclepro.2022.130671 (Q1, SSCI)   \r\n   \r\n10.	Amankona David, Kweitsu Godson, Korankye Benjamin, Ebo Arthur Emmanuel. (2018 ) “Critical Analysis of Educational Finance in Ghana”. British Journal of Interdisciplinary Research © 2018 Open Archives Initiative | Volume 8| Issue 1 | Issn: 2308-3218    \r\n   \r\n11.	Danquah. Derrick Opoku, Amankona David, Adutwum Amo Seth, &amp; Bonney, Belinda.  (2018) “Evaluating the Concept of Organizational Culture: Power Distance ReModification as Tool for  Public Institution Progress in Ghana”. British Journal of Interdisciplinary Research © 2018 Open Archives Initiative | Volume 9| Issue 1 | ISSN: 2308-3218    \r\n   \r\n12.	Amankona, David (2018). Public Policy Making in Ghana: The Role of Politics and The Media. Journal of Developing Country Studies, ISSN 2224-607X (Paper) ISSN 2225-0565 (Online) Vol.8, No.10, 2018    \r\n   \r\n13.	Amankona David, Lois Tweneboa Kodua, Tobi Michael Ogunwemimo3 Governance in Higher Education: A Comparative Study on Ghana and China. Journal of Research on   \r\nHumanities and Social Sciences, ISSN 2224-5766 (Paper) ISSN 2225-0484 (Online) Vol.8, No.20, 2018   \r\n\r\n14.	Amankona, David, Adutwum. A &amp; Danquah, D.: Improving Public Sector Service Delivery in Ghana: The Application of Innovation and ICT. Public Policy and Administration Research, ISSN 2224-5731(Paper) ISSN 2225-0972(Online) Vol.8, No.7, 2018.', 'My educational qualifications, skills as a researcher, and work experience are well-suited to the job I am applying for. I have a PhD in Management Science (Business Administration) from Zhejiang Gongshang University, a Master’s Degree in Public Management from the University of Electronic Science and Technology of China, and a Bachelor’s Degree in Business Education from the University for Development Studies. My areas of research are corporate social responsibility, digital transformation, innovation, entrepreneurship, strategic management, and organizational development. My academic qualifications include publications in reputable SSCI and Scopus indexed journals such as Technology Analysis &amp; Strategic Management, SAGE Open, Business Process Management Journal, and the Journal of Cleaner Production. Moreover, my experiences as an adult literacy tutor, National Trainer for the Ghana Statistical Service, as well as participation in different international research projects have made me a better lecturer, trainer, mentor, and communicator. I have gained the capacity to effectively conduct lectures, supervise research work of students, participate in research collaboration, as well as assist in curriculum development and community engagement programs through my experiences in research and training', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'playing and watching football', '3 weeks', NULL, 'William Agoke', 'Academic', 'Lecturer', 'School of Education   \r\nUniversity for Development Studies, Ghana', '+233244804201', 'awilliam@uds.edu.gh', 'Yelley Abraham', 'Development consultant', 'Project Coordinator', 'Atebubu &amp;Wiase Forest Landscape Restoration Project.', '0249234100', 'yelleyabraham1@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_A2A383E1_cv_6a147e8fc02933.96346146.pdf', 'Curriculum vitae..pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.154.207', '2026-05-25 16:53:35', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_A2A383E1_photo_6a147e8fc02983.36069582.jpeg', 'Amankona.jpeg'),
