(86, 'BTU-C286410A', 3, 'Mr.', 'GUURE', 'AUGUSTINE MMI-ONI', 'guureaustin73@gmail.com', '0244806654', 'SG 32 SHEAGA \r\nTALENSI DISTRICT \r\nTONGO', 'SHEAGA', 'SHEAGA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', NULL, 'married', 'JEMAIMA AMANGA ADONGO', 'SG 32', 'ALDRIDGE YINTESOMMAH GUURE 24/09/2012\r\nAIMERIC NAMKUNNA GUURE 11/12/2015\r\nARIADNE MAHAMPAAMAN GUURE 24/08/2021', NULL, NULL, '1987-04-30', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF CAPE COAST', 5, NULL, 'My studies gives me a strong understanding of agricultural systems, sustainability, and food security, which are directly relevant to agricultural teaching and training.\r\n\r\nMy training in Public Policy and Management helps me explain how agricultural programs are planned, governed, funded, and implemented in real communities and institutions.\r\nMy academic background strengthens my ability to teach practical and interdisciplinary solutions, linking engineering, climate adaptation, rural development, and community livelihoods.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Research and entrepreneurship', 'In less than a month', NULL, 'Madam Abagnamah Fauzia Yakubu+233506750315', 'CIVIL SERVICE', 'Coordinator,  school feeding program Upper East', NULL, '0554893585', 'Abagnamahphauzy@gmail.com', 'Prof. Vida Nyagre Yakong', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Deen Nursing and Midwifery department', NULL, '0506750315', 'NyagreYakong@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_C286410A_cv_6a158f995a7c13.31041346.pdf', 'admin,+kss.v9i27.17116.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '41.204.44.81', '2026-05-26 12:18:33', '2026-06-12 23:23:47', 'BTU_C286410A_photo_6a158f995a7c75.10832889.jpeg', 'bb7228cb-3959-483b-9ea6-fa27115a1a32_0_watermark.jpeg'),
(87, 'BTU-4B2416E8', 14, 'Mr.', 'Anyedina', 'Stephen Akazigayire', 'sakazigayire@gmail.com', '+233542343622', 'Access bank bolga', 'Mirigu', 'Bolga', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'NA', 'P0031354920', 'GHA-722913759-7', '1995-03-30', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'KNust', 5, 'NA', 'My professional experience are highly relevant with the accountant position at Bolgatanga Technical University. \r\nAs a Chartered Accountant with an MSc in Accounting and Finance, which has equipped me with strong knowledge and practical skills in accounting, financial management, auditing, taxation, and reporting.\r\nProfessionally, I have worked with Access Bank for over four years, starting as a Cashier and currently serving as an Account Officer. Through these roles, I have gained extensive experience in financial record keeping, customer account management, cash handling, reconciliation, preparation of financial reports, and maintaining accuracy and integrity in financial operations. These experiences have strengthened my analytical, organizational, and communication skills.\r\n\r\nIn addition, I undertook a two-month attachment at the University for Development Studies (UDS), Navrongo Campus, where I gained exposure to institutional administrative and accounting procedures. This experience enhanced my understanding of working within an academic environment and improved my ability to adapt to university systems and professional standards.\r\n\r\nI believe my academic qualifications, professional accounting background, banking experience, and exposure to university administration make me well-suited for the accountant position at Bolgatanga Technical University.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Football and music', '2weeks', 'No please', 'Kahaar Alhassan Salifu', 'Banking', 'Branch manager', 'Access bank, Bolga', '0243070452', 'kahaar.Alhassan@accessbankplc.com', 'Abudu Adwuda', 'Education', 'Senior lecturer', 'BTU, bolga', '024 857 0730', 'abdawu