(94, 'BTU-05E95859', 14, 'Mr.', 'Masahudu', 'Abdul Jabat Biimi', 'jabatmasahudu@gmail.com', '0245683945', 'BESSFA community Bank PLC\r\nP. O. Box 160\r\nGaru-Upper East Region', 'Nakpanduri', 'Nakpanduri', 'North East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Hagar Likibarsua Sampson', 'Akakiya KG/Primary School-Bolgatanga', 'Cassie Timiyennu Biimi                   24th December, 2020\r\nGenius Tipiakyennu Biimi               10th May, 2023\r\nJared Kandifeiyennu Biimi              10th April, 2026', NULL, 'GHA-723694465-4', '1995-01-27', 'male', 'Professional Certificate', 'Institute of Chartered Accountants, Ghana', 3, NULL, 'My academic background, professional training, and practical experience have adequately prepared me for the role of Accountant at the Finance Directorate of Bolgatanga Technical University. I hold both a Master’s Degree and a Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting, together with professional accounting knowledge and strong ICT competencies, which are essential for effective financial administration in a tertiary institution.\r\n\r\nThrough my studies and professional development, I have gained sound knowledge in financial reporting, budgeting, auditing, taxation, cost management, and financial analysis. These areas are directly connected to the responsibilities of an accountant within a university setting, where accuracy, accountability, and compliance with financial regulations are highly important.\r\n\r\nMy educational and research experience has also strengthened my analytical and problem-solving abilities. I am able to examine financial records critically, prepare detailed reports, and support management with reliable financial information for decision-making. Working within an academic environment further requires collaboration, confidentiality, and professionalism, qualities I have developed through both my academic and professional engagements.\r\n\r\nIn terms of professional relevance, I have practical experience in handling accounting and financial management functions such as preparing financial statements, maintaining proper accounting records, processing payroll, reconciling accounts, monitoring budgets, and ensuring adherence to internal controls and financial procedures. These experiences have enhanced my ability to work efficiently and meet deadlines under minimal supervision.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, my ICT skills provide me with the ability to work effectively with accounting software, spreadsheets, and computerized financial systems. This is particularly important in modern university administration, where technology plays a significant role in financial reporting, data management, and operational efficiency.\r\n\r\nWith my academic qualifications, accounting knowledge, practical experience, and technological skills, I am confident in my ability to contribute positively to the efficient management of financial resources at the Finance Directorate of Bolgatanga Technical University.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Football', '1 month', NULL, 'Hayatudeen Awudu Ibrahim', 'Banking', 'Chief Executive Officer', 'BESSFA Community Bank PLC\r\nBox 160\r\nGaru-Upper East Region', '0242973741', 'awuduhayatudeen@yahoo.com', 'Ayaab Jacob Asaman', 'Banking', 'Internal Audit Manager', 'BESSFA Community Bank PLC\r\nBox 160\r\nGaru-Upper East Region', '0244038234', 'ayaabjacobasaman@gmail.com', 'Konlan D. Nicholas', 'Agriculturelist', 'Sourcing Lead', 'Cargill Ghana\r\nTema \r\nFree zones Enclave', '0556491138', NULL, 'BTU_05E95859_cv_6a15d18a5c5341.00710476.pdf', 'CV_ABDUL JABAT BIIMI MASAHUDU.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '74.244.119.224', '2026-05-26 16:59:54', '2026-05-26 16:59:54', 'BTU_05E95859_photo_6a15d18a5c5386.97389729.jpeg', 'Abdul Jabat Biimi Masahudu.jpeg'),
(95, 'BTU-DC88BC1F', 2, 'Mr.', 'Awaafo', 'Ignatius Akubire', 'iakubireawaafo@gmail.com', '+233242387740', 'ST\'s Peter and Paul Catholic Church,\r\nPost Office Box E/R 119,\r\nTamale.', 'Tamale', 'Bolgatanga', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'Christianiaty', 'married', 'Hannah Atinga', 'ST&#039;s Peter and Paul Catholic Church, Post Office Box E/R 119, Tamale.', 'Kapporeth Amokama Akubire Awaafo - 16th September 2023\r\nCleopatra Asumbuno Akubire Awaafo - 3rd September 2025', 'P000389181X', 'GHA-714851638-5', '1984-02-20', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Ghana, Legon – Accra, Ghana', 11, NULL, 'My seventeen years of teaching English related subjects at the second cycle level and English and Communication related courses at the tertiary level would be of enormous relevance to the position applied for.\r\n\r\nMy research interest is in Discourse Communication, Media Communication, African Literature, African Traditions and Cultures, Language and Literature etc.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading\r\nMusic &amp; Dance\r\nFootball\r\nSocialization', 'Two (2) weeks', 'Apart from being an academic staff, I could also serve the university in its various public speaking activities such as Master of Ceremonies in major events/occasions.', 'Prof. Edward Salifu Mahama', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Former Dean of the Faculty of Communications and Cultural Studies, University for Development Studie', 'Saints Peter and Paul Parish, \r\nPost Office Box E/R 119,\r\nTamale.', '+233243821111', 'edisalifu@yahoo.co.uk', 'Haruna Rashid', 'Teacher', 'Head of Languages Department, Business Senior High School, Tamale', 'Business Senior High School,\r\nPost Office Box 261,\r\nTamale', '+233243550450', 'wahshfusion@gmail.com', 'Dr. Kwabena Opoku-Agyemang', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer - Department of English, University of Ghana, Legon, Accra, Ghana', 'University of Ghana, Legon, \r\nAccra, Ghana.', '+233561564771', 'kwabena.oa@gmail.com', 'BTU_DC88BC1F_cv_6a15eb322d6d92.22502636.pdf', 'Ignatius A. Awaafo\'s CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '41.155.1.210', '2026-05-26 18:49:22', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_DC88BC1F_photo_6a15eb322d6dd8.86278898.jpg', 'Ignatius Akubire Awaafo Picture.jpg'),
(96, 'BTU-4F58E27D', 2, 'Mr.', 'ADAM', 'CARLOS ABDUL-LATIF', 'carloslatifu@gmail.com', '+233243111142', 'C/o ST. VICTOR\'S MAJOR SEMINARY P.O. BOX 149 TAMALE', 'MALSHEGU, TAMALE', 'MALSHEGU', 'Northern', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'married', 'DOREEN AYORMALE GULBI', 'JSQ 62 TANZUI BOLGATANGA', 'PHILIP MALTITI ADAM 07-07-2017\r\nJEWELLE PUMAYA ADAM 19-08-2020\r\nTRICIA NEESIM ADAM 23-08-2024', 'P0022582827', 'GHA-714488778-2', '1986-12-06', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF GHANA', 11, NULL, 'Years of teaching communication skills at UPSA and Tamale Technical University constitute direct and substantial preparation for teaching liberal studies. The experience provides pedagogical versatility, deep contextual knowledge of Ghanaian and African communication landscapes, and a practiced ability to integrate skills-based instruction with critical intellectual inquiry. Whether facilitating discussions on African political thought or developing students\' academic writing, this background offers both the theoretical grounding and practical expertise that liberal studies education requires.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'My hobbies include: swimming, watching and playing soccer and hanging out with family and friends.', '2 weeks', NULL, 'DR ISSAHAKA FUSEINI', 'LECTURER', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'UNIVERSITY OF GHANA \r\nADULT EDUCATION DEPARTMENT', '0242604330', 'isfuseini@ug.edu.gh', 'J.B Amissah-Arthur', 'LECTURER', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH\r\nUNIVERSITY OF GHANA', '+233 (0)243422551', 'jbamissah-arthur@ug.edu.gh', 'Dr Fatimata Iddrisu Abu', 'LECTURER', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'DEPARTMENT OF LANGUAGES AND INTERNATIONAL RELATIONS\r\nTAMALE TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY', '0244775854', 'ifatima@tatu.edu.gh', 'BTU_4F58E27D_cv_6a1612678ff9a1.49414791.pdf', 'Carlos_CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.41.96', '2026-05-26 21:36:39', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_4F58E27D_photo_6a1612678ffa10.63902248.jpeg', 'CARL PS PIC.jpeg'),
(97, 'BTU-F9C37C12', 3, 'Mr.', 'MOHAMMED', 'ABDALLAH AKURUBILA', 'maakurubila@gmail.com', '+233244629414', 'Box 3, c/o MoFA\r\nIssa - Wa', 'Bolgatanga', 'Bolgatanga', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'ISLAM', 'married', 'AKUBIRE FULERA', 'S. 154, TANZUI', 'ABDALLAH HUSNA 18-JANUARY-2018\r\nABDALLAH FATHIA   6-MARCH-2026', 'P0012275034', 'GHA-716026137-5', '1986-07-25', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF GHANA', 7, 'Agro-forestry technology adoption and its effect on farmers\' crop productivity in the Upper East Region of Ghana - MPhil. Thesis.', '1. My multidisciplinary background in agribusiness, project management, extension services, and community development would add value to the university through innovative teaching, practical research contributions, institutional growth, and impactful community engagement initiatives.\r\n\r\n2. My blend of academic knowledge and practical field experience positions me to deliver teaching that is both theoretical and industry-oriented, enabling students to connect classroom concepts with real-world realities.\r\n\r\n3. My exposure to research, data collection, supervision, and project implementation demonstrates strong analytical and investigative capacity, which is essential for quality academic research, publication, and student research supervision.\r\n\r\n4. My experience in training, stakeholder engagement, and community-based development reflects excellent communication and mentorship abilities, making me capable of guiding, motivating, and nurturing students academically and professionally.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '1. Research and academic writing\r\n2. Reading scholarly journals and contemporary literature\r\n3. Public speaking and academic presentations\r\n4. Mentoring and student development activities\r\n5. Digital learning through the use of AI and educational technology exploration', 'IMMEDIATELY', 'PLEASE, I HAVE TAKEN A KEEN INTEREST IN PURSUING A PHD EDUCATION IN AGRIBUSINESS. AS A RESULT, I HAVE APPLIED TO THE UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES, NYANKPALA CAMPUS, AWAITING ADMISSION AND COMMENCEMENT OF SAME. I ASSURE THE UNIVERSITY OF PRODUCING A PHD WITHIN 4 ACADEMIC YEARS FROM MY FIRST YEAR OF ENGAGEMENT IF ALLOWED TO JOIN YOUR ESTEEMED UNIVERSITY.', 'PROFESSOR AWAL ABDUL-RAHAMAN', 'UNIVERSITY LECTURER', 'SENIOR LECTURER,', 'DEPARTMENT OF AGRIBUSINESS, FACULTY OF AGRICULTURE, FOOD AND CONSUMER SCIENCES\r\nP.O.BOX, TL 1882, UDS, NYANKPALA CAMPUS - TAMALE', '0204024398', 'awalrahaman@uds.edu.gh', 'PROFESSOR SYLVESTER AYAMBILA', 'UNIVERSITY LECTURER', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'DEPARTMENT OF AGRIBUSINESS, FACULTY OF AGRICULTURE, FOOD AND CONSUMER SCIENCES\r\nP.O.BOX, TL 1882, UDS, NYANKPALA CAMPUS - TAMALE', '0244547795', 'slusor@yahoo.com', 'DR. KANYIRI YAKUBU', 'STATISTICIAN', 'BONO REGIONAL STATISTICIAN', 'GHANA STATISTICAL SERVICE OFFICE, BONO REGION\r\nP.O.BOX, 201, SUNYANI', '0243786466', 'kd_yak@yahoo.com', 'BTU_F9C37C12_cv_6a16515a73cf69.67745077.pdf', 'MOHAMMED ABDALLAH AKURUBILA\'S RESUME..pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.239.49', '2026-05-27 02:05:14', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_F9C37C12_photo_6a16515a73cfb9.27832622.jpg', 'PassPort Picture.jpg'),
(98, 'BTU-AC2C65A4', 5, 'Mr.', 'AYAANE', 'AYURIZOYA EDWARD', 'edwardayaane1@gnail.com', '0242351038', 'Bolgatanga Technical Institute. \r\nPost office box 295, Bolgatanga \r\nUpper East Region', 'DOBA NAVRONGO', 'DOBA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHARISTIAN', 'married', 'OPHELIA AZUMAH AKOLGO', 'Bolgatanga Technical Institute.  Post office box 295, Bolgatanga  Upper East Region', '1.Fortune Awinsune Ayaane- 9/6/2005\r\n2. Prosper Atayire Ayaane-24/6/2008\r\n3.Fabiana Awinloya Ayaane-20/1/2014\r\n4. Abednego Awingura Ayaane-15/8/2019', NULL, 'GHA-715614570-8', '1981-05-25', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'KNUST', 11, 'a.	Design and construction of a Remote Fuel Level Monitory System.\r\nb.	Charaterization and Impact of Haramatant on Performance Solar Power Plants in Northern Ghana\r\nThese papers are under review for publications', 'Dynamic and results-driven energy professional with over 20 years of progressive experience in teaching, electrical engineering, and energy management. Currently pursuing a PhD in Sustainable Energy Engineering Management, with strong academic and practical background in electrical engineering technology, energy efficiency, sustainable energy systems, and technical education. Skilled in energy auditing, ISO 50001 implementation, and integrating behavioural economics into energy consumption analysis. Passionate about advancing energy efficiency policies and building capacity in Ghana and beyond My teaching, research, and professional experience are highly relevant to the post being applied for, particularly in Renewable and Sustainable Energy Technologies, Electrical and Electronic Engineering, Energy Efficiency in Electrical Systems, Technical Education in Emerging Economies, and the Integration of Practical Skills in Engineering Curricula.\r\n\r\nI have strong expertise in Basic Electrical Installation and Maintenance, where I delivered core training in residential and commercial wiring, circuit protection, earthing systems, fault diagnosis, and compliance with national electrical codes, supported by extensive laboratory practice and real-world project implementation. This has provided students with strong industry-relevant competencies.\r\n\r\nMy background in Electrical Circuit Theory and Analysis includes teaching AC/DC circuit principles, network theorems, and electrical measurements, forming a solid foundation for understanding advanced electrical and electronic systems. In Electrical Machines and Drives, I trained students in the operation, testing, maintenance, and application of transformers, generators, and AC/DC motors used in industrial and energy systems.\r\n\r\nThrough my role in Electrical Engineering Technology education and departmental leadership, I have also contributed to curriculum development, supervision of large student populations, staff coordination, and the integration of hands-on practical training into academic programs. This experience strongly aligns with the goals of advancing technical education, improving energy efficiency practices, and supporting sustainable engineering development in emerging economies.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '•	Research in Electrical Engineering: Passionate about exploring innovations in electrical systems, renewable energy, and power distribution technologies.\r\n•	Programming: Interested in software development and automation, with experience in basic coding and simulation tools related to engineering.\r\n•	Football Officiating: Former certified soccer referee and current match commissioner, with a strong interest in sports organization, rules enforcement, and fair play.', 'I will be able to assume appointment within one month of receiving official notification, to allow f', 'I bring extensive experience in Electrical Engineering Technology education, combining strong theoretical knowledge with hands-on practical training. Over the years, I have developed and delivered competency-based instruction that bridges the gap between classroom learning and industry practice.\r\n\r\nI have successfully supervised large student populations and academic staff, ensuring effective teaching delivery, discipline, and quality assurance in technical education. I am also committed to continuous improvement in engineering education, particularly through the integration of practical skills, innovation, and emerging technologies such as renewable and sustainable energy systems.\r\n\r\nI am highly motivated, adaptable, and committed to contributing to academic excellence, research development, and the training of industry-ready graduates in engineering and technology.', 'Zackary Yorose', 'Teaching', '(The Principal)', 'Bolgatanga Technical Institute. \r\nPost office box 295, Bolgatanga \r\nUpper East Region', 'Mobile No.+233(0)55 ', 'Email: botech.1985@yahoo.com', 'Thomas Adiyure Azuliya', 'Teaching', 'Deputy Director, Planning', 'District Education Office \r\nPost Office Box 224 Zuarungu', '+233(0)556650267', 'aadiyure@gmail.com', 'Benjamin Batinge', '(Lecturer)', '(Lecturer)', 'University of Energy and Natural Resources Sunyani, Ahafo Region', '233(0)246077782', 'benjamin.batinge@uenr.edu.gh', 'BTU_AC2C65A4_cv_6a168e47d153d3.55931274.pdf', 'AKATSICV 2.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.250.68', '2026-05-27 06:25:11', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_AC2C65A4_photo_6a168e47d15439.96702707.jpg', 'GO PICTURE.jpg'),
