(100, 'BTU-CA057B8F', 6, 'Mr.', 'Anak', 'Emmanuel Awenboro', 'anakemmanuel100@gmail.com', '+233209925177', 'CTM\r\nCABESA\r\nKNUST-Kumasi', 'Sandema', 'Kobdema, Azuelie Streets, Sandema', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-724737235-0', '1994-08-18', 'male', 'Other', 'St. John Boscos College of Education Navrongo', 11, 'RINENG-D-26-07032R1\r\nFROM SOIL TO STRUCTURE: A SYSTEMATIC REVIEW OF BAMBOO-REINFORCED EARTH COMPOSITES FOR SUSTAINABLE BUILDING\r\nResults in Engineering\r\nAnak, E.A., Acquah, G.K.K., Afful, A.E., Owoahene, A.M., Asare, S.A. and Kwaku, W. (2025) \r\nA bibliometric analysis of laminated bamboo research in construction. In: Owusu-Manu, D., \r\nAdesi, M. and Donkor-Hyiaman, K. A. (Eds) Proceedings of the 2nd International Conference \r\non Environment, Social, Governance and Sustainable Development of Africa (ICESDA-2025), \r\n23-24 October 2025, GIMPA Greenhill Campus, pp. 139 - 155. \r\nAcheampong, M. O., Kojo Kumi Acquah, G., Essanowa Afful, A., Anak, E.A., Awinbono \r\nAsaah, S., Wireko, K., Afi Nanor, D., &amp; Maalu, E. (2025). Financial Capacity Needs of Built \r\nProfessionals in Delivering Environmentally Sustainable Buildings (ESBs) in Ghana.', 'My KNUST Building Technology training enables me to teach all listed subjects, including Construction technology, Soils, Woodwork, Technical Drawing, Mathematics, Measurement, and Contract Law. My PhD research on bamboo-reinforced clay composites supports sustainable materials research and laboratory characterisation. My publications (ICESDA-2025, Results in Engineering) and peer review experience demonstrate research competence. I am ready to deliver tutorials, supervise projects, ensure workshop safety, and coordinate postgraduate research.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Model building (scales or structures)\r\nReading construction journals \r\nPhotography of buildings/structures', 'Immediately', 'I can assist the department in establishing a sustainable construction materials laboratory and developing industry partnerships for student internships.', 'Joshua Ayarkwa', 'Lecturer', 'Professor, Department of Construction Technology and Management', 'CTM\r\nCABESA\r\nKNUST-Kumasi', '+233246010870', 'ayarkwajosh@yahoo.com', 'Clement Apaak', 'Politics', 'Deputy Minister of Education', 'The Honourable Deputy Minister of Education\r\nMinistry of Education\r\nAccra', '+233200117620', 'godwinkkacquah@gmail.com', 'Godwin Kojo Kumi Acquah', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer, Department of Construction Technology and Management', 'CTM\r\nCABESA\r\nKNUST-Kumasi', '+233243880444', 'godwinkkacquah@gmail.com', 'BTU_CA057B8F_cv_6a16cf6ceed147.12842330.pdf', 'BTU Application.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.234.104', '2026-05-27 11:03:08', '2026-05-27 11:03:08', 'BTU_CA057B8F_photo_6a16cf6ceed1a4.13209430.jpeg', 'EMMANUEL PASSPORT PICTURE.jpeg'),
