(105, 'BTU-BE8AFB18', 9, 'Mr.', 'ACHEAMPONG', 'ISAAC ANWTI', 'ikeachie@yahoo.com', '+233247945862', '183, Techiman - Bono East', 'TECHIMAN', 'TECHIMAN', 'Bono East', 'Ghana', 'Christian', 'married', 'Portia Birago EFFAH', '183, Techiman - Bono East', 'MIKAELSON-SYREESE DARKO JUNIOR OWOAHENE ACHEAMPONG—23RD AUGUST, 2025', 'P0019035276', 'GHA-715472563-4', '1989-10-13', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'KNUST', 1, 'Boateng, S., Tawiah, B., &amp; Acheampong, I. A. (2025). Envisioning AI-Powered Future of African Print Designs - A Systematic Review of Opportunities and Challenges. Fashion and Textiles Review, 6, 333-352. https://doi.org/10.35738/ftr.v6.2025.17', 'My teaching experience is highly relevant to the post I am applying for, as it has equipped me with strong instructional, classroom management, communication, and organizational skills. I taught Creative Arts and Design for four years, which provided me with extensive experience in creative instruction, learner engagement, and student development. I am currently a Career Technology tutor and a class teacher, where I continue to support students academically and personally. In addition, my involvement in the preparation and typing of monthly and end-of-term examinations has strengthened my administrative, record-keeping, and attention-to-detail skills, which are valuable for this position.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, Research, Listening to Music', '2 weeks', 'As a Senior House Master, I have played a key role in the holistic development of students by providing guidance and mentorship both inside and outside the classroom. I supported students academically by encouraging discipline and effective study habits, while also mentoring them spiritually and morally to promote responsible behaviour and strong character formation. Through this role, I developed strong leadership, counselling, and interpersonal skills, as well as the ability to manage student welfare and maintain a positive and disciplined residential environment.', 'Prof. Ebenezer Kofi Howard', 'Professor / Lecturer', 'Vice Dean - Faculty of Art', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology\r\nPrivate Mail Bag (PMB), University Post Office\r\nKumasi, Ghana', '+233 24 476 7969', 'billhowardgh@yahoomail.com', 'Dr. Afua Akomaa Danso', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology\r\nPrivate Mail Bag (PMB), University Post Office\r\nKumasi, Ghana', '+233 20 712 0379', 'heartdanso@rocketmail.com', 'Mr. David Gyambibi Acheampong', 'Administrator', 'Assistant Headmaster', 'P.O. Box 183\r\nTechiman\r\nBono East', '+233 20 851 5273', 'kofiachie@yahoo.com', 'BTU_BE8AFB18_cv_6a16dd823cbee2.73506291.pdf', 'APPLICATION LETTER.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '179.64.71.152', '2026-05-27 12:03:14', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_BE8AFB18_photo_6a16dd823cbf47.21281346.jpg', 'IMG-20260209-WA0065.jpg'),
