(114, 'BTU-CFE1AA03', 5, 'Mr.', 'AGUMA', 'SAMUEL', 'agumosamuel8@gmail.com', '+233246410981', 'P.O. BOX 255,\r\nBOLGATANGA', 'BOLGATANGA', 'SUMBRUNGU', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', NULL, 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'P0053227271', 'GHA-722633870-2', '1996-10-15', 'male', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'BOLGATANGA TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY', 5, NULL, NULL, 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING\r\nSURFING THE INTERNET\r\nWATCHING SOCCER\r\nDOING RESEARCH', 'WITH IMMEDIATE EFFECT', NULL, 'Dr Gyaang Raymond', 'TEACHING', 'Head of Department Electrical &amp; Electronic Engineering', 'Bolgatanga Technical University\r\nP. O. Box 767\r\nBolga', '0555877338', 'gyaangraymond@outlook.com', 'Mr. Samuel Dodobatia Wetajega', 'TEACHING', 'LECTURER', 'Bolgatanga Technical University\r\nP. O. Box 767\r\nBolga', '0247563952', 'swetajega@bolgatu.edu.gh', 'Mr. Nabzoh Charles Alafi', 'LECTURER', 'LECTURER', 'Bolgatanga Technical University\r\nP. O. Box 767\r\nBolga', '0249049040', 'nabzohcharles12@gmail.com', 'BTU_CFE1AA03_cv_6a17111b20c130.53023353.pdf', 'samuel final   cv.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '179.64.71.151', '2026-05-27 15:43:23', '2026-06-12 23:43:05', 'BTU_CFE1AA03_photo_6a17111b20c179.80534818.jpg', 'passpoiujddsa.jpg'),
(115, 'BTU-E904FFCE', 15, 'Mr.', 'YUONI', 'BANYE KING NESTOR', 'yuoninestor439@gmail.com', '+233248304385', 'QUEEN OF PEACE SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL\r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 27,\r\nNADOWLI\r\nUPPER WEST REGION', 'WA', 'NADOWLI', 'Upper West', 'GHANAIAN', 'CATHOLIC', 'married', 'RUTH PELPUO', 'XW-0275-2664', 'YUONI PALMIRA 24/03/2013\r\nYUONI PAMELLA 16/06/2026\r\nYUONI PANTAENUS 26/05/2019', 'P0009974903', 'GHA-715305229-4', '1987-02-26', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION, WINNEBA', 11, 'Yet to be published', 'My teaching, research, and professional experiences are highly relevant to the position of Assistant Registrar/Registry because they have equipped me with strong administrative, communication, organizational, leadership, and records management skills needed for effective university administration.\r\nWith over 15 years of experience in the education sector, I have served in various capacities including teacher, facilitator, coordinator, and examiner. These roles have enabled me to develop excellent interpersonal relations, student management abilities, teamwork, and problem-solving skills which are essential in registry operations. My experience in coordinating academic activities, preparing reports, maintaining records, and ensuring compliance with institutional procedures has prepared me to effectively support the smooth administration of academic and administrative functions within the institution.\r\nIn addition, my academic background in Educational Administration and Management at both M.Ed and MPhil levels, coupled with my ongoing PhD studies, has provided me with in-depth knowledge in educational leadership, policy implementation, planning, supervision, and institutional management. My research experience has also strengthened my analytical, documentation, and data management skills, which are important in handling admissions, examinations, student records, staff documentation, and other registry responsibilities.\r\nAs an Assistant Registrar, I would use my experience and expertise to promote efficiency, professionalism, confidentiality, and effective service delivery within the institution. I would contribute to the implementation of institutional policies, support academic planning and coordination, improve records management systems, and ensure timely communication between management, staff, and students. I am also committed to teamwork, integrity, and continuous improvement to help advance the vision and mission of the institution.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'My hobbies include reading academic and leadership materials, conducting educational research, mentoring students, writing and reviewing academic works, participating in educational seminars and workshops, and engaging in community and school development activities. I also enjoy learning about educational policies, curriculum development, and the use of technology in teaching and administration and listening to music.', 'IMMEDIATELY', 'I am a hardworking, disciplined, and highly motivated education professional who is committed to excellence, integrity, and continuous learning. With extensive experience in teaching, educational administration, research, and leadership, I possess strong organizational, communication, and interpersonal skills that enable me to work effectively with diverse groups of people.\r\nI am currently pursuing a PhD in Education to further enhance my professional competence and contribute meaningfully to academic and institutional development. I am passionate about promoting quality education, effective administration, and efficient service delivery. I am confident that my experience, commitment, and willingness to learn will enable me to make a positive contribution to the growth and success of the institution.', 'TANIBE SONDONMO PHILIP', 'TEACHING,', 'ASSISTANT HEADMASTER (ACADENMIC)', 'QUEEN OF PEACE SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL \r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 27\r\nNADOWLI\r\nUPPER WEST REGION', '0243821664', 'philiptanibe3@gmail.com', 'PROF. KUSI HINNEH', 'LECTURER', 'DEAN OF POSTGRADUATE STUDIES', 'Dean of Postgraduate Studies \r\nDepartment of Educational Management and Administration \r\nUniversity of Education, Winneba', '+233 541 545 559 / 0', 'hinnehkusi@yahoo.com', 'DR. JUDITH BAMPO', 'LECTURER', 'HEAD OF DEPARTMENT', 'Head of Department \r\nDepartment of Educational Management and Administration \r\nUniversity of Education, Winneba', '+233 546 449 573', 'judith.atram@yahoo.com', 'BTU_E904FFCE_cv_6a171512447142.65111625.pdf', 'Nestor Yuoni cv 2026.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.119.251', '2026-05-27 16:00:18', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_E904FFCE_photo_6a1715124471a4.15312292.jpg', 'NESTOR.jpg'),
(116, 'BTU-0C77213D', 2, 'Mr.', 'Narimah', 'Emmanuel Ali', 'ealinarimah.ing@gmail.com', '+233245083172', 'Box KD 417, Kanda-Accra', 'Tamale', 'Tumu', 'Upper West', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, '&quot;N/A', 'P0045989435', 'GHA-713385334-7', '1990-03-31', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology', 11, 'N/A', 'My academic background, research focus, and extensive professional experience strongly align with the position of Lecturer in the Agricultural Engineering Department, particularly in Irrigation Technology Engineering. Although I do not have formal university teaching experience, my professional roles have consistently involved technical training, farmer education, mentorship, stakeholder capacity building, and practical field demonstrations, which have equipped me with strong teaching and facilitation abilities.\r\nI hold a BSc in Agriculture Technology with specialization in Mechanization and Irrigation Technology and an MPhil in Soil and Water Engineering from Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST). I am also currently pursuing a PhD in Soil and Water Engineering. My academic training has provided me with strong theoretical and practical knowledge in irrigation engineering, hydrology, water resources management, soil-water relationships, and climate-resilient agricultural systems.\r\nMy undergraduate thesis, titled “Prospects and Constraints of Small-Scale Irrigation in Naaga in the Kasena Nankana Municipality of the Upper East Region,” focused on the opportunities and challenges associated with smallholder irrigation development in northern Ghana. This research deepened my understanding of irrigation adoption, water management constraints, farmer livelihoods, and sustainable irrigation practices within rural agricultural systems.\r\nIn addition, my MPhil research on “Assessment of Catchment Runoff into the Kpong Reservoir in Ghana from 1986 to 2010” strengthened my expertise in hydrological assessment, watershed management, climate variability analysis, runoff estimation, and water resource sustainability. This research background is highly relevant to teaching and research in irrigation engineering and water resources management.\r\nProfessionally, I have accumulated over ten years of experience working in irrigation, water resources management, WASH, and climate-smart agriculture across Ghana. In my current role with Catholic Relief Services (CRS), I led the technical design and implementation support for 57 small-scale irrigation systems across 18 districts, improving water-use efficiency and dry-season agricultural production for over 1,000 smallholder farmers. This experience has strengthened my applied knowledge in irrigation system planning, productive water use, climate-smart agriculture, and engineering problem-solving.\r\nAlthough my work has been largely field-based, it has involved substantial teaching and knowledge-transfer responsibilities. I have regularly facilitated farmer trainings, delivered technical demonstrations, developed training materials, and provided mentorship to field officers, community groups, and stakeholders on irrigation management, climate-smart agriculture, soil moisture conservation, and sustainable water use practices. During my time with the Ga West Municipal Assembly, I trained farmers in irrigation management, conservation agriculture, and regenerative agricultural practices. Similarly, at the Ghana Irrigation Development Authority (GIDA), I supported students and researchers during field trials and demonstration activities while also training farmers on irrigation scheduling, erosion control, and water management. \r\nThese experiences have enabled me to develop strong communication, facilitation, and mentoring skills that are directly transferable to university teaching, student supervision, practical demonstrations, and academic research support. My combination of academic preparation, research experience, and hands-on professional exposure positions me well to contribute meaningfully to teaching, research, and extension activities within the Agricultural Engineering Department, especially in the field of Irrigation Technology Engineering.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, watching football and history documentaries.', '1 month', 'N/A', 'Mr. Festus Barfi Fofie', 'Development worker', 'Program Director, Water Sanitation and Hygiene', 'Catholic Relief Services, Tamale', '+233546661797', 'festus.fofie@crs.org', 'Mr. Edward Akunyagra', 'Development worker', 'Program Director, Agriculture Livelihood and Landscapes', 'Catholic Relief Services, Tamale', '+233548992869', 'edward.akunyagra@crs.org', 'Rev. Prof Saa Dittoh', 'Professor', 'Adjunct Professor', 'West African Centre of Excellence for Water, Irrigation and Sustainable Agriculture (WACWISA), Nyankpala.', '+233244296612', 'saaditt@gmail.com', 'BTU_0C77213D_cv_6a171e41743301.83223976.pdf', 'Emmanuel Ali Narimah_CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.49.79', '2026-05-27 16:39:29', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_0C77213D_photo_6a171e41743353.23153463.jpg', 'passport.jpg'),
