(121, 'BTU-2101A5EC', 8, 'Mr.', 'ESSEL', 'ISAAC KOJO', 'esselkojoisaac@gmail.com', '+233245323711', 'C/O DR ELISHA ARMAH CAPE COAST TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY, P.O BOX DL 50, CAPE COAST', 'AMOSIMA', 'AMOSIMA', 'Central', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-718993239-9', '1992-07-10', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION, WINNEBA', 3, 'Published Work \r\nEssel, I. K., Omane-Adjekum, C., Mbilla, S. A. E., &amp; Abdulai, E. (2024). Disaggregated Environmental Taxes on Energy Intensity: A Global Perspective. In Modern Concepts and Practices of Climate Finance (pp. 363-384). IGI Global. \r\nManuscripts Under Review \r\n• 	Enhancing Environmental Sustainability through Aggregated and Disaggregated Environment Taxes on Energy Intensity. A Global Perspective.', 'My teaching, research, and professional experiences are highly relevant to the Accounting and Finance Department as a Lecturer. I possess strong academic and practical knowledge in Accounting, Finance, Internal Auditing, Financial Analysis, Accounting Information Systems, and Business Computing.\r\n\r\nI have experience assisting in the teaching of courses such as Principles of Accounting, Cost Accounting, Financial Analysis, Spreadsheet Accounting, Accounting Information Systems, Database Management Systems, and Microsoft Office Applications. I also have practical experience in teaching and using accounting software such as Tally Prime, Manager, and QuickBooks for financial reporting, bookkeeping, payroll administration, and computerized accounting practices.\r\n\r\nProfessionally, I have worked as a Finance Officer, Account Officer, and Acting Manager, where I gained practical exposure in financial reporting, budgeting, payroll administration, internal auditing, internal controls, and operational management. These experiences enable me to effectively combine theoretical knowledge with practical industry applications in teaching.\r\n\r\nIn addition, my research interests in Environmental Accounting, Sustainability Reporting, Financial Analysis, and Data Analytics demonstrate my commitment to academic research and professional development, positioning me to contribute effectively to teaching, research, and academic advancement within the department.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Research and data analysis', '1 Month', NULL, 'Dr. Eugene Simon Akumbo Mbilla', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'University of Education, Winneba\r\nP. O. Box 25,\r\nWinneba, Ghana', '+233245484852', 'saembilla@uew.edu.gh', 'Dr. Elisha D’ Archimedes Armah', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Cape Coast Technical University      \r\nP.O BOX DL 50, Cape Coast  \r\nTelephone:', '+233244939990', 'E-mail: edarmah@cctu.edu.gh', 'Dr. Enoch Adjei Frimpong', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Cape Coast Technical University     \r\nP.O.BOX DL 50, Cape Coast', '+233594382207', 'enoch.frimpong@cctu.edu.gh', 'BTU_2101A5EC_cv_6a17643301a547.65177396.pdf', 'ISAAC KOJO ESSEL CV 2025 - LECTURER.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '41.155.58.201', '2026-05-27 21:37:55', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_2101A5EC_photo_6a17643301a594.89204264.jpeg', 'SIR IKE 0245323711.JPG.jpeg'),
