(141, 'BTU-10EA051B', 15, 'Mr.', 'Azinim', 'Maurice Abugr-Win', 'azinimm@gmail.com', '+233244871867', 'C/o P.O. Box 158, Bolgatanga', 'Bolgatanga', 'Bawku-Nyorugu', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'J019210200058', 'GHA7153825827', '1992-10-20', 'male', 'Professional Certificate', 'Ghana Institute of Planning', 7, 'Adams, A., Arhin, J., Agbeko, F. M., Azinim, M., Balaara, B. &amp; Oduro, F. (2018). District Medium-Term Development Plan for the West Akim Municipality, E/R. Unpublished Master’s Project, Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology, Department of Planning, Kumasi.\r\nAzinim, M. (2018). Social Protection and Poverty Alleviation: A Case of the Ghana Social Opportunities Project (GSOP) in the Talensi District. Unpublished Master’s Thesis, Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology, Department of Planning, Kumasi.  \r\nAzinim, M. A., Peprah, C. &amp; Agyemang-Duah, W. (2018). Participating in Social Interventions in Ghana: Evidence of the Ghana Social Opportunities Project in the Talensi District. Cogent Social Sciences, Manuscript submitted for Publication.', 'My research, and professional experiences are highly relevant to the position of Assistant Registrar, as they have equipped me with strong administrative, communication, planning, and organizational skills necessary for effective university administration.\r\n\r\nThrough my academic and professional engagements, I have developed the ability to work effectively with diverse groups of people, manage institutional responsibilities, and support policy implementation within structured organizational settings. My background in project planning and management has strengthened my competencies in coordination, report writing, records management, stakeholder engagement, and strategic planning, which are essential functions of the Assistant Registrar role.\r\n\r\nIn teaching and academic-related activities, I have gained experience in preparing official documents, facilitating communication, organizing meetings and presentations, and handling administrative tasks with professionalism and confidentiality. These experiences have enhanced my interpersonal, leadership, and problem-solving abilities.\r\n\r\nMy research experience has also developed my analytical thinking, data management, and report preparation skills. Conducting research requires attention to detail, adherence to procedures, and effective time management, all of which are directly applicable to administrative responsibilities in higher education institutions.\r\n\r\nProfessionally, my involvement in local governance and institutional activities has exposed me to public administration processes, teamwork, coordination of programmes, and service delivery. I am therefore confident that my combined academic knowledge, research capacity, and professional experience make me well suited for the position of Assistant Registrar and capable of contributing effectively to the achievement of the institution’s administrative and academic goals.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Travelling, reading, listening to music, and watching movies. I have a Passion for learning practical and technical skills that promote innovation and problem-solving.', '1 Month', NULL, 'Prof. Owusu Amponsah', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer/ Consultant', 'Center for Settlement Studies,\r\nDepartment of Planning, \r\nKNUST, AR.', '0248691327', 'amponsah_owusu@yahoo.co.uk', 'Ms. Juliana Talata Agyeyomah', 'Civil Servant', 'Municipal Planning Officer', 'Bolgatanga Municipal Assembly, \r\nBolgatanga, UE/R.', '0544286286', 'crispvalta@yahoo.com', 'Ing. Bertha Darteh', 'Development Practitioner', 'Consultant', 'Expertise France,\r\nSustainable Cities Project,\r\nAccra', '0501561578', 'berthadarteh@gmail.com', 'BTU_10EA051B_cv_6a18452f03b901.41105946.pdf', 'CV Maurice Azinim.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '143.105.209.186', '2026-05-28 13:37:51', '2026-05-28 13:37:51', 'BTU_10EA051B_photo_6a18452f03b964.52857330.jpg'