(145, 'BTU-E894AECD', 15, 'Mr.', 'Ofosu', 'Bright Okyere', 'brightofosuokyere32@outlook.com', '+233597232998', 'AF-0344-5282, Cherry Street, Kronum- Afrancho, Kumasi, Ghana', 'Kumasi', 'Bompata', 'Ashanti', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Lois Tweneboa Kodua', NULL, 'Annalisa Ofosu Okyere- 22/05/2020\r\nJaiden Hewins Ofosu Okyere - 26/04/2022', NULL, 'GHA-729227785-9', '1988-11-16', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'University of Electronic Science and Technology of China', 5, '1. Kodua, L. T., Xiao, Y., Adjei, N. O., Asante, D., Ofosu, B. O., &amp; Amankona, D. (2022). Barriers to green human resources management (GHRM) implementation in developing countries. Evidence from Ghana. Journal of cleaner production, 340, 130671.\r\n2. Kodua, L. T., &amp; Ofosu, B. O. (2020). Exploring Low E-Participation in Policy Making in Ghana: A Case Study of Kumasi Metropolitan Assembly.. Journal of Humanities and Social Sciences. (10)2, 1-10.\r\n3. Ofosu, B. O., Addeh, G. Y. A., Kodua, L. T., &amp; Korankye, E. (2020). Environmental Issues of Livestock Production in Developing Countries: Need for Government Intervention Using the Truck Based Approach. J. Biol. Agric. Healthc, 10, 32-48.\r\n4. Dankwa, R. A., Ofosu, B. O., Asare, I., &amp; Lois, T. K. (2018). Causality Nexus between Foreign Direct Investment and Economic Growth: Empirical Evidence from Ghana and China. International Journal of Advanced Research 6(9), 554-570', 'The position of School Administrator is highly relevant to the role of Assistant Registrar because both positions require strong administrative, organizational, and communication skills within an educational environment. As a School Administrator, I have gained an experience in managing student records, coordinating academic activities, handling official documentation, and ensuring compliance with institutional policies and procedures.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, as a School Administrator I regularly interact with students, parents, teachers, and external stakeholders, which helps to develop excellent interpersonal and customer service skills that are essential for an Assistant Registrar. The role also involves scheduling, report preparation, data management, and maintaining confidentiality of academic records, all of which align closely with the duties of an Assistant Registrar.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, experience in supervising administrative processes, supporting admissions and examinations, and utilizing educational management systems prepares a School Administrator to effectively assist in registrar functions such as student registration, records management, admissions coordination, and academic administration.\r\n\r\nOverall, the administrative experience, attention to detail, and knowledge of educational operations acquired as a School Administrator provide a solid foundation for successfully performing the responsibilities of an Assistant Registrar.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '1. Reading and research\r\n2. Writing and blogging\r\n3.Traveling and cultural exploration\r\n4.Volunteering and community service', 'Immediately', NULL, 'Seth Kwame Sakyi Arthur', 'Research Fellow', 'Research Supervisor', 'Kintampo Health Research Center\r\nHospital Road, Near Kintampo-north Municipal Hospital, Kintampo, Ghana', '0243617941', 'Seth.arthur@kintampo-hrc.org', 'Majorie Asumakah', 'Educationist', 'Proprietress', 'Royal scholars Mont, \r\nP.O.Box SE 245 Suame Kumasi', '0202286833', NULL, 'Zheng Fengli', 'Lecturer', 'Professor', 'University of Electronic Science and Technology of China\r\nschool of Public Affairs and Public Administration\r\n611731, Pidu Pixian, Sichuan, Chengdu', '+86133086676963', 'Fzhang.uestc@gmail.com', 'BTU_E894AECD_cv_6a1849e7dc3896.28583502.pdf', 'CV.BRIGHT OKYERE OFOSU.BTU.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.125.251', '2026-05-28 13:57:59', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_E894AECD_photo_6a1849e7dc38f2.43720265.jpeg', 'PIC.jpeg'),
(146, 'BTU-A2B2B464', 15, 'Mr.', 'Ofori', 'Kennedy', 'keofori@ug.edu.gh', '+233244535942', 'Department of Distance Education,\r\nUG, BoxLG31, Legon, Accra', 'Nkawkaw', 'Obo-Kwahu', 'Eastern', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Vida Collison', 'C/O Box LG31, Legon, Accra', 'Daniel Darkwah Ofori-September 3, 2013\r\nKennedy Kwadwo Ofori-August 22, 2016\r\nAbena Agyapomaa Ofori-February 18, 2020', 'P0011493240', 'GHA-712477838-9', '1980-07-17', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'University of Ghana', 11, NULL, 'My experience as a Principal Organiser/programme officer at the University of Ghana relates strongly to the role of an Assistant Registrar because both positions involve administration, coordination, communication, records management, policy implementation, and stakeholder engagement within an institution. A programme officer develops practical administrative and organisational competencies that are directly transferable to the duties of an assistant registrar, particularly in higher education institutions.\r\n\r\nAs a Programme Officer, I am often responsible for planning, organising, and supervising programmes, projects, meetings, and institutional activities. These responsibilities build skills in coordination, scheduling, report writing, budgeting, monitoring, and problem-solving, which are essential for an assistant registrar who oversees administrative operations within departments, faculties, or academic units.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, as a Programme Officer, I regularly interact with students, staff, external organisations, and management, thereby strengthening interpersonal and communication skills. An Assistant Registrar similarly serves as a liaison between university authorities, students, faculty members, and external stakeholders. The ability to manage correspondence, respond to enquiries, and maintain professional relationships is therefore highly relevant.\r\n\r\nMy experience in documentation and records management as a programme officer also aligns with the responsibilities of an assistant registrar. Both roles require maintaining accurate records, preparing reports, drafting official letters, organising institutional data, and ensuring compliance with organisational policies and procedures.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, as a Programme Officer, I often participate in policy implementation, event management, monitoring and evaluation, and team supervision. These experiences prepare an individual for the leadership and administrative responsibilities associated with the assistant registrar position, including supporting academic administration, coordinating admissions, examinations, student affairs, and committee work.\r\n\r\nIn summary, my experience as a Programme Officer has equipped me with strong administrative, organisational, communication, coordination, and managerial skills that are directly applicable to the role of assistant registrar. Such experience demonstrates the ability to work efficiently in institutional administration and contribute effectively to the smooth operation of an organisation or university.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Sports, reading, writing, gardening, researching, and travelling.', 'One month', 'I am committed to professionalism, teamwork, integrity, and continuous learning. I have the capacity to work under pressure, meet deadlines, and contribute positively toward the achievement of the goals and objectives of your university.\r\n\r\nI believe my educational background, administrative experience, and commitment to excellence make me well-suited for the position of Assistant Registrar.', 'Professor Isaac Kofi Biney', 'Lecturing', 'Head of UGLCs', 'University of Ghana Learning Centres,\r\nUniversity of Ghana, \r\nBox LG31, Legon, Accra', '0243601020', 'ibiney@ug.edu.gh', 'Professor David Addae', 'Lecturing', 'Coordinator, University of Ghana Takoradi Learning Centre', 'University of Ghana Learning Centres, \r\nUniversity of Ghana, \r\nBox LG31, Legon, Accra', '0505534793', 'daddae@ug.edu.gh', 'Professor Samuel Amponsah', 'Lecturing', 'HOD, Department of Distance Education', 'Department of Distance Education,\r\nUniversity of Ghana, \r\nBox LG31, Legon, Accra', '0244294043', 'samponsah@ug.edu.gh', 'BTU_A2B2B464_cv_6a1850034e2367.10736470.pdf', 'UP-TO-DATE CV-Ken Ofori-merged.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '197.255.109.2', '2026-05-28 14:24:03', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_A2B2B464_photo_6a1850034e23c7.15603760.jpg', 'Passport picture-26.jpg'),
