(151, 'BTU-5731428E', 8, 'Ms.', 'Avomah', 'Harriet', 'avomah.h@gmail.com', '0240459461', 'C/o Bolgatanga Technical University\r\nP. O. Box 767,\r\nBolgatanga, U.E.R. Ghana', 'Accra', 'Kandiga', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'Lucretia Abosum - 23rd November, 2018\r\nLeonardo Abosum - 23rd January, 2021', 'GHA-715807563-4', 'GHA-715807563-4', '1990-09-30', 'female', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University for Development Studies, Wa', 7, NULL, NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '•	Watching movies \r\n•	Story telling  \r\n•	Listening to music', 'Within the week upon receipt of appointment letter', NULL, 'Dr. Fuseini Mahama', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Head of Department - Accounting and Finance', 'Bolgatanga Technical University\r\nP. O. Box 767,\r\nBolgatanga, U.E.R. Ghana\r\nMobile: +233 (0) 20 9287014 | 054 143 7993', '054 143 7993', 'fmahama@bolgatu.edu.gh', 'Dr. John Williams', 'Medical Doctor', 'Director', 'Principal Medical Officer / Clinical Research Fellow\r\nNavrongo Health Research Centre (NHRC)\r\nP.O. Box 114, Navrongo, Upper East Region, Ghana\r\nMobile: +233 (0) 24 475 5385', '024 475 5385', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_5731428E_cv_6a187ac270c9a7.67841942.pdf', 'CURRICULUM VITAE_HARRIET AVOMAH.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '41.218.225.36', '2026-05-28 17:26:26', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_5731428E_photo_6a187ac270ca08.78651718.jpg', 'Harriet Avomah.jpg'),
(152, 'BTU-62352BBF', 7, 'Mr.', 'Atiah', 'Isaac Ayambila', 'ayambila094@gmail.com', '0245850095', 'Bawku Technical Institute Post Office box 279, Bawku', 'Bolgatanga', 'Bolgatanga', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'catholic', 'married', 'Akolgo Helina Asuamah', 'k1 kumbangre, Bolgatanga', 'Ayambila Perpetua Nmalebna - 4th Sep 2007\r\nAyambila Prudence Ayinbora - 20th Oct 2011\r\nAyambila Petra Apegyine - 20th May 2014\r\nAyambila Pamela Nariyine - 17th OP00141ct 2019', 'P0014134543', 'GHA-715790909-9', '1982-04-19', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'University Of education Winneba', 5, NULL, 'My academic background, teaching experience, and professional engagements are directly aligned with the requirements of the position of Lecturer in the Mechanical Engineering Department at Bolgatanga Technical University. I am confident that my qualifications and experience make me a strong and suitable candidate for this role.\r\nAcademic Qualifications\r\nMy possession of a Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering Education and a Master of Science in Mechanical Engineering provides me with a solid theoretical and practical foundation in the core areas of mechanical engineering. The combination of these two qualifications is particularly relevant to a technical university setting such as Bolgatanga Technical University, where both subject mastery and effective pedagogy are essential. My education degree equips me with the professional teaching skills needed to deliver engineering concepts in a clear, structured, and student-centered manner, while my master\'s degree deepens my technical competence in advanced areas of mechanical engineering. Together, these qualifications demonstrate my readiness to deliver high-quality instruction at the university level.\r\nTeaching Experience\r\nHaving served as a teacher in the Mechanical Engineering Department, I have accumulated substantial hands-on classroom experience in delivering lectures, conducting tutorials, and supervising practical and laboratory sessions. I am well versed in curriculum planning, scheme of work development, student assessment, and the application of instructional strategies that promote active learning and technical competence among students. I understand the unique demands of teaching engineering in a technical institution, where theory must be consistently linked to practical application, and I have consistently strived to bridge this gap in my teaching practice. This experience directly mirrors the core responsibilities expected of a Lecturer at Bolgatanga Technical University, and I am therefore well-prepared to transition seamlessly into the role.\r\nLeadership and Administrative Experience\r\nMy role as Head of the Mechanical Engineering Department has further strengthened my suitability for this position. In this capacity, I have gained considerable experience in academic administration, departmental planning, staff coordination, timetabling, laboratory and workshop management, and quality assurance. These are skills that are invaluable within a university department setting. My leadership background demonstrates that I can contribute not only as an effective and dedicated lecturer but also as a responsible, collaborative, and proactive member of the academic community at Bolgatanga Technical University.\r\nRelevance to Bolgatanga Technical University\'s Mission\r\nBolgatanga Technical University is committed to providing technical and vocational education that meets the needs of industry and drives development in the Upper East Region and Ghana at large. My background in mechanical engineering education aligns strongly with this mission. I am passionate about training practically competent and industry-ready graduates who can contribute meaningfully to the engineering and manufacturing sectors of the Ghanaian economy. My experience in a technical education environment positions me to actively support the university\'s goals of academic excellence, skills development, and community relevance.\r\nProfessional Commitment\r\nAlthough I do not yet have formal research publications, I am committed to continuous professional development and growing my contribution to the academic community. I intend to actively engage in research activities, industry collaboration, and scholarly work that will enrich my teaching and contribute to the development of the Mechanical Engineering Department at Bolgatanga Technical University. I believe that my combination of technical knowledge, teaching methodology, leadership experience, and genuine dedication to student success makes me a highly relevant and valuable candidate for this lecturing position.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading engineering and technical journals/textbooks\r\nTinkering with mechanical systems or machines\r\nDIY engineering projects and fabrication\r\nMentoring and tutoring young students\r\nProblem solving and logical reasoning activities\r\nParticipating in professional associations\r\nFootball', 'Immediately', 'I wish to use this opportunity to further express my strong desire and readiness to contribute meaningfully to the growth and development of the Mechanical Engineering Department at Bolgatanga Technical University.\r\nI have a deep passion for technical and engineering education and firmly believe in its critical role in driving industrial and economic development in Ghana, particularly in the Upper East Region. Having dedicated my career to teaching and leading a Mechanical Engineering Department, I understand the unique demands and opportunities of technical university education, and I am fully committed to meeting and exceeding those expectations as a Lecturer.\r\nI am a hardworking, dedicated, and passionate engineering educator who genuinely cares about the academic and professional development of students. I believe that every student has the potential to succeed with the right guidance, support, and quality instruction. It is this belief that drives my commitment to excellence in teaching and my enthusiasm for joining the academic team at Bolgatanga Technical University.\r\nI am grateful for the opportunity to apply for this position and I look forward to contributing positively to the mission and vision of Bolgatanga Technical University.', 'Mr Azuyemah Francis', 'Gratis foundation, Mechanical Engineer', 'Manager', 'Gratis foundation Post Office Box 204, bolgatanga', '0242303782', NULL, 'Dr. Jamal-Deen Kuumah', 'lecturer', 'lecturer', 'Tamale Technical University', '0243388858', NULL, 'Prof. Anthony Akayeti', 'Lecturer', 'lecturer', 'Tamale Technical University', '0243564223', NULL, 'BTU_62352BBF_cv_6a187ca4c02815.26401431.pdf', 'Atiah Isaac Ayambila cv-1.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '197.251.240.4', '2026-05-28 17:34:28', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_62352BBF_photo_6a187ca4c02863.05991758.jpg', 'new.jpg'),
(153, 'BTU-9AC4521B', 8, 'Dr.', 'MMIEH KWAKYE', 'RAPHAEL', 'mmiehkwakyer@yahoo.com', '+233539963907', 'Deduako Teachers Quarters\r\nAK-621-0904\r\nKotei-Deduako\r\nKumasi', 'Kumasi', 'Kumasi', 'Ashanti', 'Ghanaian', 'Catholic', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-729932805-1', '1988-09-14', 'male', 'PhD', 'Zhejiang Gongshang University', 1, 'Mmieh Kwakye R, Qu L, Wang Y, Kwakye BO (2026), &quot;From entry to engagement: how platform enablement and competition dynamics mediate SMEs’ seller responses&quot;. Journal of Entrepreneurship in Emerging Economies, Vol. ahead-of-print No. ahead-of-print. https://doi.org/10.1108/JEEE-09-2025-0565 (ESCI, Q1)\r\n\r\nMmieh Kwakye, R., Qu, L., &amp; Wang, Y. (2025). Sustainability practices and complementor innovation capability: a PLS-SEM serial mediation model of market pressure and strategic alliances. Business Process Management Journal, 1-23. (SSCI Q1)\r\n\r\nAmankona, D., Yi, K., &amp; Raphael, M.K. (2025). Unravelling the nexus of corporate digital responsibility and business success: assessing the impact of digital innovation. Technology Analysis &amp; Strategic Management, 1-15.  (SSCI Q2)\r\n\r\nRaphael, Mmieh &amp; Ofori, Charles &amp; Nsiah, Takyi &amp; Kampamba, Chikwanda. (2023). Inflation and Unemployment Dynamics in Ghana. EPRA International Journal of Economics, Business and Management Studies. 1-12. 10.36713/epra14865. \r\n\r\nNsiah, T. K., Danso, R. A., Charles, O., &amp; Raphael, M. K. (2022). Management Innovation, Green Product Innovation, Green Process Innovation Influence on Financial Performance. A Study of South African Manufacturing Firms. International Journal of Business, Technology, and Organizational Behavior (IJBTOB), 2, 2775-4936. https://doi.org/10.52218/ijbtob.v2i4.211\r\n\r\nCharles, O., Nsiah, T. K., Raphael, M. K., Jnr, I. A., &amp; Agbattey, J (2022). Liquidity management and profitability. A case of listed banks in Ghana. International Journal of Business, Technology and Organizational Behavior (IJBTOB), 2(6), 657-671.\r\n\r\nDanquah, Derrick Opoku, Belinda Bonney, and Raphael Mmieh Kwakye (2018). &quot;Examining the Psychosocial Hurdles on Effective Public Participation. A Keynote toward Enhancing Participation in the Political Milieu.&quot; JL Pol\'y &amp; Globalization 79, 11.', 'My academic training as a PhD holder, together with my teaching and professional experience, has prepared me well for this position. Through presentations, seminars, group discussions, and research activities, I have developed strong communication, analytical, and interpersonal skills essential for effective teaching and academic engagement. In addition, my teaching experience at the JHS level strengthened my ability to explain concepts clearly, manage learners, and prepare instructional materials, while my professional experience enhanced my organizational and administrative abilities. These experiences position me to contribute effectively to teaching, research, and academic service.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, research, and sports', 'Immediately', 'N/A', 'Professor Qu Liang', 'Lecturer/Professor', 'Professor', 'No.18, Xuezheng Str., \r\nZhejiang Gongshang University \r\nQiantang District, Hangzhou, China, 310018', '?86?13777851349', 'quliang@mail.zjgsu.edu.cn', 'Mrs. Cynthia Boatemaa', 'Accountant', 'Accountant', 'Mankranso SHS \r\nMankranso - Ashanti', '+233 201788054', 'N/A', 'Isaac Amankona (Ph.D.)', 'Associate Professor', 'Researcher', 'School of Computer Science \r\nUniversity of Electronic Science and Technology of China', '?86?18190856242', 'obiriisaac@uestc.edu.cn', 'BTU_9AC4521B_cv_6a18844f0de1b4.69757458.pdf', 'CV_Raphael Mmieh Kwakye_BTU.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.111.62', '2026-05-28 18:07:11', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_9AC4521B_photo_6a18844f0de205.34129856.jpeg', 'PP.jpeg'),
(154, 'BTU-F4D01A8D', 13, 'Mr.', 'Amankwah', 'Kwesi Emmanuel', 'amankwahkwesi90@gmail.com', '0556887702', 'Ashaiman-Tema', 'Tema', 'Ashaiman', 'Greater Accra', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-729753605-8', '1999-06-26', 'male', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'University of Ghana', 5, NULL, NULL, 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Coding &amp; Personal Projects, Football, Computer Hardware Repair, Keeping up with Emerging IT Trends, and hands-on exploration of new technologies and open-source resources', '1 month', 'I believe my background makes me a strong fit for this role. I hold a BSc in Information Technology (Second Class Upper) from the University of Ghana, Legon, and have over five years of hands-on experience developing, deploying, and maintaining live web systems using PHP, React.js, MySQL, and RESTful APIs — directly matching the technical stack required for this position.\r\n\r\nI have practical experience integrating third-party APIs and managing databases across institutional platforms, including a school website and learning portal with SMS gateway integration (Gallop SMS), a fintech savings system with role-based authentication, and a pharmacy POS application with inventory tracking — all of which are currently live and in active use.\r\n\r\nBeyond development, I have administered campus-wide network infrastructure, managed student information databases, and provided technical support and training to staff and faculty — experience that aligns closely with the system administration and stakeholder support responsibilities of this role.\r\n\r\nI am highly self-motivated, staying current with emerging IT trends, and I enjoy working through new technologies independently. I am willing to relocate to Bolgatanga and commit fully to supporting the university\'s academic and administrative ICT functions.', 'George Nartey', 'Teaching', 'Head of Department - Queensland International School', 'Ashaiman-Tema', '+233 24 174 1251', 'georgenartey@gmail.com', 'George Ofori Ayeh', 'Teaching', 'Head Master - Holy Gabriel Anglican School', 'Ashaiman-Lebanon', '+233 24 256 0480', 'georgefory@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_F4D01A8D_cv_6a18857caba4b2.43080105.pdf', 'Amankwah_Emmanuel_Official CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.47.64', '2026-05-28 18:12:12', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_F4D01A8D_photo_6a18857caba509.53013269.jpeg', 'WhatsApp Image 2026-05-28 at 18.05.06.jpeg'),
(155, 'BTU-44800140', 14, 'Mr.', 'POULIWEAH', 'JAMES NABEL', 'najames200@gmail.com', '0202168638', 'P O BOX 2194, LA,ACCRA', 'BILLAW', 'BILLAW', 'Upper West', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'married', 'MRS.LUCY SADIA NABEL POULIWEAH', 'P O BOX 2194,LA ACCRA', 'DEBORAH WISEWIEH NABEL  22/03/2016\r\nSALOME DINFIALU NABEL      09/06/2018\r\nEDINA NLODI NABEL              20/12/2022', 'POO28991478', 'GHA-714433916-8', '1983-01-05', 'male', 'Professional Certificate', 'ICAG', 11, NULL, NULL, 'no', NULL, NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING, LISTENING TO GOOD GOSPEL MUSIC AND PREACING, AND SOMETHING WATCHING FOOTBALL', '2WEEK TO 1 MONTH', NULL, 'ELDER JONATHAN LARTEY', 'AUDITING', 'AUDITOR', 'BANK OF GHANA', '0202071652,027563033', NULL, 'ELDER HARRISON ANKOAH KWASI', 'AUDITING', 'AUDIT MANAGER', 'THE CHURCH OF PENTECOST-HQ\r\nP O BOX 2194', '0208411165,024452056', 'hasarpong@thecophq.org', 'ELDER AMOATENG AUGUSTINE', 'TREASURING', 'DEPUTEY FINANCE MANAGER', 'THE CHURCH OF PENTECOST -HQ', '0247850287,020303700', NULL, 'BTU_44800140_cv_6a188bda37e134.88217331.pdf', 'JNPPD.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '102.223.23.181', '2026-05-28 18:39:22', '2026-05-28 18:39:22', 'BTU_44800140_photo_6a188bda37e191.51369583.jpeg', 'JPP.jpeg'),
(156, 'BTU-FCEF85C0', 14, 'Mr.', 'ACQUAH', 'DANIEL KWESI', 'danielacquah0@gmail.com', '+233246277140', 'NIHR-GSU Ghana Hub, 1st floor, Room 3 Credit Union Building, UDS, Dungu, Tamale', 'ACCRA', 'EKUMFI-EKUMPOANO', 'Central', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIANITY', 'married', 'DEBORAH APPIAH', 'C/o CREDIT UNION BOX 1350, UDS, TAMALE', 'STEPHANIE A.S. ACQUAH -17/12/2013\r\n\r\nBERNICE E. K. ACQUAH - 16/04/2016\r\n\r\nPHILIP A.O. ACQUAH - 13/03/2019', NULL, 'GHA-715218352-0', '1983-09-21', 'male', 'Professional Certificate', 'INSTITUTE OF CHARTERED ACCOUNTANT, GHANA', 11, '1.	Reducing surgical site infections in low-income and middle-income countries (FALCON): a pragmatics, multicentre, stratified, randomized controlled trial. \r\n2.	Routine sterile glove and instrument change at the time of abdominal wound closure to prevent surgical site infection (ChEETAh): a pragmatic, cluster-randomised trial in seven low-income and middle-income countries. \r\n3.	Outcomes and Their State-level Variation in Patients Undergoing Surgery with \r\nPeroperative SARS-CoV-2 Infection in the USA: A Prospective Multicenter Study. \r\n4.	Effects of pre-operative isolation on postoperative pulmonary complications after elective surgery: an international prospective cohort study. \r\n5.	SARS-CoV-2 infection and venous thromboembolism after surgery: an international prospective cohort study. \r\n6.	Timing of surgery following SARS-CoV-2 infection: an international prospective cohort study. \r\n7.	Attempted suicide of two confirmed SARS-CoV-2 infected patients in an isolation facility and recommendations to prevent COVID-19 suicides: a case report. \r\n8.	Strategies to minimise and monitor biases and imbalances by arm in surgical cluster randomised trials: evidence from ChEETAh, trial in seven low-and middle-income countries. \r\n9.	Adaptation of the Wound Healing Questionnaire universal-reporter outcome measure for use in global surgery trials (TALON-1-study): mixed-methods study and rasch analysis.', 'My experience relates to the position being applied for the following reasons:\r\n\r\n1. Technical expertise, professional knowledge and competence.\r\n2. Being able to work independently and under pressure.\r\n3. Being able to apply accounting standards/rules to a certain situation.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Research, and watching football at my leisure time', '2 weeks', NULL, 'Mr Francis Asare-Larbi', 'Accountant', 'UDS, Campus Accountant', 'University for Development Studies, Tamale, Ghana', '+233 244 599 413', 'asafrabi@yahoo.com', 'Dr Eugene Dogkotenge Kuugbee', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Head of Department', 'CK Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences (CKT-UTAS)', '+233544680556', 'Kuugbee@yahoo.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_FCEF85C0_cv_6a188f2ba37559.66258482.pdf', 'CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '179.64.71.19', '2026-05-28 18:53:31', '2026-05-28 18:53:31', 'BTU_FCEF85C0_photo_6a188f2ba375b9.53983313.jpg', 'DANIEL.jpg'),
(157, 'BTU-D088787E', 10, 'Mr.', 'Haruna', 'Jamal', 'harunajamal30@gmail.com', '0249357568', 'Navrongo SHS\r\nBox 33\r\nNavrongo', 'Pusiga', 'Pusiga', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Moslim', 'married', 'Isssaka Rihanatu', 'Box 1 Pusiga', 'Jamal Mohammed - 16-07-2013\r\nJamal Muhamin     -  20-10-2017\r\nJamal Manal          -  21 -05-2021\r\nJamal Minal           -  21 - 05-2021', 'P006441051X', 'GHA-715614744-9', '1987-01-01', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'C.K Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences', 11, NULL, 'I am a Senior High School professional teacher with experience in teaching, mentoring and guiding students in academic and personal development. My role involves preparing lesson plans delivering lectures, assessing students’ performance and supporting learners to achieve educational success.\r\n\r\nMy profession is closely related to that of a lecturer because it requires strong communication skills, subject knowledge, classroom management, research ability and the capacity to explain concepts effectively to students. I also engage in academic guidance, curriculum delivery and continuous learning to improve teaching methods and educational outcomes.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading and watching Football', 'one week A', NULL, 'Amiru Bakariwie', 'Lecturer', 'Exams Officer', 'Box WA64, Wa', '0542390139', NULL, 'Augustine Boyorbor Forkor', 'Civil Savant', 'ICT Coordinator', 'Box 19, Tumu', '0202300464', NULL, 'Haruna Amin', 'Civil Savant', 'District Co-operative Officer', 'Box 1, Pusiga', '0243194918', NULL, 'BTU_D088787E_cv_6a18919a0346c3.11916264.pdf', 'College certificate.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.254.124', '2026-05-28 19:03:54', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_D088787E_photo_6a18919a034712.53387897.jpg', 'j.jpg');
