(171, 'BTU-E13194ED', 2, 'Mr.', 'Ayariga', 'David', 'davidayariga@gmail.com', '+233243654801', 'Bawku Senior High School\r\nP.O.Box 50\r\nBawku, UE/R', 'Accra', 'Bongo-Beo (Bongo District)', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Mary Kancha', 'Bawku Senior High School, Box 50-Bawku', 'Fiona Ayariga                     08/10/2008\r\nMichelle Ayariga                27/12/2014\r\nMelvin Ayariga                  17/09/2018', 'P0010314652', 'GHA-715499867-2', '1981-02-14', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST), Kumasi', 11, 'No peer-reviewed publications yet. However, I have ongoing research work in progress, and one manuscript is currently under review.', 'My teaching experience at both the university and college levels makes me a great fit for this role:\r\n•University Experience: My role as an Assistant Lecturer at the University of Technology and Applied Sciences (UTAS), Navrongo, has given me practical experience lecturing tertiary students and adapting French lessons for science and technology students.\r\n•Teaching Methods: Serving as a French Tutor at Gbewaa College of Education, as well as at Presbyterian Nursing and Midwifery Training College, Bawku, strengthened my classroom management skills and ability to apply effective language teaching methodologies in both teacher-training and professional health education contexts\r\n•Language Skills Development: Having taught Oral Communication and French Language Usage (TEJS111), I know how to help students improve their spoken French, phonetics, and everyday communication skills.\r\n•Research Focus: My ongoing research and the paper I currently have under review show my dedication to growing as an academic and contributing to the department\'s research goals.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading journal articles, academic writing, listening to Francophone news channels, and farming.', 'Two weeks', 'I am a committed French language teacher with experience at both secondary and tertiary levels. I use learner-centred approaches in my teaching and focus on helping students improve their communication skills in French. I have a strong interest in French language pedagogy and oral communication development, and I continue to develop myself through research and professional activities to improve my teaching practice and contribute effectively to institutional goals.', 'Dr. Stella Afi Makafui Yegblemenawo', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Head of Department and PhD Supervisor', 'Department of Language and Communication Sciences\r\nKwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology(KNUST)\r\nPrivate Mail Bag (PMB), Kumasi, Ghana', '+233242350565', 'marcaphui@yahoo.co.uk', 'Rev. Abugbilla Bukari', 'Teacher', 'Headmaster', 'Bawku Senior High School\r\nP.O.Box 50\r\nBawku, UE/R', '+233244593168', 'bukson5@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_E13194ED_cv_6a198275ce6f20.97777693.pdf', 'CV-DAVID AYARIGA .pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.254.107', '2026-05-29 12:11:33', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_E13194ED_photo_6a198275ce6f71.40018912.jpg', 'pix.jpg'),
