(176, 'BTU-65C49E69', 15, 'Mr.', 'Fusheini', 'Karim', 'fusheinik@gmail.com', '+233248660756', 'P. O. Box 1602, Madina, Accra', 'Accra', 'Wulensi', 'Greater Accra', 'Ghanaian', 'ISLAM', 'married', 'NASHIRU RUKAYATU', 'Oyibi Ashform Area, ACCRA', 'Abdul Karim Ummamatu  22/06/2007\r\nAbdul Karim Raqeeba-Puumaya 26/11/2022\r\nAbdul Karim Kainat-Wunam  9/10/2024', '0019381352', 'GHA-002447688-3', '1983-06-16', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'GHANA INSTITUTE OF MANAGEMENT AND PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION', 11, '1..	Fusheini K., Alfa A.A., Salia H., Kumasey A.S. (2021), ‘Assessing the Contributions of CSR Activities to the Educational Sector.’ In: Adae E.K., Kosiba J.P.B., Hinson R.E., Twum K.K., Newman N., Nutsugah F.F. (eds) Responsible Management in Emerging Markets. Sustainable Development Goals Series. Palgrave Macmillan, Cham. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-76563-7_3. [Corporate social responsibility and sustainable business practices]\r\n2.	Fusheini, K. and Salia, H. (2021), &quot;The contribution of corporate social responsibility (CSR) initiatives to student enrollment and performance in Ghana&quot;, International Journal of Educational Management, Vol. 35 No. 3, pp. 606-620. https://doi.org/10.1108/IJEM-07-2020-0348. [Private sector social impact]\r\n3.	Letitia, S. A., Fusheini, K. (2023). &quot;Reducing Gender-Based Violence among Rural Households using Gender Action Learning Methodology.&quot; Universe International Journal of Interdisciplinary Research, 4(5), 387-410. [Gender inclusion and social development]\r\n4.	Letitia, S. A., Fusheini, K. (2021). &quot;An assessment of the impact of small-scale irrigation schemes on livelihood and poverty reduction in the Upper East Region of Ghana.&quot; Universe International Journal of Interdisciplinary Research, 2(7), 11-19. [Agriculture and Rural development]\r\n5.	Quampah, D. K., Salia, H., Fusheini, K., &amp; Adoboe-Mensah, N. (2021). &quot;Factors affecting the internal audit effectiveness in local government institutions in Ghana.&quot; Journal of Accounting and Taxation, 13(4), 255-269. [Governance and financial management]\r\n6.	Tuuli, M. M., Fusheini, K., &amp; Salia, H. (2023). Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) Effect on Teaching and Learning: Evidence from an Emerging Economy. International Journal of Innovation in Teaching and Learning (IJITL), 9(1), 1-19. [Corporate social responsibility and sustainable business practices]', 'My background in academic, research, and professional practice directly equips me to contribute effectively to the administrative and human resource management functions of the assistant registrar role.\r\nAcademically, I hold a Master of Research (MRes) in Business Administration Management from GIMPA, with focus areas in organisational development, strategic planning, and educational management, precisely the disciplinary grounding required for university administration. My undergraduate BSc in Operations and Project Management further strengthens my capacity to manage complex administrative systems, coordinate institutional processes, and support governance structures.\r\nProfessionally, I have over ten years of experience in programme administration, stakeholder coordination, and institutional management across government, NGO, and international development settings. As Programme Officer at GASIP under the Ministry of Food and Agriculture and currently as Project Administrator for a multi-partner UN-Habitat/ITC initiative, I have consistently managed documentation systems, coordinated multi-stakeholder processes, tracked budgets, ensured compliance with organisational governance frameworks, and produced high-quality reports for senior leadership, all of which are central to the work of an Assistant Registrar.\r\nMy current role as Senior Course Tutor at the University of Cape Coast\'s College of Distance Education brings direct exposure to university administration, academic records management, student advisory services, and faculty-administration liaison, providing firsthand understanding of how universities function operationally.\r\nIn terms of human resource and secretarial functions, I have coordinated recruitment and procurement processes, managed correspondence, prepared board-level briefing materials, and maintained confidential institutional records across multiple organisations. My experience managing logistics for 60+ workshops and stakeholder events further demonstrates my ability to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines, a specific requirement of this role.\r\nAs a researcher, I have co-authored eight peer-reviewed publications in international journals and book chapters, including works on governance, institutional accountability, and educational management. This analytical and writing capacity will be an asset in drafting policy documents, administrative circulars, academic briefs, and institutional reports.\r\nMy familiarity with northern Ghana, having trained at E.P. College of Education in Bimbilla and worked extensively across the northern regions, also means I understand the context in which the University for Development Studies operates and am well positioned to contribute meaningfully to its mission of producing technically skilled graduates for sustainable development.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'RESEARCH, READING AND FOOTBALL', '1 MONTH', 'KEY ACHIEVEMENTS &amp; DEMONSTRATED IMPACT\r\n•	Managed data collection, analysis, and reporting for a €50M+ program across 65 districts with over 400 participating community savings and loans associations (CSLA)\r\n•	Developed comprehensive databases and tracking systems supporting real-time project monitoring and evidence-based decision-making\r\n•	Prepared 50+ analytical reports for international donors (IFAD, Climate Adaptation Fund, UN-Habitat), meeting rigorous quality standards.\r\n•	Utilised digital data collection tools (Excel, Kobo Toolbox, ArcGIS Survey 123), improving data accuracy and efficiency\r\n•	Supported implementation of multi-million-dollar projects funded by IFAD, Climate Adaptation Fund, and UN-Habitat with zero compliance issues\r\n•	Coordinated 60+ workshops, training sessions, and stakeholder events across Ghana, managing all logistics and documentation\r\n•	Prepared comprehensive project documentation, including ToRs, concept notes, work plans, and budget proposals\r\n•	Tracked project milestones and deliverables across multiple countries and implementing partners, ensuring timely completion\r\n•	Processed hundreds of financial transactions, including travel claims, consultant payments, and operational expenses\r\n•	Supported procurement processes, ensuring compliance with organisational procedures and value for money\r\n•	Maintained comprehensive financial documentation with zero audit queries across multiple donor-funded projects\r\n•	Developed monitoring frameworks and performance measurement systems for complex multi-stakeholder programs\r\n•	Collected and analysed program data, generating insights that informed strategic adjustments and improved outcomes\r\n•	Prepared quarterly and annual reports documenting progress, achievements, and lessons learned for international donors\r\n•	Supported performance reviews and evaluations using data-driven approaches\r\n•	Coordinated effectively with UN agencies (UN-Habitat), the International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD), government ministries, and civil society\r\n•	Facilitated multi-stakeholder coordination across 65 districts, international partners, and hundreds of community organisations\r\n•	Represented organisations in national forums and coordination meetings with government and development partners\r\n•	Built and maintained strong professional relationships supporting effective project delivery', 'Daniel Kofi Abu', 'CONSULTANT', 'National Project Coordinator', 'UN-Habitat, Ghana', '+233 245272014', 'daniel.abu@un.org', 'LETITIA APAM', 'CONSULTANT', 'GENDER SPECIALIST', 'PROSPER PROJECT, TAMALE', '0246285500', 'sampoa.lit@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_65C49E69_cv_6a19bdb2429171.24952821.pdf', 'KARIM FUSHEINI_CERTIFIED TRUE COPY OF MASTERS DEGREE CERTIFICATE.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '45.221.24.254', '2026-05-29 16:24:18', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_65C49E69_photo_6a19bdb24291c5.15234294.jpg', 'DIGITAL PASSPORT PIC KARIM.jpg'),
