(192, 'BTU-7B391B1A', 8, 'Dr.', 'Boateng', 'Frank Agyei', 'frankboat89@gmail.com', '+233532617729', 'P.O Box NK 326, Nkawkaw,Eastern Region-Ghana', 'Nkawkaw', 'Nkawkaw', 'Eastern', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Stella Serwah Owusu', 'NK 326,Nkawkaw,Eastern Region-Ghana', '1.Agyei Boateng Othniel 15/01/2015\r\n2.Agyei Boateng Omari-28/09/2017', 'P0023207736', 'GHA-729213249-9', '1988-02-07', 'male', 'PhD', 'ICN Business School, France', 11, '1.Agyei, F. B., Nigam, N., &amp; Shatila, K. (2025). Impact of Financial Technology on Financial Inclusion, the Effect of Rules and Regulations: The Case of Ghana. African Finance Journal, 27(1), 1-12. https://hdl.handle.net/10520/ejc-finj_v27_n1_a1\r\n\r\n2.Agyei, F.B., &amp; Nigam, N., (2025). Financial Technology and Sustainable Development Goals in Ghana. European Journal of Management,25(1),19-47\r\nhttps://iabe.org/IABE-DOI/article.aspx?DOI=EJM-25-1.2\r\n\r\n3. Agyei, F. B., Nigam, N., &amp; Shatila, K. (2024). Impact of Sustainable Development Goals on Profitability: Evidence from Ghanaian Banks. Theoretical Economics Letters, 14(6), 2095-2118.doi: 10.4236/tel.2024.146104. \r\nhttps://www.scirp.org/journal/paperinformation?paperid=137215\r\n\r\n4.Yensu, J. Agyei, F.B. and Atuilik,D.A. (2024), Corporate Governance Characteristics And Its Effect On The Performance Of Microfinance Institutions In Ghana. Iosr Journal of Economics and Finance (Iosr-Jef) doi: 10.9790/5933-1506023845. https://www.iosrjournals.org/iosr-jef/papers/Vol15-Issue6/Ser-2/D1506023037.pdf \r\nhttps://www.iosrjournals.org/iosr-jef/pages/vol.15i6-Series-2.html\r\n\r\n\r\n5. Shatila, K., Agyei, F.B. and Aloulou, W.J. (2023), &quot;Impact of transformational leadership on leadership effectiveness: the mediating effect of emotional skills in the Lebanese small and medium-sized enterprises context&quot;, Journal of Enterprising Communities: People and Places in the Global Economy, Vol. ahead-of-print No. ahead-of-print. https://doi.org/10.1108/JEC-09-2023-0174\r\n\r\n6. NIGAM, Nirjhar and BOATENG AGYEI, Frank and SHATILA, Khodor and Benetti, Cristiane, Impact of Fintech on Financial Inclusion: The Case of Ghana. Available at SSRN: https://ssrn.com/abstract=4848758 or http://dx.doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.4848758\r\n\r\n7. Agyei, F.B. (2023), Education and Awareness Creation on Sustainability Practices, the Role of Teachers in Business Schools. International Journal of Innovative Science and Research Technology. https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8188610\r\n\r\n8. Agyei, F.B (2023), A Thorough Review and Analysis of the Role of Banks in Fighting Money Laundering; Through the Lenses of Regulations, Principles, and International Best Practices. International Journal of Innovative Science and Research Technology.8(10), 14. https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10002680', 'I am committed and a hardworking young man with Six (6) years University and High School Teaching experiences in Management, Finance, Accounting coupled with ten (10) years Banking &amp; Finance practice, with publications in international journals, poised to achieve success with great sense of humility, Integrity, honesty and dedication. I have genuine interest in teaching, community development and very passionate about sustainability related issues in creating proper shared value for all stakeholders.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '1.Reading\r\n2.Listening to Music\r\n3.Community Volunteering and Service', 'Immediately', NULL, 'Pro.Anthony Amoah', 'Faculty Lecturer', 'Dean,School of Sustainable Development,UESD,Somanya-Ghana', 'University of Environment and Sustainable Development, Somanya-Ghana', '+233244227988', 'aamoah@uesd.edu.gh', 'Benjamin Staudt', 'Faculty Lecturer', 'Academic Coordinator', 'Karls Hochschule International University Karlstr.36-38,76133, Karlshruhe-Germany', '+4915201649738', 'bstaudt@karlshochschule.org', 'Mr.Benjamin Owusu', 'Banker', 'Chief Executive Officer', 'Atiwa Rural Bank PLC, P.O Box 28\r\nKwabeng, Eastern Region, Ghana', '+2332448