(216, 'BTU-381F4855', 2, 'Mr.', 'Ameko', 'Fred', 'fred.ameko001@stu.ucc.edu.gh', '0555274182', 'Sokode Senior High Technical School\r\nP.O. Box 1362, Ho\r\nVolta Region', 'Ho', 'Ho', 'Volta', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Norvor Ivy', 'Sokode Senior High Technical School P.O. Box 1362, Ho Volta Region', 'I am yet to have a child', NULL, 'GHA-724685243-5', '1992-10-24', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Cape Coast', 3, 'PUBLICATION\r\n•	Chataa, P., Naandam, S. M., Oduro, B., &amp; Ameko, F. (2026). Optimal Control and Cost-Effectiveness of Vaccination and Treatment for Cholera–Hepatitis E Co-Infection. Mathematical Methods in the Applied Sciences.\r\n\r\nMANUSCRIPT UNDER REVIEW\r\n•	Chataa, P., Ameko, F., Naandam, S. M., Oduro, B., &amp; Ibrahim, M. (2025). Optimal Control and Economic Impact Analysis of Malaria Intervention Strategies using a Mathematical Modeling Approach. International Journal of Mathematics and Mathematical Sciences. Manuscript Under Review.', 'I am currently facilitating at the University of Cape Coast, College of Distance Education, where I teach mathematics courses, prepare lecture notes and supervise students\' learning. I am also pursuing a PhD in Applied Mathematics, specializing in mathematical modeling and disease dynamics. My combined teaching and research experience has provided me with strong analytical, instructional, and research skills that are directly relevant to this position.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, watching football and listening to music', '2 weeks', 'I currently lecture undergraduate and postgraduate students at University of Cape Coast College of Distance Education (CoDE). \r\n   This has strengthened my instructional delivery, course material development, and student supervision skills - \r\n   all directly relevant to the teaching and research mandate at Bolgatanga Technical University.', 'Prof. Samuel M. Naandam', 'University Lecturer', 'Former Head of Department (Mathematics), University of Cape Coast', 'Department of Mathematics \r\nUniversity Post Office\r\nCape Coast, Central Region, Ghana', '0244859183', 'snaandam@ucc.edu.gh', 'Prof. Ernest Yankson', 'University Lecturer', 'Dean, School of Physical Sciences University of Cape Coast', 'Department of Mathematics \r\nUniversity Post Office\r\nCape Coast, Central Region, Ghana', '0245299482', 'ernest.yankson@ucc.edu.gh', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_381F4855_cv_6a1c910abdf451.51326127.pdf', 'Fred _ Ameko_Academic_CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.160.24.121', '2026-05-31 19:50:34', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_381F4855_photo_6a1c910abdf4a5.83949139.jpg', 'IMG__Fred_Ameko_Passport.jpg'),
(217, 'BTU-95A41C1B', 15, 'Ms.', 'GEORGINA', 'BAKOBIE', 'gbakobie993@gmail.com', '+233535514145', 'ADENTA', 'Tamale', 'Accra', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1993-04-27', 'female', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'UPSA', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Godfred Nyamekye', NULL, NULL, 'Ghana Community Exchange\r\nValue Chain &amp; Production Manager Tel: 0243135501\r\ngknyamkye@yahoo.com', NULL, NULL, 'Samuel Manu', NULL, NULL, 'Tamale Teaching Hospital Principal Accountant Tel:0243346107\r\nNanamanu84@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_95A41C1B_cv_6a1cb09cdb2a05.08182548.pdf', 'GEORGINA BAKOBIE\'s CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.134.120', '2026-05-31 22:05:16', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_95A41C1B_photo_6a1cb09cdb2a41.16660263.jpeg', 'Passport pic.jpeg'),
(218, 'BTU-AE8580CE', 14, 'Mr.', 'Amelorvor', 'Kwadzo Mawudor Doe', 'amelorvormawudor@gmail.com', '0245231673', 'Presbyterian Church of Ghana Mepe \r\nP. O. BOX 6', 'Mepe', 'Mepe', 'Volta', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-713612898-7', '1999-11-01', 'male', 'Bachelor\'s Degree', 'Ho Technical University', 2, NULL, NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Reading, sports, Music', '1 month', 'I know you’re are looking for  an accountant and I am not fully qualified because just a fresh accounting and taxation graduate. I would be very grateful if you can employ me as an assistant accountant so that I can learn more on my career.', 'Amelorlawovor Agbedanu', 'Teacher', 'Head Teacher', 'Mepe Dadome', '0243476075', NULL, 'Albert Agbemabiase', 'Banker', 'Branch Manager', 'Battor', '0243611415', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_AE8580CE_cv_6a1cb6dec8b982.95595341.pdf', 'my CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.41.252', '2026-05-31 22:31:58', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_AE8580CE_photo_6a1cb6dec8b9d4.11790991.jpg', '5c1799d0-c7a6-40ed-92d0-5ef0ddfe737b-1_all_307.jpg'),
(219, 'BTU-472A2B73', 5, 'Mr.', 'OWUSU', 'JACOB JUNIOR', 'jacjunior95@gmail.com', '+233248149160', 'Northlite Solar Limited,\r\nWater Aid Avenue\r\nKumbosigo, Bolgatanga', 'AGONA ASHANTI', 'JACOBU-FIANKOMA', 'Ashanti', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-728006890-6', '1993-11-05', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'University of Nigeria, Nsukka', 5, 'J. J. Owusu, E. C. Okoroigwe, C. A. Mgbemene, G. Takyi, and O. V. Ekechukwu, “Technical\r\nstakeholders’ perspective of solar photovoltaic system failure in Sub-Saharan Africa: The case of Ghana”, SJES, vol. 9, no. 1, pp. 24–40, Apr. 2025.\r\n\r\nJ. J. Owusu, E. Okoroigwe, O. V. Ekechukwu and G. Takyi, &quot;Photovoltaic Systems and Technology Failure in Ghana: Experience from Technical Stakeholders,&quot; in 2020 Sustainable Engineering and Industrial Technology, Nsukka, 2020. \r\n\r\nJ. Owusu Jnr, S. Gyamfi, and J. Israel, “Household Electricity Tariff and Life Line Charges in Ghana – Policy Mismatch.” International Conference on Climate Change and Sustainable Development in Africa, Sunyani, 2017', 'I have spent the past 10years in the Renewable Energy space, both as an academic and an \r\nindustry player. My research, which focuses on Solar technology adoption and failure, plus \r\nmy experience in the solar industry in Ghana, has equipped me to take up this role', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING, HIKING, FOOTBALL', 'IMMEDIATELY', NULL, 'Prof. Gabriel Takyi', 'Professor, Head of Solar Research Lab, TBHEC, KNUST', 'Professor', 'PMB THE BREW-HAMMOND ENERGY CENTRE, COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING, KNUST', '0203802911', 'gabrieltakyi@yahoo.co.uk', 'Prof Samuel Gyamfi', 'PROFESSOR, DIRECTOR, RCEES, UENR', 'PROFESSOR', 'RCEES, University of Energy and Natural Resources', '0506438028', 'samuel.gyamfi@uenr.edu.gh', 'MR. FRANK ADABRE', 'SOLAR ENERGY BUSINESS PROFESSIONAL, NORTHLITE SOLAR LIMITED', 'CEO', 'NSL PLT 57, Water Aid Avenue. Kumbosigo', '0244412150', 'fadabre@northlitesolar.com', 'BTU_472A2B73_cv_6a1cbe7a0f3a45.20782192.pdf', 'Jacob Owusu_CV.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.109.29', '2026-05-31 23:04:26', '2026-06-12 23:42:36', 'BTU_472A2B73_photo_6a1cbe7a0f3a91.59079935.jpeg', 'JacobO_passport.jpeg'),
(220, 'BTU-FF1254B0', 15, 'Dr.', 'Ameyaw', 'Stephen', 'sameyaw@gmail.com', '0540533839', 'Presbyterian Church Of Ghana\r\nPost Office Box 174\r\nWa, Upper West Region\r\nTel. 0540533839\r\nEmail: sameyaw@gmail.com', 'Ashaiman', 'Kwahu-Obo', 'Upper West', 'Ghana', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'Glorious Safoa Ameyaw - 22/09/23\r\nJoyous Dunamis Ameyaw - 18/09/25', NULL, 'GHA-7225819075', '1985-10-12', 'male', 'PhD', 'University of Business &amp; Integrated Development Studies', 7, '1. Odame, F. S., &amp; Ameyaw, S. (2023). Complementary Basic Education Programme (CBE), As a Strategic School for Marginalised Children in the Nadowli-Kaleo District of Ghana. Concepts, Theories and Empirical Discourses, pp.39.\r\n2. Pufaa F.E., Odame, S.F. &amp; Ameyaw S. (2021). Social Structural Dysfunction in the Era of COVID-19; An Assessment of the Effects on Christian Churches in Ghana: A Case of the Presbyterian Church of Ghana. International Journal of Research and Innovation in Social Science (IJRISS) |Volume V, Issue II, February 2021|ISSN 2454-6186. \r\n3. Odame, F. S., &amp; Ameyaw, S. (2021). Revitalization of Ghanaian Higher Education Policies for Youth Employment using the Endogenous Model: A case study of UDS, Wa Campus. ADRRI Journal of Arts and Social Sciences, 17(8 (5)), 1-20.\r\n4. Gyader, G. &amp; Ameyaw S. (2019). Strategies for Preventing the Youth from Committing Crime in the Wa Municipality of the Upper West Region, Ghana. Africa Development and Resources Research Institute Journal, Ghana: Vol. 28, No. 7(5), Pp. 1-31, E-ISSN: 2343-6662, 30th June, 2019. Available at https://www.journals.adrri.org/ \r\n\r\n5. Ameyaw S. (2018). Social and Economic Factor Influencing youth unemployment to Crime in the Wa Municipality, Ghana. International Journal of Research Publication vol.4, 1-22. Available at http://ijrp.org/paper_detail/153 \r\n\r\n6. Odame S. F, &amp; Ameyaw S. (2018). E-Learning in Distance Education: An Innovative Strategy for Promoting Higher Education in Ghana. International Journal of Research Publication. Vol. 4, 1-20 Available at http://ijrp.org/paper_detail/154\r\n\r\n7. Ameyaw S. and Odame F. S (2017). The Menace of Open Defecation and Diseases in the Nadowli-Kaleo District of the Upper West Region, Ghana. International Journal of Scientific and Research Publications 7(12), 743-749. ISSN 2250-3153. Available at http://www.ijsrp.org/research-paper-1217.php?rp=P727090', 'I have an extensive research experience supporting evidence-based decision-making and strategic planning at the organizational level. I am skilled in designing, conducting, and analyzing qualitative and quantitative studies to inform policy, program development, and operational improvements. Experienced in preparing comprehensive reports, presentations, and recommendations for senior leadership, ensuring findings are actionable and aligned with institutional goals. Currently, I have seven published articles with a co-authored book chapter.  I am proficient in coordinating cross-departmental research initiatives, managing data collection and analysis, and overseeing project timelines. Recognized for applying analytical insights to drive organizational efficiency, improve outcomes, and support long-term strategic objectives. Adept at mentoring junior researchers and fostering a culture of inquiry and continuous improvement.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Researching, Reading &amp; Watching Football', 'Two Weeks', 'I am applying for the position of Assistant Registrar because I have a strong interest in academic administration and a passion for supporting the effective delivery of educational services. My experience in administrative work, and record management has equipped me with the skills needed to contribute positively to the institution\'s operations. I am particularly interested in this role because it offers the opportunity to support students, faculty, and management while ensuring that academic processes are carried out efficiently and accurately. I am confident that my organizational abilities, attention to detail, and commitment to professionalism will enable me to make a valuable contribution to the institution.', 'Prof. Sulemana Mohammed', 'Lecturer', 'Dean', 'The Dean \r\nUniversity of Business &amp; Integrated Development Studies\r\nFaculty of Public Policy and Governance\r\nPost Office Wa 64\r\nWa, Upper West Region', '0204500622', 'm.sulemana@ubids.edu.gh', 'Prof. Samuel Twumasi Amoah', 'Lecturer', 'Faculty Examination Officer', 'UBIDS', '0244664091', 'stamoah@ubids.edu.gh', 'Prof. Ernest Bagson', 'Lecturer', NULL, 'The HOD\r\nUBIDS\r\nDepartment of Public Policy\r\nP.O. Box WA 64', '0550791669', 'ebagson@ubids.edu.gh', 'BTU_FF1254B0_cv_6a1cfdea84f6a7.16907515.pdf', 'Stephen\'s CV-New-Admi (1).pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.246.165', '2026-06-01 03:35:06', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_FF1254B0_photo_6a1cfdea84f6e0.67173711.jpeg', 'WhatsApp Image 2026-05-27 at 4.56.36 AM.jpeg'),
(221, 'BTU-FF08025D', 15, 'Dr.', 'Ameyaw', 'Stephen', 'sameyaw@gmail.com', '0540533839', 'Presbyterian Church Of Ghana\r\nPost Office Box 174\r\nWa, Upper West Region\r\nTel. 0540533839\r\nEmail: sameyaw@gmail.com', 'Ashaiman', 'Kwahu-Obo', 'Upper West', 'Ghana', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'Glorious Safoa Ameyaw - 22/09/23\r\nJoyous Dunamis Ameyaw - 18/09/25', NULL, 'GHA-7225819075', '1985-10-12', 'male', 'PhD', 'University of Business &amp; Integrated Development Studies', 7, '1. Odame, F. S., &amp; Ameyaw, S. (2023). Complementary Basic Education Programme (CBE), As a Strategic School for Marginalised Children in the Nadowli-Kaleo District of Ghana. Concepts, Theories and Empirical Discourses, pp.39.\r\n2. Pufaa F.E., Odame, S.F. &amp; Ameyaw S. (2021). Social Structural Dysfunction in the Era of COVID-19; An Assessment of the Effects on Christian Churches in Ghana: A Case of the Presbyterian Church of Ghana. International Journal of Research and Innovation in Social Science (IJRISS) |Volume V, Issue II, February 2021|ISSN 2454-6186. \r\n3. Odame, F. S., &amp; Ameyaw, S. (2021). Revitalization of Ghanaian Higher Education Policies for Youth Employment using the Endogenous Model: A case study of UDS, Wa Campus. ADRRI Journal of Arts and Social Sciences, 17(8 (5)), 1-20.\r\n4. Gyader, G. &amp; Ameyaw S. (2019). Strategies for Preventing the Youth from Committing Crime in the Wa Municipality of the Upper West Region, Ghana. Africa Development and Resources Research Institute Journal, Ghana: Vol. 28, No. 7(5), Pp. 1-31, E-ISSN: 2343-6662, 30th June, 2019. Available at https://www.journals.adrri.org/ \r\n\r\n5. Ameyaw S. (2018). Social and Economic Factor Influencing youth unemployment to Crime in the Wa Municipality, Ghana. International Journal of Research Publication vol.4, 1-22. Available at http://ijrp.org/paper_detail/153 \r\n\r\n6. Odame S. F, &amp; Ameyaw S. (2018). E-Learning in Distance Education: An Innovative Strategy for Promoting Higher Educati