(235, 'BTU-3ACB4048', 15, 'Mr.', 'Afful', 'Ebenezer  Junior', 'ebenebenjun@outlook.com', '+233245032650', 'Box OD 170,\r\n Odorkor.\r\nAccra.', 'Prestea', 'Agona Bobikuma', 'Central', 'Ghanaian', NULL, 'married', 'Ophelia Asantewaa Koranteng', 'Box OD 170, Odorkor, Accra.', 'Mercedez Akua Brakoa Afful - 03/12/2014\r\nObrempong Kwabna Afful -  18/06/2019\r\nOkatakyie Kwabena Kesse Afful - 04/10/2022\r\nAfua Anansewaa Koranteng Afful -02/08/2024', NULL, 'GHA-000317701-9', '1979-07-23', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'Akenten Appiah-Menka University of Skills Training and Entrepreneurial Development (AAMUSTED)', 11, 'RESEARCH &amp; CONFERENCE  Presentations \r\n1. Afful, E. J. (2025). Rethinking the ‘Chinese Restaurant Syndrome’: Addressing MSG Myths in Ghana Through Education and Emerging AI Solutions. \r\n\r\n2. Afful, E. J. (2025). Positioning Student Innovation for the AI Era: Browning-Free Cassava Powder Production as a Launchpad for Intelligent Postharvest Solutions.', 'My experience as Manager of Late Success Enterprise has equipped me with strong administrative, managerial, and organizational competencies that are directly relevant to the role of Assistant Registrar. Over the years, I have supervised personnel, coordinated daily operations, managed records and documentation, prepared reports, monitored budgets, and ensured compliance with organizational policies and regulatory requirements. The role has required effective communication with clients, suppliers, and other stakeholders, as well as the ability to plan, coordinate, and resolve administrative matters efficiently. These responsibilities have strengthened my leadership, decision-making, record management, and interpersonal skills, all of which are essential for supporting institutional administration, governance processes, and service delivery within a university environment.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading and research\r\nCommunity service and volunteer activities\r\nMentoring young people and students\r\nTravelling and cultural exploration\r\nInformation and communication technology (ICT) learning', 'Immediately', 'While my academic qualifications are rooted in Hospitality, Tourism, and Education, the knowledge and skills acquired through these disciplines are highly transferable to university administration. My postgraduate training has strengthened my capabilities in management, communication, research, planning, problem-solving, and organizational leadership, while my professional experience has provided practical expertise in administration, records management, staff supervision, report writing, stakeholder engagement, and operational coordination. These experiences have prepared me to function effectively in a dynamic institutional environment. I am confident in my ability to quickly assimilate administrative procedures, uphold the highest standards of professionalism and integrity, and make a meaningful contribution to the efficient administration and strategic objectives of the University.', 'Dr. Yaa M. Akubia', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer, Dept. of Hospitality &amp; Tourism Management, AAMUSTED', 'Dr. Yaa M. Akubia - Senior Lecturer, Dept. of Hospitality &amp; Tourism Management, AAMUSTED.', '+233 244 896 857', 'yaa.akubia1@outlook.com', 'Mr. Eric Edem Mensah', 'Lecturere', 'Lecturer, Department of Hotel Catering and Institutional Management. Accra Technical University', 'Eric Edem Mensah\r\nDepartment of Hotel Catering and Institutional Management\r\nAccra Technical University', '+233 245415211', 'eemensah@atu.edu.gh', 'Mr. Benjamin Ansong', 'X&#039;tep Computer Ent.', 'Operations Director', 'Xtep Computer, Accra\r\nP O BOX OD 170\r\nODORKOR,\r\nACCRA.', '+233 053 026 8015', NULL, 'BTU_3ACB4048_cv_6a1db037a72db3.79380696.pdf', 'A.Afful_MPhil Certificate .pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.137.197', '2026-06-01 16:15:51', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_3ACB4048_photo_6a1db037a72e03.13610884.jpg', 'AFFUL PASSPORT PICTURE.jpg'),
(236, 'BTU-3005957E', 15, 'Ms.', 'Ayamba', 'Grace', 'igraceayamba@yahoo.com', '0242259440', 'Holy Angels Parish, Box 172\r\nGaru-Bawku \r\nUpper East.', 'Tempane', 'Tempane', 'Upper East', 'Ghanian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Ibrahim Adams', 'Bessfa Rural Bank Ltd 160', 'Mabel Azumah Ibrahim', 'POOOO557110', 'GHA-715482968-2', '1980-06-20', 'female', 'Other', 'University of Cape Coast.', 11, '1. Factors that influence people choice on insurance products in Bolgatanga Municipality in Fulfilment of my Master of Business Administration (MARKETING) .\r\n2. Employee motivation in a case study on Asokore Rural Bank, as part of a partial fulfillment of my Bachelor Degree in Business Administration. (Human Resource Management).', NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '1. Reading of story books\r\n2. Singing\r\n3. Sporting activities', '1 week after notification.', NULL, 'Ibrahim Adams', 'Banker', 'Credit Manager', 'Bessfa Rural Bank Plc\r\nBox 160 Garu', '0244369499', 'ibrahimadams1@gmail.com', 'Emmanuel Pedro', 'Doctor', 'Lecturer', 'University of Cape Coast\r\nPost Office Box 5007\r\nCape Coast-Ghana', '0244782178', 'Padro33@gmail.com', 'Laari Alice', 'Banker', 'Cash Manager', 'Stanbic Bank\r\nBolgatanga-Ghana', '0244939887', 'Laarialice@gmail.com', 'BTU_3005957E_cv_6a1db388c168c6.72873307.pdf', 'GRACE CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.230.60', '2026-06-01 16:30:00', '2026-06-01 16:30:00', 'BTU_3005957E_photo_6a1db388c16906.30844250.jpeg', 'AYMG.jpeg'),
(237, 'BTU-843289C0', 10, 'Mr.', 'Seidu', 'Nelson Abuba', 'nelsonseidu1995@gmail.com', '+233 241513802', 'A37\r\nAF8560365', 'Sumnibomah no. 1 A37', 'Sumnibomah no. 1 A37', 'North East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-715350173-4', 'GHA-715350173-4', '1995-09-29', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'C.K Tedam University of Technology and Applied Sciences', 3, '1.	Abuba, N. S., Baagyere, E. Y., Nakpih, C. I., &amp; Wiredu, J. K. (2025). OptiFlexSort: A Hybrid Sorting Algorithm for Efficient Large-Scale Data Processing. Journal of Advances in Mathematics and Computer Science, 40(2), 67–81. https://doi.org/10.9734/jamcs/2025/v40i21970\r\n2.	Wiredu, J. K., Abuba, N. S., &amp; Acheampong, R. W. (2024). Enhancing Accessibility and Engagement in Computer Science Education for Diverse Learners. Asian Journal of Research in Computer Science, 17(10), 45-61.\r\n3.	Wiredu, J. K., Abuba, N. S., Atiyire, B., &amp; Acheampong, R. W. (2024). Design and Implementation of Online Crime Report System using Rapid Application Development (RAD) Methodology. Asian Journal of Research in Computer Science, 17(8), 100-115.\r\n4.	Wiredu, J. K., Seidu Abuba, N., &amp; Zakaria, H. (2024). Impact of generative AI in academic integrity and learning outcomes: a case study in the upper east region. Asian Journal of Research in Computer Science, 17(8), 10-9734.\r\n5.	Wiredu, J. K., Atiyire, B., Abuba, N. S., &amp; Acheampong, R. W. (2024). Efficiency Analysis and Optimization Techniques for Base Conversion Algorithms in\r\nComputational Systems. International Journal of Innovative Science and\r\nResearch Technology, 9, 235-244.\r\n6.	Akobre¹, S., Wiredu, J. K., Aabaah, I., &amp; Abuba?, N. S. (2026). From Diffusion Models to Instruction-Tuned LLMs: A Unified Taxonomy and Trend Analysis of Generative AI. Asian Journal of Computer Science and Technology, 15(1), 55-70.', 'My academic qualifications, teaching experience, research background, and professional engagements closely align with the requirements of a Lectureship position in the Department of Computing and Information Technology. I currently serve as a Lecturer at Regentropfen University College and a Part-Time Assistant Lecturer at Bolgatanga Technical University, where I teach a broad range of computing and information technology courses, including Computer Organization and Architecture, Systems Analysis and Design, Data Structures and Algorithms, Database Management Systems, Computer Networks, Data Communication, Routing and Switching Technologies, and Computer Hardware and Software Technologies. These teaching responsibilities have equipped me with extensive knowledge and practical experience across core areas of computing and information technology. Additionally, my Master of Philosophy in Computer Science, ongoing PhD studies in Computer Science, and research interests in Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Structures and Algorithms, and Embedded Systems demonstrate my commitment to advancing knowledge in the field. Furthermore, my published research works and administrative experience as an Assistant Examination Officer have strengthened my research, leadership, assessment, and academic management capabilities, making me well-positioned to contribute effectively to teaching, research, curriculum development, and community service within the Department of Computing and Information Technology.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, Listening to Preachers.', '1 month', NULL, 'Dr. James Konjaang Kok', 'Lecturer', 'Head Of Department for Computing &amp; Information Technology, BTU.', 'Post Office Box 767 Sumburungu, Bolgatanga Ghana.', '0243743851', 'mc@bolgatu.edu.gh', 'Prof Edward Y. Baagyere', 'Lecturer', 'Dean, school of Computing and Information Sciences, UTAS, Navrongo', 'P.O Box Box 24 Navrongo, \r\nUpper East Region', '0249990362', 'ebaagyere@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Mr. Wiredu Kodua Japheth', 'Lecturer', 'Programmes Coordinator, Regentropfen University College', 'RUC Private Mail Bag\r\nGhana-Upper East Region', '0246099007', 'japheth.wiredu@regentropfen.edu.gh', 'BTU_843289C0_cv_6a1db49be3b5a2.37027651.pdf', 'Curriculum Vitae.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.120.12', '2026-06-01 16:34:35', '2026-06-12 23:33:06', 'BTU_843289C0_photo_6a1db49be3b5e0.60268320.jpg', 'Picture4.jpg'),
(238, 'BTU-B4025285', 2, 'Mr.', 'Asabea', 'Abdulrahman', 'asbea41@gmail.com', '0542763118', 'Scripture Union, P. O. Box 3064, Kumasi, Ashanti Region', 'Kumasi', 'Sumbrungu', 'Upper East', 'Ghana', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-003658439-0', '1989-05-10', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology', 2, NULL, 'My experience in quality assurance within a tertiary institution involved auditing end-of-semester examinations, course outlines, and teaching materials to promote high academic standards and effective teaching.  In my academic journey I have acquired considerable knowledge of Computer Information Management, particularly in Electronic Commerce, Database Management, etc. which equips me to engage students with contemporary digital and business related technological concepts.  Additionally, my legal training and entrepreneurship oriented qualifications as well position to deliver quality instruction and practical, industry-relevant learning experiences in entrepreneurship course and law related courses.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, NULL, 'Immediately', NULL, 'Dr. Enye Besa Ameza-Xemalordza', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology, Department of Marketing and Corporate Strategy', '0559226000', 'xemalordzo88@gmail.com', 'Dr. Chilala Osman', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Bolgatanga Technical University\r\nP. O. Box 767\r\nBolgatanga', '0201282003', 'chilalaosman@gmail.com', 'Mr. Rockson Antwi', 'Manager', 'Ashanti Regional Manager', 'Scripture Union, P. O. 3064, Kumasi', '0243472851', 'antwirockson@rocket.com', 'BTU_B4025285_cv_6a1dc6b9afb092.76820468.pdf', 'ASABEA ADBULRAHMAN CV Jk3.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '102.176.65.96', '2026-06-01 17:51:53', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_B4025285_photo_6a1dc6b9afb0e8.98333806.jpg', 'Asabea Passport.jpg'),
(239, 'BTU-6DA3AAC2', 1, 'Dr.', 'Cudjoe', 'Alfred', 'Cudjoealfred@yahoo.com', '+233249741970', 'UPPER EAST REGIONAL HOSPITAL\r\nBox 26, BOLGATANGA', 'Enchi', 'Enchi', 'Western North', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Elizabeth Cudjoe', 'Box 285 Kongo, Nabdam, Upper East Region', 'Eba Akwasi Cudjoe Junior', NULL, 'GHA-715695104-2', '1979-03-06', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'KNUST', 11, NULL, 'My fourteen years’ experience of medical Laboratory practice and ten years’ experience as Physician Assistant should be very useful and of interest to a reputable University like yours. In various capacities in Medical Laboratory practice with the Ghana health service in the Upper East Region leading to my present assignment as Principal medical Laboratory Scientist, I have acquired adequate skill and knowledge in all aspects of medical Laboratory practice in Ghana. \r\n\r\nThe major aspects of Laboratory practice that I am well vest in include the following; Haematology, Blood transfusion sciences, Chemical pathology (clinical chemistry), Bacteriology, Parasitology, Virology, Mycology and Laboratory Management. \r\nI also have qualification, knowledge, skills and experience in public health and Physician Assistantship which I would not hesitate to use if I am given the opportunity. I am currently pursuing a Master of Public Health program in Epidemiology and Statistics at UTAS with intended research in Prevalence of Anaemia and Occupational Safety Practices Among Illegal Small-Scale Gold Miners in the Talensi and the Nabdam district of the Upper East Region. I am very confident that I can contribute immensely to the quality and growth of your institution', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading\r\nComputer programming or coding \r\nTeaching', 'one month', 'ACADEMIC PROJECTS  \r\n\r\n1. Factors influencing blood transfusion reactions in the Upper East Region \r\n\r\n2. Osteometric measurements of Ghanaian males at the KNUST anatomy Department \r\n\r\n3. Factors influencing insecticide treated nets usage in the Asutuare community, Greater Accra region.\r\n\r\n4. Worm infestation in the Psychiatric Patients at the Accra Psychiatric Hospital \r\n\r\n5. Prevalence of Anaemia and Occupational Safety Practices Among Illegal Small-Scale Gold Miners in the Talensi and the Nabdam district of the Upper East Region\r\n\r\n\r\nSKILLS\r\n\r\n1.	Microscopy and Medical Laboratory Procedures \r\n2.	Management Skills \r\n3.	Research skills \r\n4.	Data Analysis with SPSS, Python, R language, power bi, Google looker  \r\n5.	Productivity computer software: MS word, Excel, PowerPoint\r\n6.	Abdominopelvic Ultrasound Scanning\r\n7.	Communication Skills', 'Dr. Mrs. Lilian Antwi Boateng', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'College of Health Sciences, KNUST', '0538985608', NULL, 'Dr. Emmanuel Adongo', 'Biomedical Scientist', 'Regional Biomedical Scientist', 'Regional Health Directorate, Bolgatanga', '0201685007 / 0244839', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_6DA3AAC2_cv_6a1dc731ee3290.42158876.pdf', 'CV-BTU.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.249.176', '2026-06-01 17:53:53', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_6DA3AAC2_photo_6a1dc731ee32f6.29521812.jpg', '8. IMG_0568-removebg-preview.jpg'),
(240, 'BTU-3F640C5E', 15, 'Ms.', 'Jakpa', 'Yvonne Faata', 'marilotte67@gmail.com', '0546712355', 'Navrongo Senior High School \r\nP 0 Box 33\r\nNavrongo', 'Bimbilla', 'Cheriponi', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Gregory K Pelig-Ba', 'UTAS', 'Cheryl Yinmalti Pelig-Ba (17/01/2017)\r\nGwenaelle Bout-Taba Pelig-Ba (26/11/2019)\r\nMirrielle Chiara Bulsongma Pelig-Ba \r\n(29/09/2024)', 'P0025484486', 'Gha-715136475-1', '1986-07-07', 'female', 'Professional Certificate', 'Chartered Institute of Administrators and Management Consultants-Ghana', 11, NULL, 'Relevance \r\n\r\nMy background in teaching English Language has directly prepared me for the Assistant Registrar role, where accuracy, organization, and compliance are key. Through maintaining detailed student records, processing scores, and submitting regular academic reports to administration and parents, I developed the data management and documentation skills needed to handle student transcripts, registration, matriculation, graduation clearance, and records in a university registry. Coordinating assessments, invigilation, and adherence to WAEC procedures strengthened my ability to support examination administration and ensure regulatory compliance throughout the academic cycle. My consistent collaboration with colleagues, parents, and management also honed my communication and stakeholder liaison skills, which are essential for serving students and faculty while upholding university policies.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading \r\nTravelling', 'Immediately', 'experience gained through my roles with the Ghana Statistical Service PHC 2021, where I supervised field enumerators and served as both Regional and National Trainer, developing and delivering CAPI-based training to staff at multiple levels. My internships at Tamale Metropolitan Assembly’s HR Unit and Savana Signatures’ M&amp;E Unit equipped me with skills in recruitment, staff induction, data collection and entry, analysis, and report writing. I have also mentored students on technology use for research and article writing, and completed professional training in research, M&amp;E, office procedure, accounting, financial management, and school records. Collectively, this experience has strengthened my capabilities in staff supervision, capacity building, data management, and administrative compliance, all core to the Assistant Registrar role.', 'Prof. Ibrahim Mohammed Gunu', 'Lecturer', 'Dean. Faculty of Education. UDS', 'University For Development Studies\r\nFaculty of Education \r\nP. O. Box TL 1350, Tamale, Ghana. ', 'Tel: 0208887590', 'igunu@uds,edu.gh', 'Prof. Moomin Abu', 'Lecturer', 'Senior lecturer. School of Public Health', 'University For Development Studies\r\nFaculty of Agriculture \r\nP. O. Box TL 1350, Tamale, Ghana', '0244849469', 'moonabu@yahoo.com', 'Salifu Abubakar (PHD)', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer. Faculty of Agriculture       UDS', 'University for Development Studies \r\nSchool of Public \r\n P O. Box TL 1350, Tamale, Ghana UDS, Tamale', '0244540547', 'a.salifu@uds.edu.gh', 'BTU_3F640C5E_cv_6a1dc76dd31cc5.49961535.pdf', 'YVONNE FAATA JAKPA COVER LETTER.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.241.51', '2026-06-01 17:54:53', '2026-06-01 17:54:53', 'BTU_3F640C5E_photo_6a1dc76dd31d14.25045378.jpg', 'IMG-20250920-WA0012(1).jpg'),
(241, 'BTU-9FC6153D', 4, 'Mr.', 'CHARLES', 'KODUAH ATTA', 'imacodua00@gmail.com', '0243235642', 'PRESBYTERIAN SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL, BECHEM\r\n\r\nPOST OFFICE BOX 81', 'KUMASI', 'KUMAWU', 'Ashanti', 'GHANAIAN', NULL, 'married', 'DOROTHY NYAMEAMA AGYEMANG', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-715909766-8', '1991-01-17', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'KWAME NKRUMAH UNIVERSITY OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY', 7, 'Are They AI-Literate? Exploring The Impact Of Generative AI Literacy On Academic Performance Among Ghanaian University Students.&quot; EDITORS: Eric Appau Asante (2025): 136.\r\n\r\nDigital Literacy, Creative Thinking Disposition, And Generative Artificial Intelligence Literacy as Predictors of Academic Performance: A PLS-SEM, IPMA, and NCA Study of Pre-Service Visual Arts Teachers in Ghana.https://doi.org/10.31235/osf.io/3t6ry_v1\r\n\r\n Digital Literacy and Academic Performance in Visual Arts Teacher Education in Ghana.', 'With over seven years of dedicated teaching experience in Visual Art at the senior high school level, I have delivered engaging a student-centred lesson in Textiles, General Knowledge in Art, Art and Design Studio, and Art and Design Foundation. As a subject head for textiles since 2019, I lead in planning of lesson notes, teacher coordination, resource procurement, and examination processes and while integrating ICT tools such as Google Docs, Adobe Photoshop, Microsoft office, Quizzes to create interactive lessons and digital assessment that consistently yield strong WASSCE results. Simultaneously, as a Form Master, I provide comprehensive pastoral care, monitor over 40 students annually, and uphold high standards of discipline and personal development \r\nI am in my third year of a PhD in Art Education at KNUST, which is an ongoing program that I am taking to keep improving my teaching.  I also fully participate in all NTC workshops and conferences on mental health, cybersecurity, and effective teaching to improve my teaching.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'reading and designing', 'Immediately', NULL, 'Proferssor Harry Barton Essel', 'Lecturing', 'Senior Lecturer', NULL, '+233 243723276', 'hbessel.knust.eist@gmail.com', 'Dr. (Mrs.) Akosua Tachie-Menson', 'Lecturing', 'Senior Lecturer', NULL, '0208161291', 'atmenson.art@knust.edu.gh', 'Mr. Adjeman-Badu Reginald', 'Teaching', 'Assitant Headmaster Administration', NULL, '+233 243352590', 'badukgh@gmail.com', 'BTU_9FC6153D_cv_6a1dce5591b4b9.52880026.pdf', 'CV_Charles_Atta_Koduah.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.242.57', '2026-06-01 18:24:21', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_9FC6153D_photo_6a1dce5591b503.54527374.jpg', 'IMG-20191009-WA0010.jpg'),
(242, 'BTU-1F5FF8C6', 15, 'Mr.', 'Imoro', 'Abdulai', 'abdulimo87@gmail.com', '+233248202040', 'Post Office Box 1342, Tamale', 'Tampion', 'Savelugu', 'Northern', 'Ghanaian', 'Islam', 'married', 'Maina Alhassan', 'Bilsitua Residential B.Blk. A 165', '1. Mardiyya Wunzaligu - 5th July 2015\r\n\r\n2. Raahat Faako Abdulai - 26th July 2018\r\n\r\n3. Nabeel Jilma Abdulai - 12th October 2021\r\n\r\n4. Suabir Suglo Abdulai - 13th October 2021\r\n\r\n5. Ikhlas Wun-nam Abdulai - 28th July 2025', NULL, 'GHA-714483257-3', '1987-05-27', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'University for Development Studies', 11, NULL, 'I have in the last 12 years worked with many Non-Governmental Organizations and acquired requisite knowledge, experience and competences necessary to serve as Assistant Registrar. I have worked as subordinate and supervisor alike, taking instructions and guiding teams to deliver impactful results. As Regional Project Manager for School for Life I led and supervised 33 field team members and that experience is necessary for the Assistant Registrar position. I have deepened my understanding of education policy and advocacy which positions me to support the University, particularly the registry in engaging Government and development partners on policy issues affecting the school.\r\nMy undergraduate research focused on job satisfaction among teachers in Cape Coast Municipality and my MSc term paper was on factors influencing strategic planning and implementation among NGOs in Northern Ghana. These experiences are relevant for people management and long-term goal settings for the University. \r\nI have intermediate computer literacy skills and familiar with applications such as Microsoft office suites, zoom, google docs, teams among others which are relevant for managing correspondence and communication within the University community.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading books on politics and governance in Africa\r\n\r\nPlaying games with my family', '2 weeks', NULL, 'Amadu Zulyaden', 'Development Work', 'Project Manager', 'School for Life, Post Office Box 787, Tamale', '0555082455', 'zulyaden@schoolforlifegh.org', 'Bright Sowu', 'Development Work', 'Head of Programmes', 'Ghana Anti-Corruption Coalition, Accra', '0242671069', 'brightsowu@yahoo.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_1F5FF8C6_cv_6a1df145a3cfa7.30212593.pdf', 'Imoro Abdulai _Updated CV_Assistant Registrar BTU.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.177.152', '2026-06-01 20:53:25', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_1F5FF8C6_photo_6a1df145a3d002.96781897.jpg', 'Passport pp - Imoro - Red BG.jpg'),
(243, 'BTU-AE797E4F', 1, 'Mr.', 'Jannabi', 'Enoch', 'ejannabi@gmail.com', '+233543410648', NULL, 'Mampong-Ashanti', 'Kuobore', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-716154737-5', '1995-03-01', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences, Navrongo', 0, NULL, 'My academic background in MPhil Biochemistry and Molecular Biomedicine makes me a strong fit for a lecturer position within the Department of Medical Laboratory Science. Throughout my training, I have built myself in areas such as clinical biochemistry, molecular diagnostic methods, laboratory procedures, and biomedical research practices. \r\nThe focus of my research was on measuring ferritin concentrations in pregnant women and exploring its predictive value for cardiovascular risks during gestation. This topic has direct relevance to Medical Laboratory Science, as ferritin is a critical biochemical indicator applied in diagnosing conditions, monitoring patient progress, and assessing health risks. Research in the field gave me practical exposure to core laboratory skills: collecting samples, conducting investigations, analysing biomarkers, interpreting results, and correlating findings with clinical relevance. It also highlighted the crucial role of laboratory science in identifying diseases early and supporting preventive health strategies.\r\nIn addition to my research background, I am well positioned to teach subjects including clinical chemistry, molecular diagnostics etc. The combination of my laboratory experience and research work has enhanced my analytical skills, scientific writing, and ability to teach effectively. This makes me capable of contributing meaningfully to teaching, learning, and research within the Department of Medical Laboratory Science', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, NULL, '1 month', 'Certificate for my Master\'s Degree (MPhil.) is currently unavailable. Graduation is within this month of June.', 'Dr. Godfred Agongo', 'Lecturing', 'Head of Department, Biochemistry and Forensic Sciences, University of Technology and Applied Science', NULL, '0244877741 or 050298', 'gagongo@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Prof. Thomas N. Tindan', 'Lecturing', 'Head of Department, Science Education, University of Technology and Applied Sciences, Navrongo', NULL, '0244980178 or 020551', 'ttindana@cktutas.edu.gh', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_AE797E4F_cv_6a1df3e02ee6b2.94508830.pdf', 'CV _Enoch Jannabi.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.126.225', '2026-06-01 21:04:32', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_AE797E4F_photo_6a1df3e02ee718.51021566.jpg', 'IMG_20210902_072020_724.jpg'),
(244, 'BTU-96783D99', 8, 'Dr.', 'EMMANUEL', 'ANYIGBAH', 'eanyigbah@gmail.com', '+233552070800', 'CC-187-5465, AKOTOKYIRE, CAPE COAST, CENTRAL REGION.', 'Kumasi', 'Tegbi - Volta Region', 'Volta', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Stella Osei Boateng', 'CC-187-5465, AKOTOKYIRE, CAPE COAST, CENTRAL REGION.', 'Ayden Eli Anyigbah - 06/11/2019', NULL, 'GHA-731254311-9', '2026-04-22', 'male', 'PhD', 'Jiangsu University, P.R. China.', 5, '[1.] Anyigbah, E., Kong, Y., Edziah, B. K., Ahoto, A. T., &amp; Ahiaku, W. S. (2023). Board Characteristics and Corporate Sustainability Reporting: Evidence from Chinese Listed Companies. Sustainability, 15(4), 3553. SCI), Q2.  \r\n[2.] Anyigbah, E., Kong, Y., Ahoto, A. T., &amp; Ahiaku, W. S. (2021). The Impact of Executive Compensation on Banking Performance: Evidence from the Ghanaian Banking Crises. Open Access Library Journal, 8(10), 1-13. Peer Reviewed  \r\n[3.]  Edziah, B. K., Sun, H., Anyigbah, E., Gyamfi, B., &amp; Asongu, S. A. (2025). Energy efficiency in times of geopolitical uncertainty: A global analysis across income levels. Energy Efficiency, SCI, Q2.  \r\n[4.]  Edziah, B. K., Anyigbah, E., Gyamfi, B., &amp; Asongu, S. A. (2025). Green total factor energy efficiency gap in Africa: exploring the role of technology, human resources, and institutions. Energy &amp; Environment, SCI, Q2.  \r\n[5.] Ahoto, A. T., Mbaye, M. B., &amp; Anyigbah, E. (2022). The Impacts of Learner-Instructor Interaction, Learner Learner, Learner-Content Interaction, Internet Self-Efficacy and Self-Regulated Learning on Satisfaction of Online Education of African Medical Students. Open Access Library Journal, 9(9), 1-16. Peer Reviewed  \r\n[6.] Edziah, B. K., Sun, H., Anyigbah, E., &amp; Li, L. (2021). Assessment of Short-and Long-Run Energy Efficiency: Evidence from 141 Countries. Studies of Applied Economics, 39(8). Peer Reviewed  \r\n[7.] Edziah, B. K., Sun, H., Anyigbah, E., &amp; Li, L. (2021). Human capital and energy efficiency: Evidence from developing countries. American Journal of Industrial and Business Management,11, 599-610. Peer Reviewed \r\n[8.] Yusheng, K., &amp; Anyigbah, E. (2019). The Impact of Board Structure on\r\n Firm Performance: Evidence from the Nonfinancial Companies Listed on Ghana Stock Exchange. Research Journal of Finance and Accounting, ISSN 2222-1697 (Paper) ISSN 2222-2847 (Online) DOI: 10.7176/RJFA. Peer Reviewed', 'Dr. Emmanuel Anyigbah is an excellent fit for the role of Accounting Lecturer due to my strong combination of academic excellence, industry experience, and research expertise. With 4years of university-level teaching experience and over five years of professional accounting and finance practice, I bring both theoretical depth and practical industry relevance into the classroom at GCTU. My specialisation in corporate sustainability/ESG, corporate governance, financial reporting, and accounting data analytics positions me to contribute meaningfully to modern accounting education and curriculum development. In addition, my international research exposure, publications in reputable journals, and passion for student development make me well-suited to support the Department\'s goals in teaching, research, and academic innovation.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Playing Table Tennis and Watching Movies', 'Immediately', NULL, 'PROF. KONG YUSHENG', 'lecturing', 'Fmr. Dean of School of Finance &amp; Economics, Jiangsu University, P.R. China.', 'JIANGSU UNIVERSITY, XUEFU ROAD 301, ZHENJIANG', '(+86) 139 5287 7918', 'yshskong@ujs.edu.cn', 'PROF.  OWUSU SAMUEL MENSAH', 'Lecturering', 'Lecturer', 'Jinggangshan University, Qingyuan District, Ji’an City, Jiangxi Province, P.R. China.', '0545931086 / (+86) 1', 'E-mail: omensju15@yahoo.com / 9020180003@jgsu.edu.cn', 'DR. OPPONG KWABENA', 'Lecturering', 'Lecturer', 'HO Technical University, \r\nHO, Volta Region, Ghana.', 'E-mail: poppong@htu.', '0244274848', 'BTU_96783D99_cv_6a1e035a35a574.53280732.pdf', 'CV- Emmanuel Anyigbah.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '179.64.71.124', '2026-06-01 22:10:34', '2026-06-13 00:05:13', 'BTU_96783D99_photo_6a1e035a35a5b7.05401446.jpg', 'Passport Photo.jpg'),
(245, 'BTU-D317F19F', 3, 'Mr.', 'YAKUBU', 'PAUL SEIDU', 'pseiduyakubu@gmail.com', '0246523715', 'C/O POST OFFICE BOX 176,  BOLGATANGA, U/E/R.', 'TECHIMAN', 'BINABA', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'ISLAM', 'married', 'YAKUBU HAMDIA', 'C/O POST OFFICE BOX 176,  BOLGATANGA, U/E/R.', 'KUBADU NAJAT-4TH JUNE, 2005\r\nKUBADU UMAR-29TH JULY, 2009\r\nKUBADU RAMADAN-5TH JULY, 2015\r\nKUBADU ABDUL-BASIT-13TH AUGUST, 2018', 'P0008302251', 'GHA-715808041-0', '1984-08-04', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES', 11, 'EVALUATION OF COWPEA (Vigna unguiculata) GENOTYPES FOR RESISTANCE TO ANTHRACNOSE CAUSED BY Colletotrichum lindemuthianum.', 'My theses work on \'Evaluation of Cowpea (Vigna unguiculata) Genotypes for Resistance to Anthracnose caused by Colletotrichum lindemuthianum\'  is directly relevant to my role as an Agricultural Science Lecturer because it enhances my expertise in plant pathology, crop improvement, and sustainable crop production. I have acquired knowledge that will help me contribute to teaching, student supervision, research publication, and community outreach. Ultimately, the study will contribute to food security, agricultural innovation, and the training of future agricultural professionals. Moreover, I have gained valuable teaching experience at the pre-tertiary level, where I have had the privilege of guiding and inspiring Senior High students in agricultural science. This experience equips me with skills to deliver lessons effectively by combining theory with practical applications to make learning impactful.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Listening to Quranic recitation, Research, Planting of trees, Crop Farming,	Gardening', 'Immediately', NULL, '1.	Professor Frederick Kankam', 'Lecturer', 'Head of Department, Agricultural Biotechnology', 'University for Development Studies, Nyankpala', '0548689158', 'fkankam@uds.edu.gh', 'Mr. Abu Dauda Dasmani', 'Teacher', 'Assistant Headmaster', 'Bolgatanga Senior School, \r\nBox 176\r\nBolgatanga.', '+233 243415567', 'abudaudaisdah@gmail.com', 'Mr. Abdulai Bukari', 'Teacher', 'Headmaster', 'Bawku Senior High/Technical School, Bawku.', '+233 209748644', 'bukariab@yahoo.com', 'BTU_D317F19F_cv_6a1e0c6ca5f697.21815852.pdf', 'YAKUBU P. SEIDU\'s CV + Certs BTU.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.239.180', '2026-06-01 22:49:16', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_D317F19F_photo_6a1e0c6ca5f6e5.77342562.jpg', 'pasport1.jpg'),
(246, 'BTU-84447758', 2, 'Mr.', 'Akumbobe', 'Adombire Robert', 'adombire2023@gmail.com', '+233244180724', 'Gambibgo Community Day SHS\r\nC\\O Bolgatanga East GES Office\r\nPost Office Box 224\r\nZuarugu', 'Zorko-Tarongo', 'Zorko-Tarongo', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Adubah  Atuabono Hellen', 'Bawku West District Hospital, Zebilla', 'Adombire Israella Awinsum Akumbobe 8/10/2013\r\nAdombire Reuel Atariwine Akumbobe  13/09/2018\r\nAdombire Miracles Winetum Akumbobe 27/10/2023', NULL, 'GHA-715645061-9', '1982-04-11', 'male', 'PhD', 'University of Technology and Applied sciences', 3, '1. 	Adombire Akumbobe, R., Abonongo, A. I. L., and Nasiru, S. (2025). New Quantile 	Regression Model for Unit Interval Regressands. Engineering Reports, 7(10), e70420.\r\n\r\n2.	Akumbobe, Robert Adombire, Abonongo, Anuwoje Ida L., Nasiru, Suleman, Secant Unit 	Gompertz Quantile Regression for Modeling Bounded Endogenous Variables, 	Computational and Mathematical Methods, 2026, 4478398, 31 pages, 2026. 	https://doi.org/10.1155/cmm4/4478398.\r\n\r\n3. 	Adombire Akumbobe, R., Abonongo, A. I. L., and Nasiru, S. (2025). Tangent 	Transformed Continuous Bernoulli Quantile Regression Model with Application to Cable 	TV Penetration and Educational datasets. Al-Bahir Journal for Engineering and Pure 	Sciences. Under Review.\r\n\r\n4.	Luguterah, A., Akumbobe, R. A., &amp; Yaan, E. A. (2015). Modelling exchange rate volatility of the 	Ghana cedi to the US dollar using GARCH models. Mathematical Theory and Modeling, 5(8), 92-	103.', 'My experience relates strongly with Liberal Studies through my proven background in teaching, research, student mentorship, and curriculum development.  As a PhD-qualified educator, I have consistently fostered critical thinking, effective communication, and problem-solving skills among diverse learners.  My record of scholarly research, publications, and learner-centered teaching demonstrates a commitment to academic excellence and interdisciplinary learning. This has positioned me to make meaningful contribution to student success and the broader goals of Liberal Studies.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'My hobby is reading academic and non-fiction literature. I also have deep interest in research and scholarly writing.', '2 weeks', NULL, '1.	Professor Suleman Nasiru', 'Lecturing', 'Former HOD, Department of Statistics and Actuarial  Science, UTAS.', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences (UTAS) \r\nDepartment of Statistics and Actuarial  Science\r\nP. O. Box 24\r\nNavrongo, Upper East Region\r\nGhana', '0246609024', 'Sulemanstat@gmail.com', 'Dr. (Mrs) Ida Abonongo', 'Lecturing', 'Senior Lecturer, UTAS', 'University of Technology and Applied Sciences  \r\nDepartment of Statistics and Actuarial  Science\r\nP. O. Box 24\r\nNavrongo, Upper East Region\r\nGhana', '0546360456', 'ilogubayom@cktutas.edu.gh', 'Madam Jualina Abaazesi', 'Teaching', 'Assistant Head Administration, Gambibgo Community Day SHS', 'Gambibgo Community Day SHS\r\nC\\O Bolgatanga East GES Office\r\nPost Office Box 224\r\nZuarugu', '0244139778', NULL, 'BTU_84447758_cv_6a1e12feb500c9.73033962.pdf', 'Curriculum Vitae Robert Adombire Akumbobe.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.124.234', '2026-06-01 23:17:18', '2026-06-01 23:17:18', 'BTU_84447758_photo_6a1e12feb50143.93045047.jpeg', 'My Official Photo.jpeg'),
