(276, 'BTU-CE2433F0', 3, 'Mr.', 'Tahidu', 'Thomas', 'ttahidu210@yahoo.com', '+233242876087', 'First Baptist church Box 1 Tamale', 'Tamale', 'Tamale', 'Northern', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'P0047221704', 'GHA715901825-4', '1989-07-06', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology', 3, NULL, 'My core strengths lie in water, climate, and agricultural systems, which are highly relevant to Agricultural Engineering, particularly in the areas of irrigation, hydrology, and resource management. These strengths are grounded in two complementary research pillars.\r\nFirst, my MSc research at Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology focused on climate change and food security among smallholder farmers in the Talensi District of Ghana. This work examined farmer systems, climate variability, and food production, and provided a strong foundation for applications in climate-smart irrigation, water use efficiency, and agricultural systems modeling.\r\nSecond, my ongoing MPhil research at the University for Development Studies (School of Engineering) investigates the effects of sand mining on sustainable water supply in the Nawuni sub-catchment of the White Volta River Basin. This study is closely aligned with hydrology, watershed management, and river system dynamics, with direct implications for water availability in agricultural production systems.\r\nMy training within an engineering faculty has further strengthened my quantitative, analytical, and systems-based problem-solving skills, positioning me well within the Agricultural Engineering field.\r\nIn addition, my work has provided me with valuable practical experience, including direct engagement with farmers in the Talensi District, extensive fieldwork within the White Volta Basin (Nawuni/Dalon), and a strong understanding of real-world water challenges in Northern Ghana. These experiences enable me to integrate theory with practice in both teaching and research.\r\nOverall, my research has strong potential for publication and contribution in the areas of water resource sustainability, climate resilience, and agricultural productivity.', 'yes', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '•	Social issues that enhance human dignity and development\r\n•	Listening to Gospel\r\n•	Reading novels\r\n•	Watching football', 'I will need one month notice to my current employer to resign with dignity and honor by following la', NULL, 'Professor Lydia Kwoyiga', 'Teaching, Lecturer University for development studies', 'Associate professor, Head of department and senior lecturer, school of engineering and department of', NULL, '+233244353595', 'lkwoyiga@uds.edu.gh', 'Dr. Zarouk Imoro Abubakari', 'Teaching-Lecturer', 'Senior lecturer and deputy head of department, school of engineering and department of environment, ', NULL, '+233242943931', 'zabubakari@uds.edu.gh', 'Dr. Richard Agyemang Osei', 'Teaching- Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer school of engineering and department of environment , water and waste engineering', NULL, '+233247425994', 'orichard@uds.edu.gh', 'BTU_CE2433F0_cv_6a1f731b763648.74402158.pdf', 'MSC. Certificate-KNUST.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.232.75', '2026-06-03 00:19:39', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_CE2433F0_photo_6a1f731b763689.57158723.jpeg', 'PASSPORT PICTURE.jpeg'),
(277, 'BTU-F20A03CB', 14, 'Mr.', 'Taapong', 'Francis Kavinaane', 'francis.taapong@yahoo.com', '0208024199', 'Box 24, University of technology and applied sciences (UTAS)-Navrongo', 'Jirapa-Tizza Boi', 'Tizza Boi', 'Upper West', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'None', 'P0031553796', 'GHA-715452874-9', '1991-03-27', 'male', 'WASSCE/SSSCE', 'Lawra senior  high school', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Playing football,vand watching movies', 'Immediately', 'No please', 'Iddrisu Suhaibu', 'Lecturing', 'Examinations officer', 'Box 24, UTAS- Navrongo', '0549963395', 'isuhaibu@uds.edu.gh', 'Olia Yaa Dogli', 'Accountant', 'Accountant', 'Box1589- Sunyani', '0245469348', 'olivewalks33@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_F20A03CB_cv_6a1f74ab294d51.72155381.pdf', 'certificate and nss cert.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '82.145.212.44', '2026-06-03 00:26:19', '2026-06-03 00:26:19', 'BTU_F20A03CB_photo_6a1f74ab294da6.35220112.jpg', 'IMG-20260316-WA0002.jpg'),
(278, 'BTU-2FD95979', 1, 'Mr.', 'Frimpong', 'Emmanuel Antwi Boasiako', 'eabfrimpong@gmail.com', '+233244965514', 'Upper East Regional Hospital\r\nP.O. Box 4\r\nBolgatanga', 'Kumasi', 'Akyem Sekyere', 'Eastern', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Sylvia Antwi Boasiako Frimpong', 'Upper East Regional Hospital, Box 4, Bolgatanga', 'Emsyl Antwi Frimpong- 17/12/2013\r\nEmmanuel Antwi Frimpong- 24/01/2016\r\nEleora Antwi Frimpong- 01/03/2018', 'P0005604915', 'GHA-723348364-8', '1982-11-11', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University For Development Studies', 11, '1.	Gyilbagr, F., Walana, W., Buunaaim, A. D. B., et al., Frimpong, E. A. B. (2025).\r\nBacterial isolates from orthopedic post-traumatic surgical infections in Northern Ghana: ES?L detection and antimicrobial resistance trends. International Journal of Microbiology. https://doi.org/10.1155/ijm/9949633\r\n2.	Ankrah, J. N. O., Gyilbagr, F., Vicar, E. K., Frimpong, E. A. B., et al. (2024).\r\nT-cell exhaustion, inflammatory and cellular activity markers predict treatment outcome in pulmonary tuberculosis. Cytokine, 182, 156708.', 'As an experienced Medical Laboratory Scientist and educator, my background directly aligns with the teaching, research, and service requirements of a university lecturer. I bring active tertiary teaching experience from my current role as a Part-Time Lecturer at Regentropfen University College, combined with over 15 years of hands-on clinical laboratory expertise. My academic qualifications, including an MPhil in Clinical Microbiology and status as a Doctor of Medical Laboratory Science (MLS.D) Candidate, provide the advanced theoretical grounding necessary to lecture and mentor health science students. Furthermore, my published research in peer-reviewed journals, advanced training in academic writing, and proven leadership as a Laboratory Manager and GAMLS Regional Chairman equip me to actively contribute to the department’s research output and administrative responsibilities.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Listening to music, Reading', '1 month', NULL, 'Dr. Williams Walana', 'Lecturer', 'Head of Department', 'University for Development Studies\r\nSchool of Medicine\r\nDepartment of Clinical Microbiology\r\nTamale', '0246774601', 'wwalana@uds.edu.gh', 'Dr. Emmanuel Adongo', 'Medical Laboratory Science', 'Regional Medical Laboratory Scientist', 'Regional Health Directorate\r\nBolgatanga\r\nUpper East Region', '0244839159', 'manueladongo@yaoo.co.uk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_2FD95979_cv_6a1f79dee682c8.19823654.pdf', 'CURRICULUM VITAE-EMMANUEL FRIMPONG - UPDATED.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.118.95', '2026-06-03 00:48:30', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_2FD95979_photo_6a1f79dee68301.52144609.jpg', 'PASSPORT PIC.jpg');
