(279, 'BTU-99F950AA', 2, 'Dr.', 'Raymond Kwame Adane', 'DARFO-ODURO', 'ray.oduro@yahoo.com', '+420770356577', 'Na brevnoske plani 1975/73\r\n169 00 Prague 6\r\nCzech Republic', 'Tokyo-Japan', 'Kwahu-Twenedurase', 'Eastern', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'married', 'Stella', 'Lamptey', 'Rayna Darfo-Oduro\r\nReagan Darfo-Oduro', NULL, 'GHA-729648879-0', '1980-09-27', 'male', 'PhD', 'University of Pardubice', 0, 'Ansong, D., Okumu, M., Kim, Y. K., Despard, M., &amp; Darfo-Oduro, R. (2019). Effects of education savings accounts on student engagement: Instrumental variable analysis. Global Social Welfare. Advance online  publication. https://doi.org/10.1007/s40609-019-00142-7 \r\n\r\nDarfo-Oduro, Raymond, Determinants of Residential House Rental Prices in Accra Metropolis (January 6, 2020). Available at SSRN: https://ssrn.com/abstract=3514560 or http://dx.doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.3514560\r\n  \r\nDarfo-Oduro, R. K. A., &amp; Stejskal, J. (2022, August). FDI Spillover Channel and its Effect on Innovation. In European Conference on Knowledge Management (Vol. 23, No. 1, pp. 289-296). \r\n\r\nArthur, E. E., Darfo-Oduro, R. K. A., Gyamfi, S., Sein, Y. Y., Stejskal, J., &amp; Prokop, V. (2022, December). Tax and Non-tax Policies Towards the Finance of Sustainable Economy: The Mediating Role of EcoInnovation. In Asia-Pacific Conference on Economics &amp; Finance (pp. 181-199). Singapore: Springer Nature Singapore \r\n\r\nDarfo-Oduro, R. (2023, September). Revisiting the Effect of R&amp;D intensity on innovation Performance: An Instrument Variable Approach. In ECIE 2023 18th European Conference on Innovation and Entrepreneurship Vol 1. Academic Conferences and publishing limited. \r\n\r\nDarfo-Oduro R, Prokop V, Stejskal J, Klímová V, Žítek V (2024) Do R&amp;D intensity and capacity utilisation  matter for SMEs’ innovations within the CEE region? Testing moderating roles of different ownership structures. PLoS ONE 19(1): e0296873. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0296873', 'I have been learning, teaching and researching economics for the past fifteeen years. I have handled courses in economics from high school to university (both masters and Bachelor\'s degree level) as lecturer or seminar lead. I have gathered wealth of knowledge in econometrics and data analysis and have supported both graduate and undergraduate students in their research journey. I have experience and expertise in the use of some of the most modern data analysis softwares which can be leveraged for research collaborations. I have also collaborated with other academics to produce articles, some of which have found space in high impact journal. I have also served as a reviewer for some top journals. I believe these skills I have acquired position me to be able to mentor students through teaching, supervision of student thesis and collaborate with academics to produce article for publications.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading', '1 month', NULL, 'Solomon Gyamfi Ph.D', 'Lecturer', 'Assistant Professor', 'Science Research Center \r\nUniversity of Pardubice \r\nCzech Republic', '+420 774 865 121', 'solomon.gyamfi@upce.cz', 'Raymond Boadi Frempong Ph.D', 'Lecturer', 'Associate Professor', 'Associate Professor \r\nEuropean School of Political and Social Sciences \r\nCatholic University of Lille \r\nFrance', '+49 1521 300 9507', 'raymond.frempong@univ-catholille.fr', 'David Ansong Ph.D  A', 'Lecturer', 'Associate Professor', 'UNC-Chapel Hill  \r\nSchool of Social Work', '+1 314 324 9056', 'ansong@email.unc.edu', 'BTU_99F950AA_cv_6a1f86d74f3a37.22355076.pdf', 'Raymond_CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '46.135.92.222', '2026-06-03 01:43:51', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_99F950AA_photo_6a1f86d74f3a71.29371508.jpg', 'IMG-20250829-WA0053.jpg'),
(280, 'BTU-C52FF391', 3, 'Mr.', 'ACQUAH', 'EMMANUEL', 'acquahemmanuel423@gmail.com', '+233540593616', 'Akim Oda- Aboabo R746, PINK, P.Box 16', 'AKIMODA', 'AKIMODA', 'Eastern', 'GHANA', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-723149458-9', '1996-02-11', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'Lovely Professional University', 3, NULL, 'My teaching, research, and professional experience are closely aligned with the mandate of the Agricultural Engineering Department and equip me to contribute meaningfully to its teaching, research, and community engagement activities. My academic training and research focus on environmental engineering, sustainable waste management, resource recovery, renewable energy systems, and circular economy principles, all of which are increasingly relevant to modern agricultural engineering and sustainable development.\r\n\r\nMy research has centered on developing practical and innovative solutions for the management and valorization of organic and agricultural wastes through composting, anaerobic digestion, biochar production, and waste-to-energy technologies. These areas contribute directly to sustainable agriculture, soil fertility enhancement, environmental protection, climate change mitigation, and efficient utilization of natural resources. In addition, I have experience applying analytical and decision-support tools such as Life Cycle Assessment (LCA), environmental impact assessment, and statistical analysis to evaluate the sustainability and performance of engineering systems.\r\n\r\nI have been actively involved in teaching, student mentoring, research support, and project supervision, helping students develop strong analytical, technical, and problem-solving skills. My interdisciplinary background enables me to bridge engineering, environmental sustainability, and agricultural resource management, thereby enriching both teaching and research activities.\r\n\r\nI am committed to academic excellence, innovation, and lifelong learning. I am particularly motivated to contribute to curriculum development, collaborative research, student-centered teaching, and the generation of practical solutions that address agricultural and environmental challenges. I believe my expertise, dedication, and passion for sustainable development will enable me to make a valuable contribution to the growth and success of the Department.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading academic and professional literature, conducting research, mentoring students, community service, scientific writing, attending seminars and workshops, and engaging in environmental sustainability initiatives.', 'Immediately', NULL, 'Prof. Ahmad Addo', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Department of Agricutural and Biosystems engineering, Kwame \r\nNkrumah University of Science and Technology', '+233244518346', 'Ahmadaddo@gmail.com', 'Professor. Pushpendra Kumar Sharma', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Dep. Of Civil Engineering, Lovely Professional \r\nUniversity, Punjab, India', '(+91) 9456064174', 'p.sharmaji10@gmail.com', 'Prof. Waseem Akram', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Dep. Of Environmental Engineering, Lovely Professional \r\nUniversity, Punjab, India', '6005502839', 'waseem.19417@lpu.co.in', 'BTU_C52FF391_cv_6a1fda4c72ce53.38135332.pdf', 'CV_ACQUAH EMMANUEL 33.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.166.4', '2026-06-03 07:39:56', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_C52FF391_photo_6a1fda4c72cee0.30473654.jpg', 'EMMANUEL_ACQUAH.jpg'),
(281, 'BTU-D3AE90B9', 8, 'Mr.', 'FUSEINI', 'ABDUL-MUMIN', 'fuseini1993.amf@gmail.com', '0241632483', NULL, 'WALEWALE', 'WALEWALE', 'North East', 'GHANAIAN', 'ISLAM', 'married', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-725295184-5', '1993-09-16', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF SKILLS TRAINING AND ENTREPRENEURIAL DEVELOPMENT, KUMASI', 5, NULL, 'My M.Phil. research was on the topic BUDGETORY CONTROL MECHANISMS AND FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE OF MANUFACTURING COPANIES IN GHANA. It has given me inadept knowledge in accounting and finance research, and I am well prepared to guid and lead more research in the field of accounting and finance.', 'no', NULL, NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading, researching, watching movies and traveling', '1 MONTH', NULL, 'Prof. Joseph Mbawuni', 'LECTURER', 'PROFFESSOR OF ACCOUNTING AND FINANCE', 'USTED, KUMASI', '0243911000', 'jombawuni@gmail.com', 'ABDUL BASHIRU GOMINA', 'MARKETER', 'SALES MANAGER', 'TVS MOTORS KUMASI', '0249660287', 'gominabashiru@gmail.com', 'Mr. Imoro Ali Sigri-Naah', 'REVENUE OFFICER', 'CHIEF REVENUE OFFICER', 'GRA, TAMALE', '0244972608', 'sigrinahr@yahoo,com', 'BTU_D3AE90B9_cv_6a1fdc3f534ad4.06584001.pdf', 'ABDUL-MUMIN Most Recent C .V).pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.249.199', '2026-06-03 07:48:15', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_D3AE90B9_photo_6a1fdc3f534b38.46611634.jpeg', 'ABDUL  PIC.jpeg'),
(282, 'BTU-36432F6B', 15, 'Mr.', 'Agyare', 'Richard', 'agyarerichard91@gmail.com', '+233245057687', 'C/O Manasseh Asante Agyare \r\nBox AS 66\r\nAshaiman', 'Ashaiman', 'Aburi', 'Greater Accra', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Catherine Agyare', 'C/O Manasseh Asante Agyare Box AS 66, Ashaiman', 'Druscilla Agyare 5/12/2009\r\nWilhelmina Yaa Agyare 27/9/2012\r\nCecrops Kwadwo Agyare 26/9/2015\r\nEliana M. A. Esi Agyare 23/2/2020', 'P0016148525', 'GHA-7713427750-4', '1981-07-27', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'University of Cape Coast', 11, 'Yet to publish', NULL, 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading religious and leadership books\r\nChristian activities', '1 month', 'I have enrolled as an ICA student and am at level two.', 'Prof. John Kwaku Amoh', 'Senior lecturer', 'Head of Accounting Department UPSA', 'P. O. Box LG 149 Legon Accra', '0243139610', 'john.amoh@upsamail.edu.gh', 'Mr. Francis Koomson', 'Ghana Education Service', 'Educational Officer', 'P. O. Box AS 66\r\nAshaiman', '0244569083', 'frankoomson@yahoo.com', 'Mr. Proper Tay', 'Accountant', 'Chief finance officer', 'Nelhsen Ghana Company\r\nGhana', '0246011884', 'protay2@gmail.com', 'BTU_36432F6B_cv_6a1fdca6b439e0.95840002.pdf', 'RICHARD AGYARE CV 5.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.160.0.58', '2026-06-03 07:49:58', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_36432F6B_photo_6a1fdca6b43a32.99632943.jpg', '1001230735.jpg'),
(283, 'BTU-33FDC6FE', 15, 'Mr.', 'ACQUAH', 'EMMANUEL', 'acquahemmanuel423@gmail.com', '+233540593616', 'Akim Oda- Aboabo R746, PINK, P.Box 16', 'AKIMODA', 'AKIMODA', 'Eastern', 'GHANA', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-723149458-9', '1996-02-11', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (Other)', 'Lovely Professional University', 3, NULL, 'From September 2021 to August 2022, I served as a Graduate Assistant in the Office of the Dean of Students at Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST). In this role, I provided high-level administrative and operational support, contributing to the effective management of student affairs and university administrative processes.\r\n\r\nMy responsibilities included coordinating official correspondence, maintaining records and documentation, organizing meetings and stakeholder engagements, preparing reports, managing schedules, and assisting in the implementation of student-centered policies and programmes. The position required strong organizational, communication, and interpersonal skills, as well as the ability to work under pressure while meeting strict deadlines.\r\n\r\nThrough this experience, I developed practical competencies in university administration, records management, stakeholder engagement, problem-solving, and institutional governance. Working closely with the Dean of Students exposed me to the complexities of higher education administration and strengthened my capacity to handle confidential matters with professionalism, integrity, and discretion.\r\n\r\nThis experience, together with my academic qualifications and subsequent professional engagements, has equipped me with the knowledge, administrative skills, and leadership potential required to effectively contribute to the Registry and support the achievement of the University\'s strategic objectives as an Assistant Registrar.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading academic and professional literature, conducting research, mentoring students, community service, scientific writing, attending seminars and workshops, and engaging in environmental sustainability initiatives.', 'Immediately', NULL, 'Prof. Ahmad Addo', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Department of Agricutural and Biosystems engineering, Kwame \r\nNkrumah University of Science and TechnologyKumasi, Ghana', '+233244518346', 'Ahmadaddo@gmail.com', 'Professor. Pushpendra Kumar Sharma', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Dep. Of Civil Engineering, Lovely Professional \r\nUniversity, Punjab, India.', '(+91) 9456064174', 'p.sharmaji10@gmail.com', 'Prof. Waseem Akram', 'Lecturer', 'Lecturer', 'Dep. Of Civil Engineering, Lovely Professional \r\nUniversity, Punjab, India.', '6005502839', 'waseem.19417@lpu.co.in', 'BTU_33FDC6FE_cv_6a1fe1d81a3b90.58630510.pdf', 'CV_ACQUAH EMMANUEL 33.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.35.90', '2026-06-03 08:12:08', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_33FDC6FE_photo_6a1fe1d81a3bd3.28496237.jpg', 'EMMANUEL_ACQUAH.jpg'),
(284, 'BTU-A5C0E923', 1, 'Dr.', 'Felix', 'Ayelazuno', 'ayelazunofelix@gmail.com', '+4915158875713', 'Buchenlochstraße 37', 'Kaiserslautern', 'Kaiserslautern', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', NULL, 'married', 'Eva Apepa Atogiba', NULL, 'Elyana Delewine Ayelazuno (13/3/2022)\r\nHeidi Awinetoya Ayelazuno (09/12/2023)', NULL, 'GHA-715313535-3', '1989-04-04', 'male', 'PhD', 'Rheinland-Pfälzische Technische Universität (RPTU)', 5, NULL, 'I hold a PhD in Molecular Parasitology from Rheinland-Pfälzische Technische Universität Kaiserslautern-Landau (RPTU), Germany, where my research focused on mitochondrial protein import in Plasmodium parasites. This work provided me with deep expertise in biochemistry, molecular biology, microbiology, and infectious disease mechanisms, all of which are foundational to preclinical medical education. My MPhil in Molecular Cell Biology of Infectious Diseases from the University of Ghana and my BSc in Biochemistry from KNUST further strengthen my grounding in both Biochemistry and Microbiology.\r\nIn addition to my doctoral research, I bring practical research leadership experience from the Navrongo Health Research Centre (NHRC) and the West African Centre for Cell Biology of Infectious Pathogens (WACCBIP). In these roles, I led and supported research projects, coordinated laboratory operations, supervised students, and contributed to data analysis and scientific reporting. These experiences have equipped me with strong project management skills, the ability to mentor young scientists, and a commitment to capacity building', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, NULL, '3 months', NULL, 'Prof. Dr. rer. nat. Marcel Deponte', 'W2 Professor, department of biochemistry', NULL, 'Faculty of Chemistry / Biochemistry         \r\nErwin-Schrödinger-Str. 54                                                    \r\n67663 Kaiserslautern, Germany', NULL, 'deponte@chemie.uni-kl.de', 'Prof. Lucas Amenga-Etego', 'Senior Research Fellow, WACCBIP, University of Ghana', NULL, NULL, '+233 20 379 7997', 'lamenga-etego@ug.edu.gh', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_A5C0E923_cv_6a1fe7b76e69f0.72806225.pdf', 'CV_ Felix Ayelazuno.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '80.187.100.208', '2026-06-03 08:37:11', '2026-06-12 23:06:34', 'BTU_A5C0E923_photo_6a1fe7b76e6a40.18259931.jpg', '7983b919.jpg'),
(285, 'BTU-6EB0C31C', 2, 'Dr.', 'Kanmiki', 'Kanluki Lambert', 'chiefkanmikikanlukilambert@gmail.com', '0246724011', 'Regional Education Office\r\nPostal Box 110\r\nBolgatanga U/E/R', 'Navrongo', 'Navrongo', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christianity', 'married', 'Mrs Juliana Akua Kanmiki', 'The Palace of the Saama Naba of Bongo, C/o Postal Box 4 Bongo.', 'Lugard Asakiwine Kanmiki.............13/07/2012\r\n\r\nLuciana Ayewine Kanmiki................18/08/2015\r\n\r\nLucencia Abesiyen Kanmiki............01/07/2018', 'P0002998831', 'GHA-716204857-8', '1984-10-20', 'male', 'PhD', 'University For Development Studies', 11, NULL, 'I have served as a lecturer in the Faculty of Culture and Development at Millar Open University for the past three years. This faculty shares significant similarities with the Liberal Studies Department at Bolgatanga Technical University (BTU). The experience I have gained during this period will enable me to contribute meaningfully to the enhancement and development of the department.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Community outreach and Socialisation.', 'immediately', 'I am a highly focused and exceptionally results-oriented individual, consistently driven by a strong desire to achieve tangible outcomes. My passion lies in making significant contributions, and I am particularly eager to apply my skills and dedication to the ongoing development and advancement of the Liberal Studies Department. I am confident that my concentrated efforts and commitment to producing excellent results will be invaluable in supporting the department\'s goals and initiatives.', 'DR. Niagia Santua Francis', 'Lecturer', 'Dean and Head of Faculty for Culture and Development Studies at Millar Open University', 'Millar Institute For  Transdisciplinary And Development Studies.\r\n P.O.Box 607, Bolgatanga.', '0277606621', 'niagiafsantuah@gmail.com', 'Professor David Millar', 'Lecturer', 'Professor and President of the Millar Open University', 'Millar Institute For  Transdisciplinary And Development Studies.\r\n P.O.Box 607, Bolgatanga.', '0244720834', 'millarad1@yahoo.com', 'Bonaba Baba Salifu Atamale Alemyarum', 'Retired Civil servant', 'Paramount Chief of the Bongo Traditional Area.', 'The Palace of the Paramount Chief of Bongo\r\nC/o Postsl Box 4\r\nBongo.', '0243743969', 'bonabababa@gmail.com', 'BTU_6EB0C31C_cv_6a1ffb3781d452.05978575.pdf', 'CV_OF_Dr_KANMIKI_KANLUKI_LAMBERT_BTU.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '41.155.64.131', '2026-06-03 10:00:23', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_6EB0C31C_photo_6a1ffb3781d4a3.93884544.jpg', 'Passport Of Chief Dr Kanmiki Kanluki Lambert.jpg'),
(286, 'BTU-3034CC27', 15, 'Mr.', 'AKOSAH', 'HENRY OPOKU', 'henryakosah94@gmail.com', '0544858914', 'OFFICE OF THE ADMINISTRATOR, NURSING AND MIDWIFERY TRAINING COLLEGE TWIFO PRASO', 'ASHANTI BEKWAI', 'ASHANTI BEKWAI', 'Ashanti', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', 'married', 'EDNA CHARITY GENSON AFFUM', NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '1994-08-01', 'male', 'Master\'s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF GHANA', 5, 'Akosah,H.H.,&amp; Akosah,H.O.(2022).Assessing Job satisfaction in public universities in Ghana: A \r\nCase study of KNUST. Journal of Science and Technology 41(2),166-130. \r\n\r\nJob Satisfaction of staff of Academic Libraries. A case of Kwame Nkrumah \r\nUniversity of Science and Technology (KNUST) library (review stage)\r\n \r\nAwareness and use of online journals at selected Nursing and Midwifery Training Colleges in Ghana \r\n(review stage)', 'My professional experience in tertiary education administration is directly relevant to the position of Assistant Registrar. As an Administrator, I have been responsible for coordinating administrative activities, managing institutional records, servicing committees, preparing official reports and correspondence, implementing policies, and engaging with key stakeholders.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, my background in information management has strengthened my skills in information organization, records management, research support, and the effective use of technology in administration. These experiences have equipped me with strong organizational, communication, leadership, and analytical skills necessary for effective university administration.\r\n\r\nI am therefore well-positioned to contribute to the efficient management of academic and administrative processes and support the achievement of the institution\'s goals as an Assistant Registrar.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Reading professional and academic literature, conducting research, mentoring young professionals and students, participating in community development activities, and exploring emerging technologies and innovations in education and administration', '1 month', 'In addition to my academic qualifications and professional experience, I have demonstrated commitment to institutional development through active participation in administrative, academic, and professional activities. My experience in higher education administration, coupled with my background in information management and research, has equipped me with the capacity to support effective governance, policy implementation, and quality service delivery. I am eager to contribute my expertise and experience toward the achievement of the University\'s strategic goals.', 'MR VICTOR TEYE', 'LIBRARIAN', 'UNIVERSITY COLLEGE LIBRARIAN', 'ANGLICAN UNIVERSITY COLLEGE OF TECHNOLOGY', NULL, NULL, 'STELLA SARPOMAAH OPPONG', 'Community Health Nursing Training College, Akim Oda', 'PRINCIPAL', 'Akim Oda', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_3034CC27_cv_6a1ffbddbc5f98.14242489.pdf', 'HENRY O.AKOSAH CURRICULUM VITEA.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.225.99', '2026-06-03 10:03:09', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_3034CC27_photo_6a1ffbddbc5fd1.83224092.jpg', 'passport_photo.jpg'),
