(297, 'BTU-FEFBEE57', 8, 'Mr.', 'Anyedina', 'Stephen Akazigayire', 'sakazigayire@gmail.com', '+233542343622', 'Hse no E C D 36 Mirigu', 'Mirigu', 'Bolga', 'Upper East', 'Ghanaian', 'Christian', 'single', NULL, NULL, 'NA', 'P0031354920', 'GHA-722913759-7', '1995-03-30', 'female', 'Professional Certificate', 'Institute of chartered accountant Ghana', 5, 'NA', 'As a Chartered Accountant with a Master of Science (MSc) in Accounting and Finance, possessing a strong academic and professional background that is highly relevant to the Lecturer position at Bolgatanga Technical University. Having studied at Bolgatanga Technical University myself, I have a deep understanding of the institution\'s values, academic culture, and commitment to developing skilled professionals, which positions me well to contribute effectively to its mission.\r\nOver the past five years, I have worked with Access Bank, where I have gained extensive practical experience in accounting, finance, financial analysis, risk management, customer relationship management, and professional ethics. This industry experience enables me to bridge the gap between theory and practice and provide students with real-world insights into the accounting and finance profession.\r\nIn addition to my professional experience, I have a strong passion for teaching and mentoring. During my university studies, I regularly assisted and taught my colleagues in accounting and finance-related subjects, helping them understand complex concepts and improve their academic performance. I also taught at the Basic and Junior High School levels for one year, where I developed effective teaching, communication, and classroom management skills.\r\nMy combination of academic qualifications, professional accounting expertise, teaching experience, and familiarity with Bolgatanga Technical University equips me to deliver quality instruction, mentor students, engage in research, and contribute meaningfully to the University\'s academic goals. I am committed to creating an engaging learning environment that promotes critical thinking, practical application of knowledge, and academic excellence.\r\nI am confident that my background, experience, and dedication to education will enable me to make a valuable contribution to Bolgatanga Technical University as a Lecturer', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'Football and music', 'Two weeks', 'NA', 'Kahaar Alhassan', 'Banker', 'Branch manager', 'Access bank Bolga', '0243070442', 'kahaar.Alhassan@accessbankplc.com', 'Abudu Dawuda (CA)', 'Lecturer', 'Senior Lecturer', 'BTU Bolga', '024 857 0730', 'dabudu@bolgatu.edu.gh', 'John Egyir', 'Accountant', 'dabudu@bolgatu.edu.gh', 'URA Radio Bolga', '0243401509', 'johnegyir@gmail.com', 'BTU_FEFBEE57_cv_6a203bb88ff468.00519422.pdf', 'Anyedina Stephen A. CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.124.88', '2026-06-03 14:35:36', '2026-06-07 23:59:41', 'BTU_FEFBEE57_photo_6a203bb88ff4b8.39632769.jpeg', 'IMG_8936.jpeg');
