es geared towards the built environment, which the building technology department belong. This confirms that there is going to be positive impact both on the students and the University at large.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'traveling and sight seeing', '2 WEEKS', NULL, 'Dr. Daniel Jato Espino', 'academics', 'Senior Researcher', 'Valencia International University', '+34680209260', 'Djato@universidadviu.com', 'Jorge Hernandez Rodriguez (Prof.)', 'Academics', 'Head of Studies (Civil Eng. Dept.)', 'University of Cantabria, Spain', '+34680546512', 'Jorge.rodriguez@unican.es', 'Fausta Ganaa (Mrs)', 'Academics', 'Public Relations Officer', 'Accra Technical University', '+233 548032968', 'fkganaa@atu.edu.gh', 'BTU_E7C5DA3B_cv_6a2726cf004b87.39717847.pdf', 'MTCE MGT.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.170.45', '2026-06-08 20:32:15', '2026-06-08 20:32:15', 'BTU_E7C5DA3B_photo_6a2726cf004bc9.03528326.jpeg', 'Passport photo_Dr. Yiwo.jpeg'),
(310, 'BTU-6AE5C3B6', 16, 'Mr.', 'DOGBE', 'FRANCIS', 'kdogbe4@gmail.com', '+233553031328', 'P.O.Box 14', 'TARKWA', 'Tarkwa', 'Western', 'GHANAIAN', 'CHRISTIAN', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-723907931-9', '1996-03-03', 'male', 'Master&#039;s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF BUSINESS AND INTEGRATED DEVELOPMENT STUDIES, WA', 2, 'Dogbe, F., Alhassan, M. D., &amp; Bawuah, B. (2024). The role of information and communication technologies in public sector performance: Exploring the interactions between government and citizen usage. Transforming Government: People, Process and Policy, Emerald Publishing.\r\n\r\nDogbe, F., Alhassan, M. D., Adomako, R. B., &amp; Davies, E. (2024). The mediating role of government ICT use on the nexus between ICT access and public sector performance. Transforming Government: People, Process and Policy, Emerald Publishing.', 'My academic training in Accounting at both the master&#039;s level and my ongoing PhD studies provides a strong foundation for contributing to the Department of Communication Design and Applied Art. My expertise in accounting, financial analysis, and research equips me with the ability to teach and conduct interdisciplinary research in areas such as creative enterprise management, financial sustainability of art and design ventures, project budgeting, entrepreneurship, and the economic value of creative industries. Through my research, I have developed strong analytical, communication, and problem-solving skills that are essential for evidence-based decision-making and effective project management. I am particularly interested in exploring the intersection between accounting, innovation, sustainability, and the creative economy. These competencies will enable me to support students in developing both artistic creativity and business acumen, while contributing to research, curriculum development, and the advancement of the Department’s academic and professional objectives.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'READING AND PLAYING FOOTBALL', '1 week', 'I am a dedicated academic with a strong commitment to excellence in teaching, research, and community service. Beyond my academic qualifications, I possess excellent communication, leadership, and interpersonal skills that enable me to work effectively with students, colleagues, and external stakeholders. I am actively engaged in research and scholarly publishing, with a keen interest in interdisciplinary studies that address contemporary societal and developmental challenges. My ongoing PhD studies have further strengthened my analytical, research, and problem-solving abilities. I am committed to continuous professional development and to creating an inclusive, student-centered learning environment that promotes critical thinking, creativity, and innovation. If given the opportunity, I will contribute meaningfully to the Department&#039;s teaching, research, curriculum development, mentorship, and community engagement activities while upholding the highest standards of academic integrity and professionalism.', 'Prof Bernard Bawauh', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Head of Department (Accounting)', 'University of Business and Integrated Dev. Studies WA Upper West \r\nP.O.Box WA64', '0244676079', 'bbawauah@ubids.edu.gh', 'Mr Andrews Salakpi', 'Senior Lecturer', 'Industrial Attachment Coordinator School of Business', 'University of Business and Integrated Dev. Studies WA Upper West \r\nP.O.Box WA64', '0241812960', 'Andycoleb@gmail.com', 'Ezekiel Davies', 'Lecturer', 'Department Exam Officer Banking and Finance', 'University of Business and Integrated Dev. Studies WA Upper West \r\nP.O.Box WA64', '0540438522', 'edavies@ubids.edu.gh', 'BTU_6AE5C3B6_cv_6a28972a0c0dc3.13931843.pdf', 'Dogbe_CV 1.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.145.48', '2026-06-09 22:43:54', '2026-06-13 00:05:34', 'BTU_6AE5C3B6_photo_6a28972a0c0e12.61224663.jpg', 'IMG-20220705-WA0001.jpg'),
(311, 'BTU-371B219C', 11, 'Mr.', 'MAHAMA', 'ABULBASIE', 'bashmohammed0000@gmail.com', '0242804353', 'ZORKOR SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL P. O. BOX 56 BONGO', 'BOLGATANGA', 'TAMALE', 'Northern', 'GHANAIAN', 'ISLAM', 'married', 'ISSAH ZALIYA', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'GHA-715690222-8', '1980-06-21', 'male', 'Other', 'TAHIRIYA JHS', 11, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CEASER ACHIGEWE', 'TEACHING', 'HEADMASTER', 'ZORKOR SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL, BOX 56, BONGO', '0241847721', NULL, 'MUSAH NATHANIEL', 'TEACHING', 'BURSAR', 'ZORKOR SENIOR HIGH SCHOOL BOX 56 BONGO', '0244421792', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'BTU_371B219C_cv_6a2931f6663615.87522376.pdf', 'MAHA.pdf', 'shortlisted', '', '154.161.127.109', '2026-06-10 09:44:22', '2026-06-12 23:00:28', 'BTU_371B219C_photo_6a2931f6663669.42853223.jpg', 'MAHAMA.jpg'),
(312, 'BTU-29DB68A3', 7, 'Mr.', 'NYAABA', 'ISAAC AZEGURA', 'ikeazegura@gmail.com', '0547366990', 'NKAWIE SENIOR HIGH/TECHNICAL SCHOOL, P. O. BOX 88, NKAWIE', 'KALBEO', 'KALBEO', 'Upper East', 'GHANAIAN', 'CATHOLIC', 'married', 'Gifty Ayinpogbila Atingane', 'UB-02684587, Kalbeo-Bolgatanga', '1. SUCCESS NYAAB - 24/11/2012\r\n2. ZIMRAN NYAABA -30/04/2015\r\n3. WISHGRANT NYAABA - 30/04/2019\r\n4. BRYANNA NYAABA - 20/05/2022', NULL, 'GHA-716912320-9', '0000-00-00', 'male', 'Master&#039;s Degree (MPhil.)', 'UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION', 11, '1.Isaac, A. N., Alex, K. O. &amp; Sherry, K. A. (2022). Analysis of Variant Stresses Acting on Modified Animal Drawn Mouldboard Plough Share using Finite Element Method. SSRG International Journal of Mechanical Engineering, 9 (8), 1-10. DOI: https://doi.org/10.14445/23488360/IJME-V9I8P101.\r\n2. Sulley, Y. S., Isaac, A. N., Isaac, K. Y., Alex, K. O. &amp; Baba, Z. (2024). Finite element analysis of a FeC, Cr-V and Al 7075-T6 leaf springs for light vehicle suspension system. World Journal of Advanced Engineering Technology and Sciences, 11 (02), 296 –307. DOI: https://doi.org/10.30574/wjaets.2024.11.2.0112.\r\n3. Alex Kojo Okyere, Nicholas Nii Aryee Aryeetey, Sherry K. Amedorme and Isaac Azegura Nyaaba (2025). Enhancing Safety Management Practices in Mechanical Workshops in Kumasi Suame Magazine Industrial Sector. International Journal of Engineering Innovation &amp; Research Volume 14, Issue 2, ISSN: 2277 – 5668.', 'My experience as a Mechanical Engineering Educator is directly relevant to the position of Lecturer, as it has provided me with extensive knowledge of engineering principles and effective teaching methodologies. Through teaching undergraduate engineering courses, preparing instructional materials, assessing student performance, and supervising projects, I have developed the ability to communicate complex technical concepts clearly and foster student learning.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, my experience in engineering research, design, and the use of industry-standard software such as Autodesk Inventor and ANSYS Workbench enables me to integrate practical applications into the classroom. My involvement in research and academic writing has also strengthened my capacity to contribute to scholarly activities, supervise student research, and support the university&#039;s academic mission. These experiences have equipped me with the teaching, research, and mentorship skills necessary to excel as a Lecturer in Mechanical Engineering.', 'no', 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, 'WATCHING ATHLETICS, BOXING AND LISTENING TO MUSIC', 'TWO (2) WEEKS', NULL, 'PRO. SHERRY KWABLA AMEDORME', 'LECTURERING', 'HoD/SENIOR LECTOR, USTED, KUMASI', 'UNIVERSITY OF SKILLS TRAINING AND ENTREPRENEURIAL DEVELOPMENT\r\nP. O BOX 1277                                                                                             \r\nKUMASI- ASHANTI', '0243104361', 'skamedorme@aamusted.edu.gh', 'MR. NELSON TWUM. ASABRE', 'TEACHING', 'HEAD OF DEPARTMENT', 'NKAWIE SENIOR HIGH/TECHNICAL SCHOOL, P.O. BOX 88, NKAWIE', '0243005434', 'nellytwum20@gmail.com', 'DR. EMMANUEL ADU', 'LECTURERING', 'SENIOR LECTURER', 'KUMASI TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY, \r\nP. O BOX 854                                                                                 \r\nKUMASI- GHANA, WEST AFRICA', '0244972070', 'Emmanuel.adu@kstu.edu.gh', 'BTU_29DB68A3_cv_6a2a4a5f477808.58346969.pdf', 'ISAAC AZEGURA NYAABA- CV.pdf', 'pending', NULL, '154.161.249.126', '2026-06-11 05:40:47', '2026-06-11 05:40:47', 'BTU_29DB68A3_photo_6a2a4a5f477899.57496599.jpg', 'ISAAC AZEGURA NYAABA.jpg');
