(85, 46, 'September,', 'May, 2024', 'PureTrust Foundation LBG', 'PureTrust Foundation LBG, P. O. Box 552, E/R, Ghana', 'Agriculture Programme Advisor', ' Provided research and policy guidance on soil, water, and agricultural development. \r\n Supervised and trained the agriculture team in sustainable land and water management practices. \r\n Designed and implemented strategies for farmer cooperatives and community-driven agricultural projects. \r\n Promoted dry-season irrigation farming to strengthen food security and income generation.\r\n Developed and managed conservation agriculture and soil management demonstration fields. \r\n Delivered farmer trainings and practical sessions on improved soil and water management techniques.', '', 'End of contract', 1),
(86, 46, 'September,', 'September,', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST)', 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology, Kumasi, Ashanti region, Ghana', 'Field Research Assistant', ' Managed soil–water research activities at the Tropical Agrivoltaic Research Fields in Tamale and Kumasi and writing of manuscript for publication.\r\n Installed and maintained irrigation systems for experimental plots.\r\n Oversaw irrigation scheduling, soil moisture monitoring, and water management practices.\r\n Supervised collection of crop growth, soil moisture, sensor, and weather data.\r\n Analyzed soil–water data and contributed to technical reporting and project documentation.', 'full-time', 'Better opportunity', 2),
(87, 46, 'June, 2022', 'September,', 'Hikma Agro-Service Limited', 'Hikma Agro-Service Limited, Zagyuri, Tamale, Ghana', 'Agronomist/Supervisor', ' Coordinated a variety of field-based agronomic operations to support field research.\r\n Supervised the installation and maintenance of irrigation systems to support research trials and water use efficiency.\r\n Designed innovative agricultural technologies to enhance productivity.\r\n Assessed the performance of farm units and provided research-informed recommendations for improvement.', '', 'End of National Service', 3),
(88, 46, 'August, 20', 'September,', 'University for Development Studies', 'University for Development Studies, P. O. Box TL. 1882, Tamale, Ghana', 'Teaching and Research Assistant', ' Engaged in teaching, research, and marking of students’ exams scripts.\r\n Prepared and delivered tutorial sessions to support students’ understanding of course materials.\r\n Facilitated in-class and online student group discussions.\r\n Supervised undergraduate student research projects. \r\n Participated in student examination invigilation processes.', 'full-time', 'For further studies', 4),
