(107, 55, 'JUN 2019', 'SEPT 2018', 'GHANA HEALTH SERVICE-BOLGATANGA', 'BOLGATANGA, UPPER EAST REGION', 'INTENSIONSHIP', '1. Accounting\r\n•	Ensured proper books of accounts were maintained in accordance with GHS financial management procedures.\r\n•	Supported the preparation of the Directorate’s monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements.\r\n•	Ensured consistent adherence to financial policies, approval processes, and budgetary controls, reducing processing errors.\r\n•	Contributed to improving filing and documentation systems, resulting in faster retrieval of financial records for audits and management reviews.\r\n2. Auditing\r\n•	Served as a member of the Audit Implementation Committee, supporting internal and external audit processes.\r\n•	Monitored the implementation of audit recommendations and ensured compliance across departments.\r\n•	Helped strengthen internal controls by ensuring audit findings were addressed to their fullest, contributing to reduced repeat audit queries.\r\n3. Taxation\r\n•	Coordinated tax-related activities between the Regional Directorate and the Ghana Revenue Authority (GRA).\r\n•	Ensured strict adherence to tax laws and policies regarding withholding tax, VAT, and PAYE on all expenditures incurred by the Directorate.\r\n•	Supported timely submission and documentation of tax payments, minimizing compliance risks.\r\n4. IT &amp; e-Transactions\r\n•	Assisted in the daily operations of the Directorate’s computerized accounting systems.\r\n•	Worked with platforms such as AccPac and Hyperion, supporting data entry, reconciliations, and financial reporting.\r\n•	Contributed to the shift toward increased use of e-transactions and digital documentation, improving processing efficiency and accuracy.', 'full-time', 'NEEDED TO LEARN FROM OTHER SECTORS', 0),
(108, 55, 'OCT 2016', 'AUG 2016', 'LOAD GHANA', 'BOLGATANGA, UPPER EAST REGION', 'ACCOUNTANT', 'Management / People Responsibility\r\n•	Supervised 2 finance and administrative staff, ensuring accurate financial documentation and compliance with internal policies.\r\nUnique or Additional Responsibilities\r\n•	Monitored funds allocation to rehab programs and community outreach, ensuring alignment with donor restrictions and project objectives.\r\n•	Coordinated with program managers to track expenses for detoxifiers distribution and rehabilitation services, beyond standard accounting duties.\r\n•	Assisted in preparing financial reports for donors, grant submissions, and regulatory compliance.\r\n\r\nKey Achievements &amp; Impact\r\n•	Implemented a financial tracking system for donations and program expenditures, improving transparency and accountability.\r\n•	Reconciled sales and inventory records of detoxifiers, reducing losses by 20% and supporting program sustainability.\r\n•	Streamlined payroll and staff allowances, reducing errors by 95% and saving the NGO ₵10,000 annually.\r\n•	Prepared donor financial reports that contributed to continued funding and successful grant applications.', 'full-time', 'BETTER OPPORTUNITY', 1),
(109, 55, 'SEPT 2013', 'JUL 2013', 'RURAL WAVES NETWORK (WORD FM)', 'ZUARUNGU, UPPER EAST REGION', 'ACCOUNTANT', 'Management / People Responsibility\r\n•	Supervised 3 staff in billing, cash collection, and petty cash management, ensuring accurate revenue recording and proper documentation across departments.\r\n\r\nKey Achievements &amp; Impact\r\n•	Implemented a new revenue-tracking system that reduced unrecorded advertising income by over 25%, improving the station’s financial accuracy and cash flow.\r\n•	Strengthened expenditure controls by introducing a petty-cash reconciliation process that cut unexplained variances by 40% within six months.\r\n•	Prepared monthly financial reports that enabled management to make better budgeting decisions, helping reduce unnecessary operational costs by 15%.\r\n•	Improved creditor and vendor management, resulting in faster payment cycles and stronger supplier relationships, which secured more favourable terms for the station.\r\n•	Supported management in developing the station’s annual budget, including forecasting advertising revenue and operational costs, which improved planning and programme funding.\r\n•	Digitised manual financial records, reducing reporting time by 30% and improving audit readiness for external reviews.', '', 'END OF SERVICE', 2),
(110, 55, 'AUG 2012', NULL, 'GHANA AUDIT SERVICE', 'BAWKU, UPPER EAST REGION', 'SERVICE PERSONNEL', 'Responsibilities \r\n•	Assisted in planning and executing audits for MDAs and District Assemblies, including testing controls, verifying expenditure, and documenting audit evidence.\r\n•	Reviewed financial statements, payment vouchers, payroll reports and procurement documents to ensure compliance with Public Financial Management (PFM) regulations.\r\n•	Supported the preparation of audit working papers and contributed to draft audit reports submitted to senior auditors and managers.', 'full-time', NULL, 3),
