(112, 57, 'APRIL 2024', 'MARCH 2024', 'BONGO DISTRICT HOSPITAL (GHS)', 'BONGO, UPPER EAST REGION, GHANA', 'LABORATORY MANAGER/ BIOMEDICAL SCIENTIST', '•      Oversee laboratory operations across hematology, clinical chemistry, immunology, blood banking, microbiology, and molecular diagnostics units. \r\n•	Implements and reinforces laboratory Quality Management Systems (QMS)\r\n•	Performs diagnostic testing, equipment calibration, quality control, preventive maintenance, troubleshooting, and interpretation of laboratory results across multiple diagnostic disciplines.\r\n•	Coordinates diagnostic and sample referral activities among hospital laboratory, sub-district facilities, and higher-level referral centers to ensure efficient continuity of patient care. \r\n•	Manages laboratory inventory systems, including monitoring supplies, consumables, reagents, and timely procurement/resupply processes. \r\n•	Ensures appropriate personnel scheduling, task allocation, and workflow coordination to ensure efficient laboratory operations and service delivery.\r\n•	Implements and reinforces the adherence to biosafety protocols.\r\n•	Trains, supervises, and mentor laboratory staff, interns and sub-district facilities’ laboratory staff.\r\n•      Generates, analyzes and manages laboratory data for DHIMS2 disease surveillance.\r\n•     Supports public health emergency activities within the district as a member of the district\'s public health emergency response team.', 'full-time', 'Transfer', 0),
