(140, 71, 'August, 20', NULL, 'Ghana Christian International High School', 'Ashanti -Fomena', 'Head Master', '1. Instructional Leadership &amp; Academics Curriculum Management: Oversees the implementation of the educational curriculum, syllabus distribution, and the school calendar.\r\n\r\nTeacher Supervision: Mentors and appraises teaching staff, conducts classroom observations, and ensures high instructional standards. \r\nStudent Assessment: Sets policies for student examinations, grading, and academic progress tracking.\r\n2. Administration &amp; Operations School Operations: Manages daily administrative functions, including scheduling, time-tabling, and facility maintenance .Record Keeping: Ensures accurate maintenance of school records, student admissions, and personnel files.\r\n\r\n3. Finance &amp; Resource Management Budgeting: Prepares and administers the school budget to align with institutional goals. Resource Procurement: Oversees the acquisition and maintenance of educational materials, laboratory equipment, and library resources.\r\n4. Student Welfare &amp; Discipline Code of Conduct: Maintains order, enforces school regulations, and oversees disciplinary procedures. Pastoral Care: Promotes a safe environment that caters to the health, guidance, and overall welfare of students. Extracurriculars: Organizes sports, clubs, and cultural activities for holistic student development.\r\n5. Stakeholder &amp; Community Relations Parent Communication: Acts as the primary liaison between the school, the Parent-Teacher Association (PTA), and the community. External Representation: Represents the institution to educational boards, government agencies, and the public', 'full-time', NULL, 3),
