(209, 106, 'Nov, 2020', NULL, 'University of Cape Coast', 'Lutheran Centre Madina/Papafio Hills, Accra Campus', 'IT LECTURER (Part Time)', '•	Lecturing areas of the IT course outline.\r\n•	Lecturing according to the educational needs, abilities and achievement of the individual students and groups of students.\r\n•	Planning, and presenting lectures that cater for the needs of the whole ability range within students’ levels. \r\n•	Planning and delivering lectures to students. \r\n•	Preparing of lecture notes to students.\r\n•	Marking of students’ examinations, assignments, group works etc. to facilitate positive student\'s development.\r\n•	Maintaining discipline at the computer labs and lecture halls.\r\n•	Organising the computer labs, lectures halls, and also creating learning resources to encourage a positive learning environment.\r\n•	Motivating students with enthusiastic, imaginative presentations.\r\n•	Adopting and working towards the implementation of the development plan of a particular student.\r\n•	Assigning work, correcting and supporting students.\r\n•	Assessing, recording and reporting on the development, progress, attainment and behaviour of students.\r\n•	Providing or contributing to oral and written assessments, planning, brainstorming sessions, reports and references relating to individual students or groups of students.\r\n•	Participating in arrangements within the framework of the institute for the appraisal of students\' performance.\r\n•	Promoting the general progress and well-being of individual students and groups of students.\r\n•	Planning developmental activities and programs with HOD’s and staff of the department that will enhance the personal and academic development of students.\r\n•	Providing guidance and advice to students on educational and social matters and on their further education and future careers.', 'full-time', 'Better opportunities and remuneration', 0),
