(264, 134, '14/01/2014', NULL, 'Universal Co-operative Credit Union', 'Post Office Box 50, New Edubiase', 'Financial Manager / Operations', 'Major Achievements\r\n•	Increased Union financial mobilization by over 600% within first two years through strategic planning and improved staff performance monitoring.\r\n•	Designed and implemented the Union’s Internal Control System, approved by the Board and currently in effective use.\r\n•	Developed financial and operational policies and supervised implementation to strengthen accountability.\r\n•	Introduced an anonymous staff feedback system, significantly improving staff morale, transparency, and productivity.\r\n•	Ensured all staff acquired TIN numbers and complied with tax regulations.\r\nKey Responsibilities\r\n•	Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements for the Board, CUA Ashanti, CUA National, and the Bank of Ghana.\r\n•	Lead and consolidate annual budget preparation and monitor performance to ensure targets are achieved.\r\n•	Handle full tax compliance: PAYE filing, SSNIT contributions, Tier 2 &amp; Tier 3 payments.\r\n•	Manage cashflow operations, bank accounts, cheque issuance, and safe custody of funds.\r\n•	Prepare monthly Bank Reconciliation Statements for GCB and ADB accounts.\r\n•	Oversee all Investments and Project Management activities.\r\n•	Support loan recovery initiatives and fund mobilization strategies to improve Union liquidity.\r\n•	Perform other strategic and administrative duties as assigned by the Board.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(265, 135, '2023', NULL, 'IS Evolutions Consult Ltd', '52 Akoa Ndoh RD, Newtown - Accra', 'Software Engineer', '• Owned end-to-end delivery of backend systems from requirements gathering to deployment, ensuring high\r\nperformance, scalability, and reliability.\r\n• Designed and maintained scalable Django/DRF APIs supporting high-volume transactional workflows with\r\nstrong data validation and access control.\r\n• Built email notification systems using Mailtrap/SMTP for transactional messaging, system alerts, and\r\ncustomer communication workflows.\r\n• Designed API and middleware integrations with third-party services (payment gateways, SMS platforms),\r\nensuring secure, reliable, and scalable communication.\r\n• Implemented caching (Redis), retry logic, and structured error handling to improve system reliability and\r\nuptime.\r\n• Optimised database queries and backend performance, improving response times by over 30%.\r\nLanguages Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, C#, SQL\r\nBackend WebSockets\r\nFrontend Databases optimisation, ACID transactions\r\nIntegrations event handling\r\nArchitecture processing\r\nCloud infrastructure, deployments, DevOps RabbitMQ, Linux server management\r\nSecurity JWT, OAuth, RBAC, secure trails\r\nTesting &amp; QA readiness\r\nCollaboration Photoshop\r\nIT &amp; Infra diagnostics\r\n• Implemented real-time WebSocket-based features, improving collaboration efficiency by 40%.\r\n• Participated in Agile delivery processes including sprint collaboration, SIT/UAT testing, deployment, and\r\nrelease readiness using Jira.\r\n• Mentored junior developers through code reviews, technical guidance, and knowledge sharing.\r\n• Reduced production defects by 30% through improved testing practices and QA integration.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(266, 135, '2022', NULL, 'Ghana Health Service, Tongo', 'Dapooretindongo - UB-0011-0079, Bolgatanga,Upper East', 'System Administrator', '• Managed and maintained the Lightwave Health Information Management System (LHIMS) across multiple\r\ndistributed health facilities, ensuring high system availability and operational continuity.\r\n• Administered and monitored LAN infrastructure, including troubleshooting connectivity issues, cable\r\nreplacement, fault isolation, and hardware diagnostics.\r\n• Led data quality and integrity initiatives impacting patient insurance validation and electronic medical\r\nrecords accuracy.\r\n• Provided first-line technical support and coordinated with central ICT teams to resolve system-level issues\r\npromptly.\r\n• Trained over 100 healthcare professionals on digital systems, significantly improving adoption and reporting\r\ncompliance.\r\n• Streamlined reporting workflows and data submission processes, reducing report generation time by 25%.\r\n• Managed user accounts, access rights, and ensured adherence to data security and IT policies.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(267, 135, '2021', NULL, 'Ghana Health Service, Tongo', 'Dapooretindongo - UB-0011-0079, Bolgatanga,Upper East', 'System Administrator', '• Managed and maintained the Lightwave Health Information Management System (LHIMS) across multiple\r\ndistributed health facilities, ensuring high system availability and operational continuity.\r\n• Administered and monitored LAN infrastructure, including troubleshooting connectivity issues, cable\r\nreplacement, fault isolation, and hardware diagnostics.\r\n• Led data quality and integrity initiatives impacting patient insurance validation and electronic medical\r\nrecords accuracy.\r\n• Provided first-line technical support and coordinated with central ICT teams to resolve system-level issues\r\npromptly.\r\n• Trained over 100 healthcare professionals on digital systems, significantly improving adoption and reporting\r\ncompliance.\r\n• Streamlined reporting workflows and data submission processes, reducing report generation time by 25%.\r\n• Managed user accounts, access rights, and ensured adherence to data security and IT policies.', 'full-time', NULL, 2);
