(275, 140, 'October 20', '2018', 'Ejura Government Hospital', 'Ejura-Atetubu Road, Ghana', 'Information Technology Manager', '	Collation and analysing of patient data from the various units \r\n(Male’s Ward, Female’s Ward, Maternity Ward, Child Ward and Out Patient Department.)\r\n	Entering data into DHIMS2.\r\n	Ensuring accuracy of patient records.\r\n	Ensuring privacy of patient records.\r\n	Managing and maintaining database.\r\n	Attending Workshops and Training to acquire new skills and knowledge.\r\n	Hardware and software installations.\r\n	Developing of Software and Networking\r\n	Manage information technology and computer systems\r\n	Design, develop, implement and coordinate systems, policies and procedures. etc', 'full-time', 'End of service', 0),
(276, 140, '2016', NULL, 'Ghana Communication Technology University', 'Kumasi', 'Teaching and Library Assistant', '	Selecting, cataloguing and classifying library resources.\r\n	Answering readers’ enquiries.\r\n	Assisting lecturers and developing IT facilities.\r\n	Ensuring the library services meet the needs of group of users (staff and students)\r\n	Talk staff or clients through a series of actions, either face-to-face or over the phone, to help set up systems or resolve issues.\r\n	Installing and configuring computer hardware, software, systems, networks, printers and scanners and Training more junior staff members\r\n	Monitoring and maintaining computer systems and networks\r\n	Repairing and replacing computer equipment', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(277, 141, 'Dec 2019', NULL, 'Local Government Service-Bolgatanga Municipal Assembly', 'C/o P.O. Box 38, Bolgatanga, Upper East Region', 'Development Planning Officer', '•	Facilitate the preparation of Development Plans (i.e. Annual and Medium-Term plans).\r\n•	Sensitizes staff and other stakeholders prior to the implementation of new development policies.\r\n•	Facilitate in the planning, design, implementation, monitoring and evaluation of government and donor development projects and programmes [Gulf of Guinea Northern Regions Social Cohesion Project (World bank), Ghana Productive Safety-Net Project (World bank), Ghana Secondary Cities Support Programme (World bank), Sustainable Cities Project (European Union)].\r\n•	Ensure the development of the capabilities, skills and knowledge of staff.\r\n•	Liaison between the District Planning and Coordinating Unit and all other stakeholders working in the interest of the district.\r\n•	Conduct/facilitate research on behalf of the Assembly in collaboration with development partners for interventions.\r\n•	Appraises and write reports (i.e. quarterly and annual progress reports, project inspection reports, technical reports and minutes for meetings). \r\n•	Facilitate the collection of data for the District Development Data Platform (DDDP by GIZ/MLGRD)\r\n•	Municipal Ghana Labour Exchange Programme (GLEP) focal person. \r\n•	Undertakes any other tasks that may be assigned.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(278, 142, 'May 2018', NULL, 'Lawra Senior High School', 'Lawra, Upper West Region', 'Asisstant Accountant', 'Managed school finances, including fee collection, receipts issuance, and accurate record keeping \r\nPrepared financial records (cash books, ledgers) and assisted in reporting to management\r\nMonitored budgets and expenditures to ensure effective cost control \r\nSupported internal and external audits by organizing records and ensuring compliance with, Public Financial Management Act and Ghana Education Service policies\r\nUtilized ICT tools (e.g., Microsoft Excel, accounting software) for financial reporting, documentation, and client support\r\nPerformed bank reconciliations to ensure accuracy between financial records and bank statements \r\n•Ensured tax compliance and prepared/filed tax returns in accordance with Ghana Revenue Authority regulations \r\nFinance Officer | SD Dombo University Alumni', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(279, 142, 'August 201', NULL, 'Community Water and Sanitation Agency', 'Nandom Water System, Upper West Region', 'Accounts Officer', 'Recorded income and expenditure of the System Management Team\r\nKept financial/ administration records and prepared financial reports\r\nReceived daily sales and payment of bills from revenue collectors and private subscribers\r\nPreparation of Bank Reconciliation Statements\r\nMaintained imprest and accounts for it appropriately\r\nPreparation of payroll of auxiliary staff\r\nPreparation of budgets and monitoring budget execution.\r\nComputation for taxes and filing of tax returns', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(280, 143, 'Nov. 2018', 'March 2019', 'Keta Senior High Technical School', 'P. O. Box kw122, Dzelukope, Keta, Volta Region', 'Teacher', 'I teach Integrated Science. \r\nI prepared lesson plans, practical demonstrations, and assessments of students. \r\nI mentored students in scientific enquiry and laboratory practices. \r\nI contributed to academic improvement and science education development.', '', 'End of contract,', 0),
