(294, 151, '2023 to Da', NULL, 'Bolgatanga Technical University', 'P. O. Box 767, Bolgatanga, U.E.R', 'Part-Time Lecturer', 'Deliver high-quality lectures, tutorial sessions, and practical modules to undergraduate and Higher National Diploma (HND) students.\r\n\r\nInstruct core specialized courses, including Entrepreneurship, Financial Risk Management, Money and Banking, Principles of Financial Accounting, Principles of Micro Economics and Administrative Law.\r\n\r\nDesign comprehensive course outlines, continuous assessment tests, and end-of-semester examinations in compliance with Commission for Technical and Vocational Education and Training (CTVET) guidelines.\r\n\r\nProvide academic counselling, supervise student group projects, and actively participate in departmental consultative meetings.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(295, 152, 'August, 20', NULL, 'Bawku Technical Insttute', 'Bawku, Upper East', 'Teacher', 'Duties\r\nDelivered lectures, tutorials, and practical sessions in Mechanical Engineering to undergraduate students\r\nDesigned and developed course materials, lesson plans, and instructional resources aligned with curriculum objectives\r\nAssessed and evaluated student performance through assignments, tests, laboratory reports, and examinations\r\nProvided academic guidance, mentorship, and support to students to enhance learning outcomes\r\n\r\nSubjects Taught\r\n1. Workshop Processes and Materials\r\n2. Machine Tools Practice\r\n3. Practical\'s \r\n\r\nAdministrative and Leadership Responsibilities (as Head of Department)\r\n1. Provided academic and administrative leadership for the Mechanical Engineering Department\r\n2. Coordinated departmental activities including timetabling, staff supervision, and resource management\r\n3. Managed and mentored teaching staff to ensure quality delivery of instruction\r\nLiaised with school/faculty management on matters relating to curriculum review and departmental development\r\n4. Ensured compliance with institutional policies, academic standards, and accreditation requirements\r\n5. Organized and supervised departmental examinations, practical assessments, and laboratory activities\r\n6. Participated in staff meetings, academic board meetings, and departmental planning sessions\r\n7. Managed departmental equipment, tools, and workshop/laboratory facilities', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
