(301, 154, 'Queensland', 'December 2', 'Queensland International School', 'Accra, Sakonomo', 'Web Developer, ICT Administrator &amp; Computing Facilitator', 'Designed, built, and deployed the school\'s official website and online learning portal using React.js, PHP, and MySQL.\r\n\r\nAdministered the campus network infrastructure, including Wi-Fi configurations, LAN routing, and digital systems (Gallop SMS).\r\n\r\nDelivered standard-based computing curricula covering web technologies, programming logic, algorithms, robotics, and artificial intelligence.\r\n\r\nFounded and coordinate the school Coding Club to mentor students in software foundations.\r\nAchieved a 90% student pass rate within BECE Aggregates 1–3 in the 2025 assessment.', 'full-time', 'Distance and transportation issues', 0),
(302, 154, 'Jan 2023', 'December 2', 'Pioneer International Academy', 'Dawhenya, Greater Accra Region, Ghana', 'Computing Facilitator', 'Facilitated Cambridge-aligned computing lessons covering basic programming concepts and critical digital literacy for Year 1-9 learners.\r\n\r\nDesigned project-based tasks, assignments, and practical coding exercises.\r\n\r\nSupported students in resolving technical challenges in classroom hardware and software environments.', 'full-time', 'For better opportunities', 1),
