(308, 156, 'APRIL 2019', NULL, 'NIHR-GSU GHANA HUB, SoM, UDS TAMALE', 'NIHR-GSU Ghana Hub, 1st floor, Room 3 Credit Union Building, UDS, Dungu, Tamale', 'FINANCE OFFICER', '➢	Prepare project budget for the approval by the funder. \r\n➢	advice management on monitoring budget forecasts to ensure proper spending within budget lines.\r\n➢	I work with IFRS, ISA or Ghana GAAP. \r\n➢	Prepare timely and accurate financial reports to the funder. \r\n➢	Advice management on financial rules and regulation regarding research grants for the maximization of funds. \r\n➢	Track all expenditure to ensure financial utilization within budget. \r\n➢	Provide research grant application support to the School of Medicine in the University for Development Studies. \r\n➢	Ensure compliance with local tax regulations. \r\n➢	advise management in providing contracts and related documentation for staff and other external partners. \r\n➢	Managed a budget of GHS 20 million. \r\n➢	Reduced operational cost by 14 percents through efficiency measures.\r\n➢	Advise management in the procurement of goods and services to ensure value for money. \r\n➢	Prepared monthly bank reconciliation statement. Monitoring the financial statement to be sure there is enough funds in the project’s account.  \r\n➢	Preparation of staff payroll, payment of statutory deductions to the respective Agencies. \r\n➢	Liaise with external Auditors to audit the accounts of the Project.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(309, 156, 'Feb 2014', NULL, 'Mission Aid South Germany, New Apostolic Church, Ghana', 'Accra, Greater Accra Region', 'Accountant', '➢	Travel to regional offices across the country to review financial accounts to ensure proper utilization of funding. \r\n➢	Write and review site visit reports and make recommendations for improvement. \r\n➢	Responsible for the timely and accurate preparation of the financial report of all procurement expenditure. \r\n➢	Prepares quarterly account for onward submission to funder. \r\n➢	Make payments and withhold taxes (WHT) from payments made to vendors and file the returns of all taxes withheld with the Ghana Revenue Authority (GRA) and secure from the GRA Tax Clarence certificate for the vendors.  \r\n➢	Key invoices/vouchers into account software (Hanza), process them for payment, transfer of payment into suppliers/vendors accounts. \r\n➢	Handling and Monitoring of budget control of expenditure, undertaken procurement of goods and services. \r\n➢	Prepares monthly bank reconciliation statement to track expenditure. \r\n➢	Prepare staff payroll, payment of statutory deductions to the respective Agencies. \r\n➢	Payment of all staff travel allowances, per diem and Hotel bills. \r\n➢	Liaise with external Auditors to audit the accounts of the organization.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
