(320, 163, 'January 20', 'May 2026', 'Anglican Diocesan Development and Relief Organization', 'Post Office Box 545', 'Programs Coordinator', '	Providing strategic leadership in program design implementation process.\r\n	Leading the program team in operationalising program plans.\r\n	Fostering and promoting strategic partnerships across multi-stakeholder groups\r\n	Overseeing activities of program managers, Project officers and field officers \r\n	Leading in the design and implementation of Institutional strengthening policy framework. \r\n	Managing programmatic budgets for efficient utilization of funds\r\n	Identifying staff capacity needs through staff appraisals and needs assessment, and facilitating appropriate capacity building approaches. \r\n	Consolidating and reviewing program reports for key strategic partners\r\n	Collaborating with relevant strategic partners and key stakeholders for enhanced agriculture, livelihood and climate resilience interventions.', 'part-time', NULL, 0),
(321, 163, 'September ', NULL, 'Norsaac', 'Tamale, Northern Region', 'Economic Interest Lead', 'Providing strategic leadership, technical guidance to program managers, fostering collaboratives partnerships for enhanced livelihood interventions, leading organizational strengthening and influencing strategies.   \r\nI Provide technical leadership on all six (6) Economic Interest Area Programs (EIA) and ensure all programs are implemented in compliance with contractually agreed targets, scope, duration, budgets, and donor compliance obligations. The Six (6) programs/projects are: Ghana Performance Accountability Activity (GPAA) Program founded by USAID, Women Economic Advancement for Collective Transformation (WEACT) Program founded by OXFAM, Women Innovation Sustainability Enterprise (WISE ADVOCACY) Program, FAIR TAX Project, Digital Property Tax Initiative (DPTI) Program, and HerStart Project. \r\nOther responsibilities are:\r\n▪	Identify and recommend capacity strengthening opportunities for all program managers and project officers\r\n▪	Establish, strengthen, and sustain networking with the public and private stakeholders working on the Economic Empowerment programs and interventions\r\n▪	Serve as second face to program partners at regional, national and global levels\r\n▪	Scout for partnership opportunities and link appropriate program managers for action.\r\n▪	Coordinate with managers and provide relevant updates on programs at national platforms for enhanced partnership\r\n▪	Lead the development and review of donor reports, regularly participate in global/regional/national conferences to maintain the organizations presence in relevant advocacy spaces.\r\n▪	Lead the development of written content on blogs, policy briefs, papers and publications, focused on technical updates in global economic issues. \r\n▪	Serve as connecting point between all program staff and for all programs with donors and supervising all program managers to facilitate program implementation.\r\n▪	Develop internal team tracking mechanisms to track activities of all managers\r\n▪	Provide technical lead in the development of overall workplan/schedules of work that reflect planned activities.\r\n▪	Undertake periodic technical monitoring visits to all EIA programs\r\n▪	Develop tracking mechanisms to strategically participate in various program activities \r\n▪	Maintain organizational standards of satisfaction, quality and performance\r\n▪	Leading the advocacy trajectories of all projects and programs \r\n▪	Plan and undertake team meetings with various managers, undertake periodic team appraisal and identify needs area for team growth, recommend capacity strengthening opportunities for program managers and projects officers.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(322, 163, 'October 20', NULL, 'Blueforce Inc.', NULL, 'Ghana Country Training Coordinator', 'Responsible for providing strategic and operational leadership on overall training policy and approaches, fostering strategic partnership with key Ghana government security and law enforcement agencies for enhanced capacity building in the fight against national and Cross boarder crimes, identifying the training and capacity building needs of key governmental agencies, connecting with the INL in contracting national and international training and capacity building experts for participants training,  coordinating all program administrative and logistical support services, facilitating the development of training manuals, overseeing training planning and implementation processes including coordination and reporting training outcomes, and overseeing the design and implementation of program training monitoring, evaluation, and learning (MEAL) activities in the Regional Training Center (RTC) in Accra, Ghana.', 'full-time', NULL, 2),
(323, 163, 'September ', NULL, 'Anglican Diocesan Development and Relief Organization (ADDRO).', 'P. O. Box 545, Bolgatanga, UER, Ghana', 'Monitoring, Evaluation, and Learning (MEL) Coordinator', 'Responsible for project MEL design, and implementation, serving as technical lead in all processes leading to effective and timeous project outcome and results documentation and communication.', 'full-time', NULL, 3),
