(331, 165, 'March 2026', 'August 201', 'Transsion Technology Ghana Ltd', 'Circle - Accra', 'HR Supervisor', 'Provide strategic leadership to the administrative function, setting clear objectives, aligning team goals with organizational priorities, and driving high performance across the department.\r\n•	Design, implement, and continuously improve administrative systems, policies, and processes to enhance operational effectiveness, scalability, and organizational agility.\r\n•	Oversee the strategic procurement and management of office infrastructure, facilities, and vendor partnerships, ensuring optimal value, service quality, and alignment with business needs.\r\n•	Coordinate high-level executive support services, including strategic scheduling, cross-functional meetings, corporate travel, and enterprise-level events that enhance leadership effectiveness and collaboration.\r\n•	Deliver actionable insights through the preparation of executive-level reports, presentations, and data analytics, supporting informed decision-making and performance tracking for senior leadership.\r\n•	Lead budget planning and cost optimization strategies for administrative operations, identifying opportunities for savings while maintaining service excellence and operational continuity.\r\n•	Champion compliance and governance initiatives, ensuring all administrative operations align with internal policies, regulatory requirements, and corporate risk management standards', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(332, 165, 'May 2023', 'October 20', 'Dynasty Management Consulting', 'Remote', 'Administration &amp; Human Resource Officer', '•	Coordinated administrative and human resource activities for multi-location teams and client organizations.\r\n•	Prepared operational reports, workforce data analysis, and documentation to support management decisions.\r\n•	Implemented HR and administrative policies while supporting recruitment, onboarding, and performance management activities.\r\n•	Supported organizational restructuring and operational improvement initiatives to enhance efficiency and collaboration.\r\n•	Facilitated stakeholder communication, staff coordination, and employee engagement initiatives.', 'full-time', 'End of Service', 1),
