(357, 176, 'JULY 2025', 'MARCH 2019', 'ITC (University of Twente Faculty of Geo-information Science and Earth Observation)', 'LUSPA HQ', 'COUNTRY REPRESENTATIVE PROJECT ADMINISTRATOR', '•	Lead delivery of multi-million-dollar climate change and adaptation initiative with impact-based execution across Ghana and Côte d\'Ivoire\r\n•	Define project scope, goals, success criteria, and deliverables supporting organisational objectives in collaboration with stakeholders (ITC, UN-Habitat, Action Aid Ghana, Habitat for Humanity International and government ministries and departments).\r\n•	Coordinate project planning and implementation sessions, communicate minutes and action items for tracking.\r\n•	Facilitate high collaboration among international project team members, optimising delivery across cultural boundaries.\r\n•	Monitor expenditures against the budget, prepare variance reports, and support financial decision-making in both countries.\r\n•	Coordinate change requests and budget adjustments in line with donor financial management frameworks.\r\n•	Effectively communicate project expectations and status reports to team members and stakeholders in a timely and clear manner.\r\n•	Liaise with project stakeholders (government agencies, UN partners, community organisations), following up on tasks.\r\n•	Work directly with Project Leadership to manage stakeholder relationships and ensure alignment.\r\n•	Coordinate issue and conflict resolution within the project team with timely escalations when necessary.\r\n•	Proactively coordinate changes in project scope, identifying potential crises and contributing to contingency plans.\r\n•	Prepare and deliver project documents, including project plans, progress reports, and presentations, per governance frameworks.\r\n•	Ensure compliance with organisational governance requirements and donor best practices.\r\n•	Collect, clean, structure, and validate project data from multiple sources, ensuring accuracy, consistency, and reliability across technical, financial, and environmental/social datasets.\r\n•	Develop and maintain databases and tracking systems for real-time project monitoring covering activities, budgets, milestones, and performance indicators across Ghana and Côte d\'Ivoire.\r\n•	Prepare analytical and visual reports, briefs, and presentations for Climate Adaptation Fund, UN-Habitat, ITC, government stakeholders, and project partners.\r\n•	Utilise digital data collection tools (Kobo Toolbox, ArcGIS Survey 123), enhancing data accessibility and field data management\r\n•	Monitor project budget utilisation, track expenditures against approved allocations and prepare variance analysis reports.\r\n•	Process travel authorisations, expense claims, consultant payments, and related financial transactions in compliance with organisational policies\r\n•	Maintain accurate financial documentation supporting audits, donor reporting, and internal financial controls.\r\n•	Coordinate with external service providers on event logistics, technical services, and operational support.\r\n•	Provide timely inputs for donor and corporate reporting, ensuring analytical rigour and compliance with Climate Adaptation Fund and UN-Habitat reporting standards.\r\n•	Prepare quarterly progress reports, annual reports, and ad-hoc analytical briefs for project leadership and donors.\r\n•	Document lessons learned, best practices, and innovative approaches from project implementation.\r\n•	Participate in knowledge-sharing initiatives, contributing insights on climate adaptation, project management, and data systems.\r\n•	Support capacity-building activities providing training on monitoring tools, data collection systems, and reporting procedures.', 'full-time', 'BETTER OPPORTUNITY', 0),
(358, 176, 'NOV 2023', 'AUGUST 201', 'Access To Basics (ATB) – Women, Youth &amp; Community Development NGO', 'ACCRA', 'PROGRAM OFFICER', '•	Coordinated implementation of donor-funded community development projects, ensuring alignment with work plans and donor requirements\r\n•	Developed monitoring &amp; evaluation frameworks, establishing data collection systems, performance indicators, and reporting structures\r\n•	Collected and analysed program data using digital tools (Kobo Toolbox), identifying trends and generating evidence-based improvement recommendations\r\n•	Prepared high-quality narrative and financial reports for international donors documenting achievements, challenges, and lessons learned\r\n•	Maintained comprehensive project documentation and data management systems supporting audit and compliance requirements\r\n•	Organised stakeholder workshops and capacity-building sessions, coordinating all logistics including venue booking, travel arrangements, materials preparation, and participant management\r\n•	Developed and maintained project tracking systems, monitoring activities, timelines, budgets, and deliverables\r\n•	Facilitated communication with program participants, partner organisations, and donors, ensuring consistent engagement and timely follow-up\r\n•	Supported resource mobilisation, developing funding proposals and concept notes for international donors\r\n•	Coordinated procurement processes for program materials and services, ensuring value for money and compliance\r\n•	Managed program budgets, tracking expenditures and preparing budget variance analysis reports\r\n•	Coordinated administrative processes, including scheduling, correspondence management, and document preparation\r\n•	Prepared analytical reports and presentations for internal and external audiences', 'full-time', 'PERSONAL TRANSFER', 1),
(359, 176, 'APRIL 2019', 'AUGUST 201', 'Ghana Agricultural Sector Investment Programme (GASIP), Ministry of Food and Agriculture', 'ACCRA', 'PROGRAMME OFFICER', '•	Supported annual work plan development, budget preparation, and activity planning, ensuring alignment with IFAD requirements and government priorities\r\n•	Coordinated implementation activities across 65 districts, liaising with the District Department of Agriculture, district assemblies, government technical departments, and community organisations\r\n•	Prepared project documentation, including concept notes, Terms of Reference, memoranda, and administrative forms\r\n•	Organised and managed logistics for 60+ workshops, training sessions, and stakeholder meetings across Ghana\r\n•	Coordinated travel arrangements (domestic and international), venue bookings, accommodation, materials preparation, and participant management\r\n•	Monitored program budget execution, tracking expenditures against approved allocations and work plans\r\n•	Managed office imprest and prepared monthly petty cash reconciliation reports\r\n•	Supported procurement processes, coordinating vendor selection, contract management, and payment processing\r\n•	Maintained comprehensive financial and procurement documentation supporting audits and compliance reviews\r\n•	Processed mission documentation, including travel authorisations, per diems, expense claims, and reimbursements\r\n•	Served as the official keeper of program records, maintaining comprehensive documentation systems, ensuring data accuracy and security\r\n•	Prepared quarterly and annual reports for IFAD documenting program progress, achievements, challenges, and lessons learned\r\n•	Maintained program trackers, monitoring activities, milestones, budgets, and deliverables against work plans\r\n•	Documented program interactions, field visit reports, and stakeholder meeting outcomes\r\n•	Prepared briefing materials and presentations for senior management, donors, and government officials\r\n•	Facilitated stakeholder consultations, ensuring inclusive participation and follow-up on commitments\r\n•	Represented the program in national forums and coordination meetings with government and development partners\r\n•	Documented lessons learned and best practices contributing to organisational knowledge management\r\n•	Collected and analysed program data across 65 districts using digital tools (Kobo Toolbox, ArcGIS Survey 123), supporting evidence-based management of €50M+ IFAD-funded program\r\n•	Developed and maintained databases and tracking systems monitoring over 400 community savings and loans associations, program activities, financial expenditures, and performance indicators\r\n•	Prepared data summaries and analytical reports identifying engagement patterns, implementation trends, and areas requiring management attention\r\n•	Conducted data quality checks and validation procedures, ensuring the integrity of monitoring data and compliance with IFAD reporting standards', '', 'END OF SERVICE', 2),
(360, 176, 'SEP 2016', NULL, 'Fafraha Community Senior High School, Accra, Ghana', 'ACCRA', 'BUSINESS MANAGEMENT TUTOR', '•	Developed and implemented robust educational strategies through evidence-based planning and analysis while ensuring alignment with curriculum frameworks and examination requirements (WAEC/GES). \r\n•	 Created and delivered engaging lesson plans, sourcing appropriate learning materials, and continuously evaluated teaching methodologies. \r\n•	Maintained high standards of assessment through regular grading, performance monitoring, and detailed record-keeping of student progress. \r\n•	Demonstrated adaptability by specialising in diverse curricula that accounted for students\' varied educational, cultural, and linguistic backgrounds while providing additional support to struggling learners \r\n•	Worked closely with school leadership, department heads, and fellow educators to enhance course content and teaching approaches. \r\n•	Participated actively in curriculum development and revision, ensuring materials remained current and effective. \r\n•	Professional development was prioritised through engagement with current literature, professional organisations, and conference attendance. \r\n•	Provided educational and career guidance, child protection practices, managed student behaviours, and served as a vital link between students and administration. \r\n•	Maintained open communication channels with parents and guardians, ensuring comprehensive support for student development and protection. \r\n•	Maintained accurate attendance records, managed classroom policies, and prepared detailed student assessments and references.', 'full-time', NULL, 3),
