as prioritised through engagement with current literature, professional organisations, and conference attendance. \r\n•	Provided educational and career guidance, child protection practices, managed student behaviours, and served as a vital link between students and administration. \r\n•	Maintained open communication channels with parents and guardians, ensuring comprehensive support for student development and protection. \r\n•	Maintained accurate attendance records, managed classroom policies, and prepared detailed student assessments and references.', 'full-time', NULL, 4),
