(370, 180, '2023', NULL, 'Kulturstudier / Oslo Metropolitan University - Norway (contract basis), Cape Coast – Central Region.', 'https://www.kulturstudier.com/countries/ghana. @ The Center for Development Studies, University of Cape Coast, Ghana.', 'Academic Seminar Leader / Lecturer (Contract basis)', '1. Teach courses on research methods, development theories, culture and development, gender and development, community livelihoods, sociology, etc\r\n2. Coordinate the arrival of students from their home countries (Norway, Sweden &amp; Denmark)\r\n3. Coordinate students’ learning activities both online &amp; face-to-face, e.g., guidance on academic essay writing.\r\n4. Conduct class assignments, exams etc. and record marks\r\n5. Organize research seminars in order to prepare students for field research work in Central Region\r\n6. Lead students to conduct field research in groups and write their dissertations individually\r\n7. Coordinate and lead students’ field research presentations - findings etc.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(371, 180, '2021', NULL, 'Forestry Commission', 'C/o Forestry Commission Ahafo Regional Office  P. O. Box GS 217 Goaso Ahafo Region', 'Field Supervisor, HR Officer, Regional PR Officer, Regional Field Monitoring Team Member', '1. Supervise field officers and farmers to plant trees in the Bolgatanga (on-reserve and off-reserve forest lands).\r\n2. Prepare field reports and timesheets for Management in the Bolgatanga Forest Office.\r\n3. Demarcate plots/acres to field staff and farmers for planting in the various zones, Bolgatanga.\r\n4. Staff management, record keeping, field monitoring, needs assessment and targets setting and appraisal etc. for staff in all the 9 Lawra Forest Districts, Upper West Region.\r\n5. Organizing staff meeting, welfare benefits, staff validation, administrative activities, procurement, advocacy, etc. in all the 9 Lawra Forest Districts, Upper West Region.\r\n6. Regional field monitoring on forest activities in the Ahafo region, media coordination for public awareness on forest activities, report writing, Newsletters, videos, pictures etc.\r\n7. High level stakeholder engagements, community engagements on friendly forest practices, zero deforestation campaign, afforestation campaign, agroforestry advocacy etc., Ahafo Region.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(372, 181, 'February 2', 'May 2023', 'Fortress Oil &amp; Gas / Asset Integrity', 'Greater Accra', 'Associate Software Developer', '• Designed and developed Python backend logic handling real-time data processing for 500+ asset data points, ensuring accurate rendering and data integrity across all modules. \r\n\r\n• Led full-cycle 3D photogrammetry reconstruction pipeline, transforming 500+ 2D images into 3D point-clouds and textured models, cutting manual inspection preparation time by ~30%\r\n\r\n• Wrote unit tests achieving 80%+ backend coverage across Python modules, reducing regression issues during iterative deployments. \r\n\r\n• Coordinated weekly code reviews across a 4-person team, enforcing coding standards and best practices — resulting in 100% on-schedule project delivery. \r\n\r\n• Built and maintained desktop application backend using PySide6/PyQt, reducing manual workflow steps by ~40% for asset integrity teams.', 'part-time', 'Project was shelved due to insufficient fund to continue', 0),
(373, 181, 'Feb 2024', 'Feb 2023', 'Vibraniuum Technologies', 'Greater Accra', 'Software Developer', '• Designed and implemented 15+ RESTful API endpoints with scalable data models; reduced average API response time by ~20% through query optimisation and efficient schema design.\r\n• Rebuilt authentication and authorisation workflow using secure token-based mechanisms (JWT/RBAC), cutting customer onboarding time by 30% and eliminating a class of login-related support tickets. \r\n• Delivered 6+ backend modules across 3 client projects applying SOLID principles and clean architecture— all delivered on time and within scope. \r\n• Participated in bi-weekly code reviews and architectural discussions, contributing improvements adopted across 3 team projects.', '', 'Fulfilled the terms of the contract and signed-off, handing over documents and other wiki to the team lead.', 1),
(374, 181, 'July 2023', 'Mar 2022', 'Upworks --(A global freelance platform for contract client)', 'Remote(Global)', 'Freelance Back-End Developer', '• Built and maintained RESTful APIs, database schemas, and authentication systems for 3+ client projects using PHP (Laravel), and Python. \r\n• Managed full project lifecycles from requirement gathering and system design through to deployment —applying clean code and OOP principles throughout. \r\n• Implemented security measures including input validation, error handling, and structured logging to protect against vulnerabilities.', 'full-time', 'The company was heavy impacted financially by COVID-19 and lock-down and had to layoff some of his staff.', 2),
(375, 181, 'Nov 2023', NULL, 'Browsio (https://reachvolunteering.org.uk/org/browsio)', 'London, United Kingdom (Remote)', 'Software Developer', '• Built a secure authentication microservice for NGO, charity, and individual customer onboarding, incorporating ACID-compliant database schema design, error handling, logging, and security best\r\npractices. \r\n• Designed and implemented one-to-one database schema in Laravel with migration files and associated models, maintaining data integrity across all operations. \r\n• Optimised customer onboarding UX flows, resulting in a 25% increase in user retention rate. \r\n• Authored detailed use case documentation to guide developers on action flow, improving team velocity and code consistency.', 'full-time', NULL, 3),
(376, 181, 'Jul 2022', NULL, 'Virdge Digital', 'Greater Accra', 'Web Developer', '• Enhanced event ticket purchase aggregation in core PHP, boosting concurrent processing performance by 35% and eliminating billing errors. \r\n• Implemented ACID compliance through systematic database normalisation, improving data reliability and reducing query errors across 4 core tables. \r\n• Refactored and optimised a broken PHP/Laravel Movie API, restoring full functionality and improving maintainability through clean code restructuring. \r\n• Reduced page load times by ~50% for image-heavy pages through browser-side image optimisation and lazy loading.', 'full-time', NULL, 4),
(377, 181, 'Jan 2020', NULL, 'Essien Arthur Technologies Ltd', 'Greater Accra', 'Software Developer', '• Troubleshoot and resolved 50+ production issues across client applications by analysing logs and data, reducing recurring bug rates by ~45%. \r\n• Delivered backend features across 5+ client projects, applying OOP and clean code practices —contributing to a consistent on-time delivery record. \r\n• Led monthly internal training sessions for a team of 6 developers on backend best practices, versioncontrol workflows, and emerging frameworks.', 'full-time', NULL, 5),
(378, 182, 'OCTOBER 20', 'JUNE 2024', 'COLLEGE OF NURSING AND MIDWIFERY-TANO DUMASI', 'NYINAHIN, AHANTI REGION', 'I.T OFFICER', '	Lectures the Nursing Informatics course, equipping nursing students with knowledge and practical skills in health information systems, electronic medical records, and the application of ICT in healthcare delivery\r\n	Lectures Statistics course, equipping nursing students with knowledge and practical skills in data collection, analysis, interpretation, biostatistics, and the application of statistical methods in healthcare decision-making and research.\r\n	Manage and maintain the college’s ICT infrastructure, including servers, networks, and computer systems.\r\n	Installs and maintains basic computer software and hardware in the ICT laboratory.\r\n	Provide technical support to staff and students, ensuring smooth operation of academic and administrative digital platforms.\r\n	Oversee installation, configuration, and troubleshooting of hardware, software, and network devices.\r\n	Ensure data security, backup, and recovery procedures to safeguard institutional information.\r\n	Support e-learning systems and digital tools to enhance teaching and learning processes.\r\n	Develop and implement IT policies, procedures, and user guidelines in line with institutional goals.\r\n	Collaborate with management to identify, plan, and implement technology-driven solutions for improved efficiency.\r\n	Conducts class exercises, tests, assignments, and examinations. \r\n	Manage and maintain the college’s database systems to ensure data accuracy, security, and accessibility. \r\n	Update, organize, and monitor institutional records and digital information within the database system. \r\n	Perform regular database backups, troubleshooting, and system maintenance to ensure smooth operations. \r\n	Assist staff and management in retrieving, processing, and managing data for administrative and academic purposes. \r\n	Ensure confidentiality and integrity of institutional data through proper database management practices.', 'full-time', 'BETTER OPPORTUNITY', 0),
