(385, 184, 'AUGUST 202', 'AUGUST 202', 'DESERT PASTURES INTERNATIONAL SCHOOL | BOLGATANGA', 'BOLGATANGA, UPPER EAST', 'ICT FACILITATOR &amp; I.T OFFICER', '	Prepared lesson notes and delivered ICT lessons to students. \r\n	Developed a Student Marks Management System that automated report generation and migrated the school from manual to digital records.\r\n	Facilitated ICT lessons for students, introducing them to computer fundamentals and literacy, digital tools, basic programming concepts, and problem-solving skills.\r\n	Conducted class exercises, tests, assignments, and examinations. \r\n	Managed and supervised students during practical ICT sessions. \r\n	Supported teachers in integrating technology into classroom instruction to enhance learning outcomes.\r\n	Provided technical support by troubleshooting hardware, software, and network issues within the school.\r\n	Managed and maintained the school’s ICT infrastructure, including computer labs and administrative systems.\r\n	Installed and maintained basic computer software and hardware in the ICT laboratory.\r\n	Conducted class exercises, tests, assignments, and examinations. \r\n	Managed and supervised students during practical ICT sessions. \r\n	Maintained classroom discipline and ensured an effective learning environment. \r\n	Provided academic guidance and support to students. \r\n	Managed student records, attendance, and assessment reports.  \r\n	Assisted in organizing school academic and ICT-related activities.', '', 'END OF SERVICE PERIOD', 1),
(386, 184, 'SEPTEMBER ', NULL, 'BOLGATANGA NURSING TRAINING COLLEGE', 'BOLGATANGA-UPPER EAST', 'NATIONAL SERVICE PERSONNEL', '	Assisted in lecturing Nursing Informatics course, introducing students to health information systems, electronic medical records, and the role of ICT in modern healthcare.\r\n	Assisted in the management and maintenance of ICT infrastructure, including computer labs and networks.\r\n	Provided IT support to staff and students, troubleshooting hardware, software, and network issues.\r\n	Collaborated with the IT department in implementing security measures, updates, and system improvements.\r\n	Supported lecturers and administrators in the use of digital tools for teaching, research, and office work.', 'full-time', NULL, 2),
(387, 185, '2023', 'Till date', 'Kulturstudier/Oslo Metropolitan University (contract basis), Cape Coast – Central Region', 'https://www.kulturstudier.com/countries/ghana. University of Cape Coast, Central Region', 'Academic Seminar Leader / Lecturer (Contract basis)', '1. Teach courses like research methods, development communication, rural sociology, culture and development, development theories, political economy, livelihoods, development governance etc.\r\n2. Coordinate the arrival of students from their home countries (Norway, Sweden &amp; Denmark)\r\n3. Coordinates students’ learning activities both online &amp; face-to-face, e.g., guidance on academic essay writing.\r\n4. Conduct exams and assignments and records marks\r\n5. Organize research seminars in order to prepare students for field research work in Central Region\r\n6. Lead students to conduct field research in groups and write their dissertations individually\r\n7. Coordinates students’ field research presentations - findings etc.', 'full-time', 'Still on the job', 0),
(388, 185, '2021', NULL, 'Forestry Commission', 'C/o Forestry Commission Ahafo Regional Office  P. O. Box GS 217 Goaso Ahafo Region', 'Field Supervisor, HR Officer, Regional PR Officer, Regional Field Monitoring Team Member', '1.Supervise field officers and farmers to plant trees in the Bolgatanga (on-reserve and off-reserve forest lands).\r\n2.Prepare field reports and timesheets for Management in the Bolgatanga Forest Office.\r\n3.Demarcate plots/acres to field staff and farmers for planting in the various zones, Bolgatanga.\r\n4.Staff management, record keeping, field monitoring, needs assessment and targets setting and appraisal etc. for staff in all the 9 Lawra Forest Districts, Upper West Region.\r\n5.Organizing staff meeting, welfare benefits, staff validation, administrative activities, procurement, advocacy, etc. in all the 9 Lawra Forest Districts, Upper West Region.\r\n6.Regional field monitoring on forest activities in the Ahafo region, media coordination for public awareness on forest activities, report writing, Newsletters, videos, pictures etc.\r\n7.High level stakeholder engagements, community engagements on friendly forest practices, zero deforestation campaign, afforestation campaign, agroforestry advocacy etc., Ahafo Region.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(389, 186, 'NOV 2023', 'AUG 2023', 'DOCUTECH GHANA LIMITED', 'Borteyman -Tema West District, Opposite Community 18 Junction, Accra – Tema Motorway, GP address: GD-306-4193.', 'IT SUPPORT TECHNICIAN', '1. Technical Support: Provides first-level technical support to end-users, resolving\r\nhardware, software, and network issues.\r\n2. Troubleshooting: Diagnoses and resolves technical problems both remotely and in\r\nperson.\r\n3. System Maintenance: Conduct regular maintenance on computer systems (Xerox printers most especially) and\r\nnetworks to ensure optimal performance.\r\n4. User Training: Trains staff on new hardware installations, ensuring smooth transitions\r\nand efficient use.\r\n5. Documentation: Creates and maintain detailed documentation of technical issues\r\nand solutions for future reference.\r\n6. Customer Service: Deliver excellent customer service, ensuring user satisfaction and\r\neffective communication.\r\n7. Collaboration: works closely with other IT team members to coordinate support efforts\r\nand share knowledge.', 'part-time', NULL, 0),
(390, 186, 'AUG 2021', NULL, 'UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES', 'TAMALE', 'IT SUPPORT', '• Created help desk tickets, troubleshoot and resolved desktop issues.\r\n• Prepared new computers and mobile devices according to internal policies on\r\nstandardized software and security deployments.\r\n• Answered questions and provided information to employees about new software and\r\nhardware.\r\n• Delivered onsite technical support to employees.\r\n• Provided front-end website development using WordPress.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
