(412, 196, 'April, 201', 'August, 20', 'Wa Technical Institute', 'Wa Technical Institute Box 238 Wa', 'Head of Department Electronic Engineering / Academic board Secretary', 'As Head of Department for Electronic Engineering and Secretary to the Academic Board,  I allocate classes and period to facilitators, plan, coordinate, and supervise lesson delivery across all levels of the department, ensuring alignment with TVET standards and competency-based education frameworks, while monitor and supervise facilitators through lesson observations and provide feedback. In addition, I chair regular and emergency departmental meetings. I monitor learners\' progress, attendance, and practical competency assessments, guide them in hands-on projects, and prepare them for industrial attachment, while also teach subjects including Electrical Circuit Analysis, Digital Electronics and Logic Gates, AC Circuit Theory, Power Transformers, Electronic Components and Devices, Power Electronics, and Practical Training. I prepare departmental reports, budgets, and requisitions for tools, equipment, and materials, maintain records of assessments and departmental activities, liaise with school administration, industry partners, and other relevant bodies, ensure examination question papers are set and marked on time, and enforce workshop safety compliance among both facilitators and learners during practical. As Secretary to the Academic Board, I organize and prepare agendas for board meetings in consultation with the chairperson, record and present minutes, brief management on board outcomes, convey management responses back to the board, assist in supervising examinations, and provide administrative support to the Vice Principal Academic.', 'full-time', 'Better opportunity and job satisfactory', 0),
