(427, 203, 'June, 2022', 'June, 2022', 'Jaman South Municipal Assembly', 'Drobo, Bono Region', 'Quantity Surveyor', '	Preparation of tender documents, budgets, and detailed costs for labor, materials, and equipment for projects.\r\n	Prepare draft and priced bills of quantities for tenders \r\n	Evaluation of tenders and the preparation of evaluation reports for projects\r\n	Preparation of contract documents\r\n	Conducting site visits, measuring project progress, preparing monthly client applications, and producing valuation reports for payments\r\n	Preparation of interim and final payment certificates \r\n	Projects supervision and monitoring\r\n	Preparation of monthly, quarterly, and yearly progress reports on ongoing projects', 'full-time', 'Better opportunity', 0),
(428, 203, 'March, 201', NULL, 'St. Joseph\'s Technical Institute', 'Saboba, Northern Region', 'Teacher', '	Taught Construction practises and practicals, set exam questions, invigilate exams, and mark and grade students\r\n	Develop and implement instructional plans for the curriculum designed for various construction trades.\r\n	Teach students fundamental skills and techniques in hands-on construction projects.\r\n	Assess student performance and provide constructive feedback to promote skill development.\r\n	Ensure a safe and organized classroom and workshop environment.\r\n	Manage tools and equipment used in training\r\n	Guide students in the laboratory to undertake practical work to gain skills and experience', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(429, 204, 'Sept 2020', NULL, 'Navrongo Health Research Centre', 'Navrongo, Upper East Region, Ghana', 'Research Officer, Biomedical Science Department', '1. Conduct laboratory sample processing, quality control, and biosafety procedures for infectious disease studies (Lassa fever, enteroviruses, malaria).\r\n\r\n2. Design and analyse diagnostic and surveillance data using R, Python, Stata.\r\n\r\n3. Lead genomic epidemiology (WGS) and antimicrobial resistance projects.\r\n\r\n4. Collaborate on vaccine trials and co‑infection studies relevant to medical laboratory diagnostics.\r\n\r\n5. Supervise data management and reporting; contribute to research proposals and manuscripts', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(430, 205, 'Jan 2024', NULL, 'German Insititute of Business and Technology', 'German-IBT, Reiss Junction Road, Accra, Ghana', 'Software Engineer', 'Designed and integrated RESTful APIs to connect frontend applications with backend services, applying interface logic and data-fetching strategies relevant to system integration across complex environments\r\n\r\nImplemented role-based access control and JWT authentication flows, demonstrating applied knowledge of\r\naccess management and IT security fundamentals\r\n\r\nBuilt and maintained scalable backend services using Node.js and Express, managing MySQL and MongoDB databases with optimised query patterns to support reliable data operations\r\n\r\nLed cross-functional QA cycles across multiple platforms, collaborating with stakeholders to identify issues, drive resolution, and ensure consistent system performance\r\n\r\nApplied continuous improvement principles to codebase architecture, introducing code-splitting, lazy loading, and state management patterns that improved application performance and maintainability\r\n\r\nWrote automation scripts using Node.js to streamline repetitive data-handling and workflow tasks, reducing manual effort and improving operational efficiency', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(431, 206, 'September,', NULL, 'Zebilla Senior High/Technical School', 'Zebilla Senior High/Technical School, Post Office Box 9, Zebilla.', 'Mathematics teacher', 'Taught both core and elective Mathematics. Also served as Nkrumah house Master', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(432, 207, '2024', NULL, 'CVF/V20', 'AFRICA TRADE HOUSE, ACCRA', 'IT/WEB ANALYST', 'System Administration  \r\nOversee office IT infrastructure including routers, printers, phones, and broadband services. Ensure uptime, troubleshoot issues, and document configurations.\r\n\r\nWeb Analytics  \r\nCollect and analyze website traffic data using tools like Google Analytics or Adobe Analytics. Identify trends, user behaviors, and conversion patterns to improve site performance.\r\n\r\nTechnical Documentation  \r\nMaintain detailed notes on IT assets, configurations, and troubleshooting history. Provide structured handover documentation for continuity.\r\n\r\nData Reporting  \r\nBuild dashboards and reports for stakeholders, translating complex data into actionable insights.\r\n\r\nCollaboration  \r\nAct as liaison between IT, marketing, and management teams. Ensure technical requirements align with organizational goals.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(433, 207, '2021', NULL, 'VATEBRA LIMITED', '10 BOULEVE, WEST LANDS, ACCRA', 'SOFTWARE ENGINEER', 'Software Design  \r\nArchitect system structures, define requirements, and plan solutions that meet business and user needs.\r\n\r\nCoding &amp; Development  \r\nWrite clean, efficient, and maintainable code using languages such as Python, Java, C++, or JavaScript.\r\n\r\nTesting &amp; Quality Assurance  \r\nConduct unit, integration, and system testing to ensure software reliability and performance.\r\n\r\nMaintenance &amp; Updates  \r\nMonitor applications post-deployment, fix bugs, and roll out updates to improve functionality.\r\n\r\nCollaboration  \r\nWork with product managers, designers, and other engineers to align technical solutions with organizational goals.\r\n\r\nProgramming Languages: Python, Java, C++, JavaScript, SQL.\r\n\r\nProblem-Solving: Analytical thinking to break down complex issues.\r\n\r\nAlgorithms &amp; Data Structures: Optimize performance and scalability.\r\n\r\nObject-Oriented Design: Build modular, reusable, and maintainable systems.\r\n\r\nCollaboration Tools: Jira, GitHub, Confluence, Slack.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(434, 208, 'September,', 'August 201', 'Opoku Ware Senior High School', 'P.O.Box 849, Kumasi-Santasi', 'Teacher', 'Subjects: Core and Additional Mathematics \r\n\r\nDuties:\r\n\r\ni.	Developed and delivered lessons in General and Advanced Mathematics in accordance with the curriculum.\r\nii.	Designed practical assignments and Projects to bridge the gap between theory and practice\r\niii.	Evaluation of students’ performance through continuous assessment in order to identify learning gabs for remediation.', '', 'End of Service', 0),
(435, 208, 'November 2', NULL, 'Obuasi Senior High Technical School', 'Obuasi, Ashanti Region.', 'Teacher', 'Subjects Taught: Core and Additional Mathematics\r\nDuties\r\ni.	Developed and delivered lessons in General and Advanced Mathematics in accordance with GES curriculum.\r\nii.	Designed practical assignments and Projects to bridge the gap between theory and practice\r\niii.	Evaluation of students’ performance through continuous assessment in order to identify learning gabs for remediation.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(436, 208, 'September,', NULL, 'Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology', 'Kumasi, Ashanti Region', 'Teaching and Research Assistant', 'Duties\r\ni.	Conducted full time lectures and tutorials, marked and graded assessment in the  \r\n             following courses;\r\n•	Mathematical optimization\r\n•	Algebra\r\n•	Mathematical Economics\r\n•	Differential Equations\r\n•	Operations Research\r\n\r\nii.	 Held special mathematics classes for foreign medical students who are deficient in advanced mathematics. \r\niii.	Prepared lecture materials and assisted in organizing departmental meetings', 'full-time', NULL, 2),
(437, 209, 'January 20', NULL, 'Nyong Technical Institute/GTVET', 'Nyong, Karaga District of Northern Region.', 'Senior Assistant, General Administration', '1.Receiving end dispatching of letters. \r\n2. Writing all official correspondence. \r\n3. Recording minutes during meetings. \r\n4. Managing students records and files. \r\n5. Managing staff files and records. \r\n6. Any other duties assigned by the Principal.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(438, 210, '2012-DATE', '2019', 'GHANA EDUCATION SERVICE', 'P.O.BOX M 45 ACCRA', 'TEACHER/HEAD OF DEPARTMENT', '**Main Duties, Subjects Taught, and Key Responsibilities**\r\n\r\n* Teach Information and Communication Technology (ICT) and related computing subjects to Senior High School students in accordance with the national curriculum.\r\n* Prepare lesson notes, schemes of work, instructional materials, assessments, and examinations to facilitate effective teaching and learning.\r\n* Deliver practical and theoretical instruction in areas such as computer applications, digital literacy, programming fundamentals, networking, internet technologies, and information systems.\r\n* Assess students\' academic performance through assignments, quizzes, practical exercises, projects, and examinations, and provide appropriate feedback.\r\n* Supervise students during practical laboratory sessions and ensure the effective utilization and maintenance of ICT facilities and equipment.\r\n* Serve as Head of the ICT Department, providing academic and administrative leadership for departmental activities.\r\n* Coordinate departmental planning, curriculum implementation, timetabling, examinations, and quality assurance activities.\r\n* Mentor and supervise teachers within the department, promoting effective teaching practices and professional development.\r\n* Monitor students\' academic progress and implement strategies to improve learning outcomes and examination performance.\r\n* Participate in school committees, staff meetings, and institutional development initiatives.\r\n* Promote the integration of information technology and digital tools into teaching, learning, and administrative processes.\r\n* Guide students in project work, career development, and participation in ICT-related competitions and activities.\r\n* Ensure compliance with educational policies, institutional regulations, and professional standards of teaching practice.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(439, 210, '2019', NULL, 'MODAL UNIVERSITY COLLEGE, SOGAKOPE', 'MODAL UNIVERSITY COLLEGE, SOGAKOPE', 'PARTTIME LECTURER', '**Main Duties, Subjects Taught, and Key Responsibilities**\r\n\r\n* Delivered undergraduate-level instruction in Introduction to Computers and Introduction to Databases within the Department of Computer Science.\r\n* Prepared and delivered lectures, tutorials, practical sessions, and instructional materials in accordance with approved course outlines and academic standards.\r\n* Introduced students to fundamental computing concepts, including computer hardware, software systems, operating systems, networking fundamentals, and digital literacy.\r\n* Taught database concepts, including data modeling, relational database systems, database design principles, Structured Query Language (SQL), normalization, and database management techniques.\r\n* Developed course assessments, assignments, quizzes, practical exercises, and examinations to evaluate student learning outcomes.\r\n* Supervised student practical work, projects, and laboratory activities, ensuring effective application of theoretical concepts.\r\n* Provided academic guidance, mentoring, and consultation to students regarding coursework and project-related activities.\r\n* Assessed and graded student performance and submitted results in accordance with institutional academic policies.\r\n* Participated in departmental academic activities, curriculum delivery, and quality assurance processes.\r\n* Promoted the integration of current computing technologies and industry-relevant practices into teaching and learning.\r\n* Supported the development of students\' analytical, problem-solving, and technical skills in computer science and information technology.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(440, 211, 'July 2024-', NULL, 'ABG Consult', 'Greater Accra', 'Audit Associate', 'Conducted audits of client financial records to ensure compliance with regulations and\r\nProcessed payroll and ensured compliance with labor and tax regulations\r\nMonitored and recorded daily financial transactions to improve reporting accuracy standards\r\nManaged VAT, PAYE ,and statutory taxfilings for multiple clients\r\nPerformed inventory costing and reconciliations to support accurate financial reporting', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(441, 212, NULL, NULL, 'J’Effect CCTU Driving School', 'Box 6 Kwabeng-Bomaa', 'Administrative Officer/Driver', 'Assistant in recruiting drivers.\r\nDaily routine checks.\r\nDefensive driving.\r\nChauffeur to Managing Director.\r\nScheduling drivers to their respective fields.\r\nVehicle tracking.\r\nTraining drivers.\r\nFuel monitoring with the aid of mileage recording.\r\nAssigned vehicles for maintenance.\r\nAdministrative support.\r\nCustomer care.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(442, 213, 'September,', 'August, 20', 'Wa Technical Institute', 'Wa Technical Institute Box 238 Wa', 'Head of Department Technical Drawing', 'Lead and coordinate the day-to-day running of the Drawing Department, ensuring students receive practical, skill-focused instruction in technical and creative drawing. Teach core subjects including Technical Drawing, Geometrical and Mechanical Drawing, Building Drawing, and Freehand/Artistic Drawing across various year groups.\r\nResponsibilities include developing lesson plans and schemes of work, supervising departmental teachers, and maintaining drawing studios and equipment. Assess and evaluate student work through practical, projects, and end-of-term examinations, while also preparing students for external certification exams.\r\nCollaborate with school management on curriculum planning, resource allocation, and departmental budgeting. Mentor junior staff, organize inter-departmental activities, and ensure the department meets both national curriculum standards and the hands-on demands of technical and vocational education.\r\nAt the core of the role is helping students develop spatial thinking, precision, and creative problem-solving skills they will carry directly into the world of work or further technical training.', 'full-time', 'Better opportunity and job satisfactory', 0),
(443, 213, 'September,', NULL, 'Ponyentanga R/C Junior High School, Ghana Education Service', 'Wa West District Upper West Region', 'Assistant Head Teacher', 'Supported the Head teacher in the daily administration and smooth running of the school, stepping in to manage the school in their absence.\r\nSupervised teachers and pupils, monitored attendance, maintained school discipline, and coordinated timetables, duty rosters, and school events.\r\nEnsured curriculum delivery aligned with the GES scheme of work, supported classroom teachers, and assisted in organising school-based assessments and BECE preparations.\r\nHandled pupil welfare, parent concerns, and staff matters with care and professionalism, while serving as a link between teachers, parents, the PTA, and school leadership.\r\nMaintained assigned teaching duties, managed school records and GES returns, and contributed actively to school improvement and community engagement.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(444, 214, 'Jan 2021', NULL, 'PKF Accountants and Business Consultancy', 'Accra', 'Audit Senior', 'Lead and execute audit engagements across multiple industries, ensuring \r\ncompliance with IFRS and regulatory standards \r\n• Perform analytical and substantive testing to detect material misstatements and \r\nreduce financial risk \r\n• Identify control weaknesses and fraud indicators through analysis of large and \r\ncomplex datasets \r\n• Prepare statutory accounts and review financial statement disclosures for \r\naccuracy and completeness \r\n• Utilize CaseWare and Inflo audit software to enhance audit efficiency and \r\nreporting accuracy \r\n• Support tax computations and filings by liaising with the Ghana Revenue \r\nAuthority (GRA) \r\n• Monitor audit progress against budgets, improving cost control and project \r\ndelivery timelines \r\n• Produce detailed audit reports to support strategic decision-making for clients \r\n• Conduct follow-up reviews to ensure implementation of corrective actions', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(445, 215, '2014', NULL, 'T I Ahmadiyya Junior High School', 'Post Office Box 88, Bolgatanga', 'Headmaster', '1) Monitoring the teaching, learning, attendance, movement, conduct of teachers and learners during school hours\r\n2) Administration: link between school and office, school community, assembly, NGOs, and other stakeholders \r\n3) Soliciting for support for the school development through organizing PTA, SMC, SPAM, and other meetings\r\n4) Ensuring high academic achievements for the school through good leadership, motivating facilitators and ensuring adequate teaching and learning resources are available and that the learning environment is conducive. \r\n5) Ensuring that the data of learners, teachers, the school and others\' important documents are saved and readily available when the need arises.\r\n6) Ensuring facilitators build their capacities in new and emerging strategies of teaching and learning order to facilitate teaching.\r\n7) Ensuring the right and competent facilitators are in my school by recommending transfers of facilitators who are not ready to work for the growth of the school.\r\n8) Ensure that hard-working facilitators are duly recognised at the right time. These are just a few.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(446, 215, '1st Septem', NULL, 'Yarigabisi Primary and T I JHS respectfully', 'Bolgatangta', 'Classroom teacher and Subject teacher', 'Taught at Yarigabisi Primary as a classroom teacher from 1st September 2007 to 1st September 2008.\r\nTaught at T I Ahmadiyya Junior High School from 1st September, 2008 to 1st September, 2014 as an English and ICT Facilitator', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
