(539, 256, 'June', NULL, 'Tontrac ghana', 'Tema greater accra Region', 'IT/CCTV', 'Monitored CCTV surveillance systems to ensure the safety and security of personnel, assets, and facilities.\r\nOperated and maintained CCTV cameras, Digital Video Recorders (DVRs), and Network Video Recorders (NVRs).\r\nConducted routine inspections and preventive maintenance of surveillance equipment.\r\nTroubleshot and resolved hardware, software, and network connectivity issues affecting CCTV systems.\r\nInstalled, configured, and upgraded CCTV cameras, access control systems, and related security devices.\r\nRetrieved, reviewed, and archived video footage for investigations and incident reporting.\r\nGenerated incident reports and provided video evidence to management and authorized personnel when required.\r\nMonitored alarm systems and coordinated responses to security incidents.\r\nAssisted users with IT-related issues, including computer hardware, software, printers, and network connectivity.\r\nMaintained user accounts, system access permissions, and security protocols.\r\nCollaborated with security personnel and management to improve security operations and system effectiveness.\r\nEnsured compliance with organizational security policies and data protection requirements.\r\nMaintained accurate records of equipment inventories, maintenance activities, and system performance.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(540, 256, 'September ', NULL, 'Margins ID Group', 'Accra Central, Greater Accra Region', 'Operation Officer', 'Led end-to-end production processes for non-citizen ID cards, ensuring accuracy, security, and compliance with regulatory standards.\r\nConducted applicant interviews to verify identity information and ensure data authenticity.\r\nManaged data collection, validation, and entry processes while maintaining strict confidentiality and data integrity.\r\nSupervised biometric capture processes including fingerprints and photographs.\r\nCoordinated data management workflows, ensuring seamless transition from registration to card production.\r\nPerformed data quality checks and resolved discrepancies in applicant records.\r\nGenerated operational and analytical reports to support decision-making and performance tracking.\r\nCollaborated with technical teams to troubleshoot system issues and improve process efficiency.\r\nParticipated in field surveys and registration exercises to support large-scale enrollment initiatives.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(541, 256, 'June 2023', NULL, 'G4S Ghana Security Services', 'Greater Accra Region', 'CCTV Operator', 'Monitored surveillance systems to detect suspicious activities and prevent security breaches.\r\nConducted incident documentation and reporting for investigation and audit purposes.\r\nEnsured continuous functionality of CCTV systems and reported technical faults.\r\nProvided intelligence support to security teams through video analysis.\r\n\r\nMonitored surveillance systems to detect suspicious activities and prevent security breaches.\r\nConducted incident documentation and reporting for investigation and audit purposes.\r\nEnsured continuous functionality of CCTV systems and reported technical faults.\r\nProvided intelligence support to security teams through video analysis.', 'full-time', NULL, 2),
(542, 258, 'April, 202', NULL, 'Judicial Service of Ghana', 'Box BL 6', 'Deputy Chief Registrar/Cashier', '1. Preparation of bank reconciliation statement and summary of the Court.\r\n\r\n2. Maintain bookkeeping of the Court.\r\n\r\n3. Assist in updating office asset register and tagging of the court assets.\r\n\r\n4. Ensures compliance with established internal control procedures by examining records, reports, operating practices, and documentations.\r\n\r\n5. Support the reviewing of invoices, payments, vouchers and receipts\r\nProcess and payment of court compensations.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(543, 259, 'Jan, 2025', 'Nov, 2024', 'NAVRONGO-BOLGATANGA CATHOLIC DIOCESAN DEVELOPMENT ORGANISATION (NABOCADO)', 'P. O. Box 351', 'BUSINESS AND INVESTMENT DIRECTOR', '1.	Coordinate and ensure that all business units are operating effectively, efficiently and profitably\r\n2.	Lead in establishment of Navrongo - Bolgatanga Catholic Credit Society for Development (NABOCCSOD) and ensure its growth and development.\r\n3.	Research into new viable businesses and lead in business proposals development towards sustainable business growth thereby increasing Diocesan resource mobilization \r\n4.	Lead in Fund raising efforts towards business growth and sustainability of the Diocese and also development of Diocesan Business Strategic plan.\r\n5.	Lead the implementation of the Diocesan Strategic plan for the Diocesan Financial Administrator\r\n6.	Prepare quarterly, half yearly and annual business performance reports to the Board, train and mentor staff on business management on market dynamics.\r\n7.	Develop the business, sales and marketing strategies for various business units, recommend equity on investment to the Board.\r\n8.	Examine risks and potentials for business opportunities, educate, lead and supervise members of the business development team to ensure targets are achieved.', 'full-time', 'Better Opportunity', 0),
(544, 259, 'Jan, 2021', 'March, 202', 'THE BABA TREE COMPANY LTD', 'The Baba Tree Company Ltd  Hakim House, Asumda Estates, Tamale Road, Tindonsobligo -   Bolgatanga', 'ACCOUNTANT AND ADMINISTRATOR', '1.	I worked closely with the director of the company and oversee/supervise and offer training/advise to the various heads of departments/units such as the accounts unit, the shipping/logistics unit, the design and website/photography and the leather/finishing department and also responding to mails from clients from overseas.\r\n2.	I worked together with consultants and other contract staff to develop, train where necessary and implement critical financial and non-financial strategies that can help sustain the company while closely working with staff of the Ghana Revenue Authority to ensure compliance.  \r\n3.	Processing of daily purchases of Baskets, dye materials and packaging materials and payment of labour cost into Quickbooks.\r\n4.	Processing of staff salaries and other end of year bonuses for staff. \r\n5.	Managing receivables and payables of customers to ensure minimal exchange losses arising from creditors.\r\n6.	Generating trial balances and profit and loss accounts and control accounts and other ledgers for auditing.\r\n7.	Liasing with the forex department of our bankers in negotiating exchange rates for withdrawal to undertake daily purchases of baskets and other costs.\r\n8.	Supervising the accounts department and coaching/advising on value for money, budgetary and financial planning.', 'full-time', 'Better Opportunity', 1),
(545, 259, 'April, 202', 'Dec, 2017', 'OUR LADY QUEEN OF AFRICA PARISH (OLA)', 'P. O. Box 245', 'ACCOUNTANT AND ADMINISTRATIVE PERSONNEL', '1.	In charge of budgeting and preparation of quarterly and yearly financial statement for the Parish and representing the Parish at Diocesan level in terms of financial issues.\r\n2.	Assess and recommend appropriate use of Church funds in consultation with the Parish development committee.\r\n3.	Processing staff salaries for payment and other statutory deductions.\r\n4.	Managing the cash book of the Church and processing payment vouchers for payment.\r\n5.	Issuing cheques, receipts and other vouchers for staff, clients, Priest and other suppliers. \r\n6.	As an advisor to the Parish Priest on matters relating to finance and administration of the Parish.\r\n7.	As an advisor to the Parish Priest on developmental projects and assisting in raising funds for projects in the Church.\r\n8.	Maintains all financial records of the Parish including bank reconciliations and payment of staff salaries and others.\r\n9.	Ensures Parish equipment, vehicles and other buildings are in good shape for smooth running of the Church.\r\n10.	Keep proper records of Parish assets and also assist the various outstations in the Parish in proper accountability and record keeping.', '', 'PROJECT ENDED', 2),
(546, 259, 'June, 2009', NULL, 'TECHNOSERVE GHANA', 'P. O. BOX 176', 'ACCOUNTANT AND BUSINESS ADVISOR', '1. I was able to identify and approach potential financial partners and financial institutions, understanding the specific barriers to smallholder lending and working with them to address those barriers where possible; work with FIs and assisted to develop financial products and/or solutions.\r\n2. I took care of the financial planning and budget preparation for the projects in the Upper East Region to ensure best financial practices and reporting same for Head of Finance at Head Office (Accra). \r\n3. Prepare monthly bank reconciliations and Cash book for the projects in Upper East for onward submission to Head Office while ensuring the daily running of the Office.\r\n4. Ensuring timely preparation and presentation of financial statements while making sure budgetary allocations are monitored to derive the spent verse the actual allocated and balances retired or re allocated. \r\n5. I worked closely with Head of finance at head office on all financial issues relating to clients and staff in designated project areas.\r\n6. I dealt directly with vendors of goods and services to ensure prompt payment for goods supplied while maintaining value for money principle in selecting vendors.  \r\n7. My work helped farmer groups to improve management and sales of farm produce and also facilitated access to high end markets.\r\n8. I ensured that effective M&amp;E data collection and information management systems were in place for program component analysis, planning, evaluation.', 'full-time', NULL, 3),
(547, 260, 'January 20', 'July 2024', 'National Ambulance service', 'Box 787, Bolgatanga', 'Emergency Medical Technician Driver.', 'Attending to the sick and injured by administering oxygen, arresting of bleeding, performing CPR and transporting patients safely to the hospital in a manner that doesn\'t affect other road user\'s.', '', 'Expiration of contract', 0),
(548, 260, 'April 2023', NULL, 'Cardinal Namdini', 'Bolgatanga', 'Emergency Response Team Driver', 'Transporting the sick and injured to to camp clinic from the field. Helping the clinic staff to treat minor or major wounds and if possible transport to a higher level of care whiles continuity of care continues. Train mine staff\'s on first aid.', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(549, 261, '2021', NULL, 'Bawku Senior High Technical School', 'P.O.Box 68', 'Accountant', 'Raising of Payment Vouchers\r\n  	 Vetting of memos approved for payment\r\n	 Raising of cheques for payment\r\nEnsuring that all cash and cheques received are receipted deposited to the bank and proper records recorded to that effect.\r\n			Maintains ledgers for transactions pertaining debtors, creditors schedules\r\n			Maintains General Journals\r\n			Monthly preparation of Reconciliation Statement\r\n			Records Entries into Cashbooks\r\n			Prepares Quarterly Reports using the approved templates\r\n            Addressing staff salary issues\r\n			Payment of WHT Tax returns to GRA', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(550, 261, '2018', NULL, 'Bawku Senior High Technical School', 'P.O.Box 68', 'Administrative Officer', 'Receive and register all incoming correspondence\r\n			Processing of promotion letters of staff\r\n			File and sort documents and its relevant attachments\r\n                                 Processing student’s admissions\r\n                                 Ensure easy tracing, location and proper custody of files\r\n                                 Weed files as and when due and ensure that all diaries are up to date \r\n                  Supervise the dispatch of all outgoing correspondence\r\n                  Ensure general cleanliness of the Registry\r\n            Supervise and direct the activities of clerical, administrative and other support   	service staff in the institution\r\n            Provide administrative support to management by arranging meetings and 	conferences and writing letters, circulars, memos and minutes\r\n                                 Perform any other official duty that may be assigne', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(551, 261, '2016', NULL, 'Mawums Quarry Limited', 'Arigu', 'Accountant', 'Supervising sales officer and weigh bridge officer\r\nEnsuring that all cash and cheques received are properly deposited to the bank and proper records recorded to that effect.\r\n			Maintains ledgers for transaction pertaining debtors, creditors, fixed assets\r\n			Monthly preparation of payroll for workers\r\n			Maintains production of quarry products records\r\n			Maintains stock ledger records for fuel and quarry products\r\n			Prepares bi-weekly, quarterly and monthly reports and budget for approval\r\nPreparation of periodic reconciliation statement of debtors, creditors and bank deposits', 'full-time', NULL, 2),
(552, 262, 'MARCH, 201', NULL, 'GHANA EDUCATION SERVICE', 'GHANA EDUCATION SERVICE, POST OFFICE BOX 110-BOLGATANGA', 'ACCOUNTANT', 'AS A DEPUTY ACCOUNTANT I PERFORM THE FOLLOWING DUTIES BUT NOT LIMITED TO;\r\n1. Daily update of all value books.\r\n2. Ensure payment vouchers are well prepared and retired accordingly.\r\n3. Prepare for value books and other documents for audit purposes.\r\n4. Assist in the preparation of quarterly and year-end financial statement for the Region.\r\n5. Prepare monthly trial balance of the Region.\r\n6. Prepare monthly reconciliations of all accounts.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(553, 263, 'OCTOBER 20', NULL, 'BINDURI SHS', 'BINDURI, UPPER EAST REGION', 'ASSISTANT HEADMASTER,ACADEMIC', 'TEACHING AND ADMINISTRATIVE DUTIES, SUBJECT; GENERAL AGRICULTURE AND PLC COORDINATOR', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
(554, 264, 'June 2025', '2012', 'Eastside Life Hospital', 'Bolgatanga', 'IT Director', '1. Technical Support &amp; Help Desk\r\n\r\n* Providing IT support to all hospital departments.\r\n* Troubleshooting hardware and software issues.\r\n* Assisting users with printers, scanners, computers, and network-related problems.\r\n* Resolving phone and communication system issues.\r\n* Responding to support requests and incidents.\r\n\r\n2. Network Administration\r\n\r\n* Managing wired and wireless network infrastructure.\r\n* Troubleshooting access points, routers, switches, and internet connectivity issues.\r\n* Monitoring network performance and uptime.\r\n* Replacing or recommending replacement of faulty network equipment.\r\n\r\n3. CCTV &amp; Security Systems Management\r\n\r\n* Monitoring CCTV systems during working hours.\r\n* Reviewing overnight CCTV footage.\r\n* Reporting suspicious activities or incidents to management.\r\n* Ensuring CCTV equipment is functioning properly.\r\n\r\n4. Database &amp; System Backup Management\r\n\r\n* Performing regular backups of the MTR12 database and other critical systems.\r\n* Verifying backup integrity.\r\n* Maintaining data recovery procedures.\r\n* Ensuring organizational data is protected against loss.\r\n\r\n5. Hardware Maintenance\r\n\r\n* Diagnosing faulty computers, printers, UPS units, access points, and other IT equipment.\r\n* Coordinating repairs and replacements.\r\n* Maintaining an inventory of IT assets.\r\n\r\n6. Software &amp; System Administration\r\n\r\n* Installing and configuring software applications.\r\n* Managing hospital information systems.\r\n* Updating systems and applications.\r\n* Maintaining user accounts and access permissions.\r\n\r\n7. Telecommunications Support\r\n\r\n* Supporting landline telephone systems.\r\n* Troubleshooting communication equipment.\r\n* Managing extensions and connectivity issues.\r\n\r\n8. Digital Media &amp; Graphics Support\r\n\r\n* Designing flyers and promotional materials for hospital events and celebrations.\r\n* Supporting the hospital\'s social media engagements.\r\n* Creating digital content for announcements and campaigns.\r\n\r\n9. IT Documentation &amp; Reporting\r\n\r\n* Preparing weekly and monthly IT reports.\r\n* Documenting technical issues and resolutions.\r\n* Recording maintenance activities and system changes.\r\n* Providing recommendations for equipment replacement and upgrades.\r\n\r\n10. IT Infrastructure Planning\r\n\r\n* Assessing equipment performance.\r\n* Recommending upgrades and replacements.\r\n* Supporting technology procurement decisions.\r\n* Assisting management with IT-related planning and budgeting.\r\n\r\n11. Information Security\r\n\r\n* Ensuring systems and data remain secure.\r\n* Monitoring user access.\r\n* Maintaining backup and recovery procedures.\r\n* Supporting compliance with organizational security policies.', 'part-time', NULL, 0),
(555, 264, 'Jan 2021', '2010', 'Senior Developer and Social Media Marketer', NULL, 'Senior Developer and Social Media Marketer', '1.	Manage Aweplaza and Gyatahost Website\r\n2.	Manage business social media handles\r\n3.	Design and Manage clients website\r\n4.	Promo clients busineses on social media\r\n5.	Design promo flyers for aweplaza and gyatahost\r\n6.	Design promo flyers for clients businesses\r\n7.	Living Streaming on Social media', 'full-time', NULL, 1),
(556, 264, '2012', '2009', 'Rlg Institute of Technology', 'Bolgatanga', 'Junior Trainee', '1.	Train students on Computer and Phone base on the institution syllabus\r\n2.	Perform software installation and troubleshooting on Computer and Phone', 'full-time', NULL, 2),
(557, 264, '2011', '2011', 'Regional Health Directorate', NULL, 'Assistant System Administrator (Attachment)', '1.	Carried out network address assignment, assignment of routing protocols.\r\n2.	Handled network devices and equipment\r\n3.	Perform software installation and troubleshooting\r\n4.	Administering and Monitoring Database', 'full-time', NULL, 3),
(558, 264, '2009', '2006', 'Fountain Gate International School', 'Bolgatanga', 'Instructor/Technician', '1.	Train students base on Ghana Education Service syllabus.\r\n2.	Install and manage LAN configuration and troubleshooting to ensure efficient communication network.\r\n3.	Carried out network address assignment, assignment of routing protocols.\r\n4.	Handled network devices and equipment\r\n5.	Conducted daily reports of computer lab to managements\r\n6.	Perform software installation and troubleshooting', 'full-time', NULL, 4),
(559, 264, '2008', '2005', 'Customary Land Secretarial', 'Bolgatanga', 'Computer Specialist', '1.	Install and manage LAN configuration and troubleshooting to ensure efficient communication network.\r\n2.	Perform servicing of computer, software installation and troubleshooting\r\n3.	Conducted daily reports of computer lab to managements\r\n4.	Administering and Monitoring Database', 'full-time', NULL, 5),
(560, 264, '2008', '2003', 'Waller Internet Cafe', 'Bolgatanga', 'Technician', '1.	Install and manage LAN configuration and troubleshooting to ensure efficient communication network.\r\n2.	Carried out network address assignment, assignment of routing protocols.\r\n3.	Handled network devices and equipment\r\n4.	Perform servicing of computer, software installation and troubleshooting', 'full-time', NULL, 6);
