(602, 286, '2024', NULL, 'NURSING AND MIDWIFERY TRAINING COLLEGE TWIFO PRASO', 'TWIFO PRASO', 'COLLEGE ADMINISTATOR', '1. Coordinate and oversee the day-to-day administrative activities of the College.\r\n\r\n2. Provide secretarial and administrative support to Management, Academic Board, and statutory committees.\r\n\r\n3. Prepare official correspondence, reports, minutes, memoranda, and institutional documents.\r\n\r\n4. Facilitate the implementation of policies, decisions, and directives of Management and governing bodies.\r\n\r\n5. Coordinate student administration activities, including admissions, registration, records management, and welfare matters.\r\n\r\n6. Maintain and manage institutional records and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.\r\n\r\n7. Liaise with external stakeholders, including regulatory agencies, partner institutions, and community organizations.\r\n\r\n8. Coordinate meetings, workshops, conferences, and official events of the College.\r\n\r\n9. Assist in human resource administration, including staff records management and personnel-related activities.\r\n\r\n10. Support the planning, monitoring, and implementation of institutional projects and programmes.\r\n\r\n11. Coordinate quality assurance activities and ensure adherence to academic and administrative standards.\r\n\r\n12. Manage information resources and support knowledge management initiatives within the institution.\r\n\r\n13. Participate in committee work and provide administrative guidance for institutional decision-making processes.\r\n\r\n14. Prepare proposals, concept notes, and reports for institutional development and stakeholder engagement.\r\n\r\n15. Perform other administrative duties assigned by Management in support of the College\'s strategic objectives.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
