(648, 310, 'NOVEMBER 2', NULL, 'UNIVERSITY FOR DEVELOPMENT STUDIES', 'P.O.Box TL1350', 'PART TIME LECTURE', 'A part-time lecturer in Accounting and a Graduate Assistant Lecturer with teaching responsibilities in Financial Accounting, Taxation, Corporate Reporting, Cost Accounting, and Auditing. I also teach at the postgraduate level, handling courses such as Public Sector Accounting and Finance, and Financial Accounting. An enthusiastic accounting professional and researcher with strong expertise in accounting education, financial reporting, taxation systems, and auditing practices. Possesses solid research capabilities, strong analytical and critical-thinking skills, and the ability to communicate complex accounting concepts clearly to diverse learners. In addition, I supervise both undergraduate and postgraduate students in research and academic work. I am a committed team player who can multitask, meet tight academic deadlines, and adapt quickly to evolving academic and professional environments without compromising quality.', 'full-time', NULL, 0),
